title: Faulty cords—extreme falling danger
author: scubadaddy
comments: One minute all was bliss. My wife and I were snuggling in to our double nest  above sharp rocks 4 feet below. With no warning at all the cable came loose from the hammock and we crashed to the ground getting bruises on our backs and hips. I set stunned for a minute thinking about all the times I have used my Eno hammock high in  trees and hanging over precipices.  Our combined weight is 100 pounds less than the product rating So that should not have been a factor.There’s no way to check the cord  for defects because it’s hidden inside the fabric. My cord did not break. It simply came loose. I’m guessing they just tied it with some kind of invincible knot up in the fabric.Before when I saw these things stacked six and eight high I thought it was cool but now it scares me to death to think about that. Sad to say, Do not trust your life to this product.

title: Nests all around!
author: Tom Hightower
comments: edit 12/28/2017Well since the original review the boys, and one of our huskies have made the transition to outside hammock-ing with under quilts and all. In the updated photos I have included you can see the new hammocks outside in a carport. Great place to test them sleeping externally while having close access to the home should they wish to go inside. Yes dear old dad slept outside with them. We even slept out side on xmas eve looking for Santa. Luckily he was smart enough to wait till they had fallen asleep. Which honestly took less time than there beds inside. Even with an outside temp in the 30'sWith the appropriate gear you can use your hammock year round. We do!Original :I absolutely love this/these hammocks. They have a wide range of colors to choose from. We purchased 4 over the last year. A single, Double and Double deluxe.The singles were for our kids and the double and deluxe were for the wife and myself. Truth be told I didn't realize I had a deluxe till after the purchase was complete. Oh well. I love the extra fabric of the double and the deluxe. The double safely held myself and my bouncy husky with no problem. One just bedded down and slept another well he wasn't having anything to do with it.We purchased the wall hanging mounts and setup ours for use while indoors too. What better way to introduce 2 kids to hammock-ing slowly. Lets just say they slept better in their hammocks than in their own rooms.I found out rather quickly why even a slow gentle breeze cools you down. So, we added in our sleeping bags and were toasty all night. Our next adventure the outdoor test with the kids. It will be their first outdoor sleeping. Heres hoping that goes well for this dad.When out doors I would highly recommend a set of ENO Eagles Nest Outfitters - Atlas Straps XL, Hammock Suspension System, Black. They are used to string the hammock between trees, its much easier than anything else like rope. I look forward to many years of continued use out of all our purchases.

title: NICE HANGER!
author: Old Dog
comments: I was skeptical that I would be comfortable in any "packable" hammock.  At 6'3" (235 lbs) I always seem too tall or heavy for anything that others seem to fit well. This hammock has changed that. I love this thing! I got it for Father's Day and have used it several times over the past two weeks. It is easy to pack and easy to set up (you will need hammock straps to affix it to a tree ... I suggest Rallt straps which are the ones I purchased and have used successfully several times).  The hammock is plenty long and wide for me and would even be better for someone under 6 foot.  I fall asleep like a baby as soon as I stop hiking and fall into this cocoon. It's been fun to carry on our local (mtn) hiking trails and deploying out between two trees just off the trail.  I wish I had purchased this years ago to add to my hiking enjoyment. Get one ... you'll love it! Enjoy!

Two people is very close cuddle space, it is nice for relaxing in, sitting side by side, and sometimes sleeping. If you want more comfort, you can spread out the ends for more room. We are thinking of  getting a longer one for even more space. :) This one has made it through a ton of wear and tear, though!

title: ENO (EAGLES NEST OUTFITTERS) double nest blue navy
author: Mary
comments: I bought this to replace my queen size bed, yes you heard me right! I am a single woman. And really there is no need for me to have a bed right now. Because I don't have anybody to share it with. Anyways...this hammock is a must have!! It's very very comfortable!  I sleep in this hammock every night.  I don't nearly toss and turn as much as I did in a bed. I simply lay comfortably.  A hammock rocks you to sleep.  And my  cat loves it as well. Plenty of room for two to sit. Not to sleep. Unless you want your limbs to fall asleep. One problem I. Found is you get cold underneath. But I simply solved that with a mummy sleeping bag. After sleeping in this hammock for 12 days so far, I get a very good night's sleep. I recommend laying at a angle! As all YouTube reviews say. And I also plan using this on the beach. To buy the portable hammock frame simply go to these websites,- happytimeslife.com-eaglesnestoutfittersinc.comAt happy times life you can either buy just the frame or the combo frame and hammock. But you get to only choose 3 colors for combo.  My opinion ENO has way more colors. Double nest is a staff favorite.  In the package it's tightly packed in a carrying bag.  The bag is sort of sewn to the hammock so you won't loose the bag.ENO Comes with:-two carabiner-two stickers- No tree straps you will need to buy additional if attaching to trees

My young sons loved to play in it and it was good for me sleeping. I would have preferred a slightly longer hammock for my 6’1” frame but it worked and it packed small. I spend a week in it at scout camp with the ENO rain fly and it did great, much better than the tents that were flooded in the down pours. When I took it on a second week long scout camp, it split down the middle on the first night, very bad timing, leaving me up the proverbial creek. I completed the ENO on-line warranty claim form 3 times and never received a response. I also could not get anyone on the phone. NEVER AGAIN buy ENO.

title: There is no better portable hammock available
author: Michael
comments: There is no better portable hammock available.  Period.  I have had mine for years, and have given dozens to friends/family as gifts (always with the atlas straps).  I'm 6 foot, 190 pounds, and would definitely get the DoubleNest again if I had to re-purchase - and 90% of the time it's just me in the hammock.  The other 10% the dog is in it with me.  Can't get my wife on board for some reason...  It's light and compact for traveling (about the size of a softball when packed).  I keep mine in my car at all times, and have been known to pull over and lounge when driving through wooded areas.  Other hammocks I've owned stayed in the closet or my camping bag because they were cumbersome or too finicky to easily deploy.  This one I use at least once a week just around the house for reading, relaxing, etc.

title: My only Issue - Too Small For My Liking
author: Average Guy
comments: I purchased this product and immediately took it on a 2 night backpacking trip with a friend who has a Grand Trunk hammock which I had borrowed for a previous backpacking trip and slept in.  I expected this ENO hammock to be similar but it is considerably smaller and for that reason I do not like it.  I am 5'11" and about 170 lbs. When I am in the Grand Trunk it will completely close around me.  It almost feels like a tent and there is no concern of falling out.  The ENO did not even come close to closing around me and I always feel some part of me is either hanging out or on the edge.  To be fair, since it was colder out, I placed a backpacking Thermarest EVO Lite air mattress under me to help provide insulation and this certainly contributed to the issue.I probably should have returned it but instead I kept it.  I will let my son use it since he is smaller and before my next trip I will purchase the Grand Trunk.The ENO does have good quality construction and worked flawlessly in every other way.  However, make sure you purchase the ENO Atlas straps which are fantastic.  Overall, I find sleeping in a hammock far more comfortable than a tent when backpacking if you expect to have trees to be able to hang it from.

title: I have honestly told people that it is easily on of my favorite purchases over the last several ...
author: R.Roach
comments: What can I say about the ENO DoubleNest Hammock?Well, in one phrase, I have honestly told people that it is easily on of my favorite purchases over the last several years.ENO makes some really nice and enjoyable products as I have come to discover.  I have since gone on to buy the Atlas Straps, the Pro Fly XL rain tarp, and the Guardian Bugnet, all very worth looking into as well.Well to begin this hammock as many nowadays, comes in a very small package when it is stored, probably about the size of two average sized fists.  Weird measurement I know, but they were what was in front of me and it's close enough!  It only takes about 5-7 minutes at most to set this hammock up, particularly if you have the Atlas straps or a similar hanging system.  It is also very comfortable and breathable for that great hammock feel, especially on a hot day.  The D-ring hooks that it hangs with a very convenient as well.  I wouldn't run off to climb with them, but they are rated at 400Ib between them and the rest of the implements.  This is rated for two people as well which is nice for those relaxing evenings at camp or on the trail.  It is as most have said fairly tight for two however so this is really a close friend or significant other type of situation.  Also, from an actual sleeping perspective, because of the nature of hammock sleeping and the somewhat restricted range of motion, I wouldn't really advise sharing the hammock with another person overnight.  It can certainly be done, but unless you're a very sound sleeper you may not stay very comfortable, especially with a sleeping bag or two in the hammock with you.Overall I love this hammock and the other accessories I have for it.  It can be a little pricey, but I don't mind spending a little bit more to support a company I really like.  I intend on buying one for my dad as a gift very soon.  Do yourself a favor and buy one to keep in the car, it takes up basically no room and you'll always be glad to pull it out in a pinch or for those on the spot times when you just need to do some lounging.

title: High quality, but extremely overpriced and short
author: jswright2005
comments: Look, ENO is great for getting people into hammocking by having huge availability, and simple suspension systems that anyone can understand.But no matter how you look at it, this is not at all worth the price you pay for it.For starters, the hammock is short. And I mean really short in comparison to standard double hammocks. At 9'4", it is 12" shorter than the 10'6" Grand Trunk Double, and a whopping 20" shorter than a standard 11' hammock by many cottage vendors such as Dutchware Gear. This may not sound like much of a difference, or you might think, "hey, I'm short, I won't miss the extra length," but this simply isn't true. No matter how tall or short you are, you will notice and appreciate a longer hammock.Once properly hung at a 30 degree angle from the trees with proper sag (recommend adding a structural ridgeline for this), you will want to lay on a diagonal, no parallel/in-line with the hammock so you can sprawl out and practically lay flat in the hammock.This is where you will really feel the tension and small size of this hammock. Even when perfectly hung, I will get a kink in my neck after lying in this hammock long enough. It simply isn't big enough.So, for $70 retail price, you're getting less comfort, less material, and much heavier weight with no gain in strength when compared to a $43 11' Dutchware. In my opinion, you just shouldn't get this over a Dutchware. There is no benefit.Also, the Atlas Straps and cheaper alternatives...while easy, they are insanely heavy, and again, ENO is overpriced. Get a lightweight suspension system like the combination whoopie sling/marlin spike hitch/toggle system. You'll see online that this is what all the more experienced hammockers do.So basically, do some research, and very quickly you will see that this is not a good buy for the money.I appreciate that ENO gives hammocking some great exposure, but it uses its position to overprice for compromised products.Good luck, and happy hanging!

title: Great hammock for outdoor adventures
author: Amazon Customer
comments: The Eagles Nest Outfitters DoubleNest Hammock is great for someone who enjoys spending time outside and connecting with nature.  As long as you can find two trees that are close to each other, you can relax in this hammock all day long.The DoubleNest Hammock has several features that make it a worthwhile purchase.  First of all, Eagles Nest Outfitters hammocks are very durable; I bought this hammock 3 years ago and have used it over 100 times but it shows no signs of wear.  It has triple interlocking stitching which ensures that the hammock stays functional no matter how many times it is used. In addition, this hammock is made of nylon which is lightweight and soft making it the perfect place to lay all day or night. The DoubleNest hammock can hold up to 400 pounds, which is quite a lot considering it is only a very thin piece of material. Another great feature of this hammock is that it is large enough to fit two people comfortably, but it is also compact enough to travel with or throw in your backpack. Fully extended the hammock is over 9 feet long however, it can be compacted to only 5x4 inches. This hammock is able to roll up and fit inside a bag that is attached to the hammock; this is very convenient for storage purposes and the fact that the bag is attached ensures that you wont lose it, no matter how many adventures you embark upon. The DoubleNest Hammock also comes with carabineer attachments which make setting up your hammock quick and easy, no matter where you are.  You can also buy this product in a variety of colors which is great because you will be able to find one that fits your personal style.  This hammock can also be used for camping; the double hammock is especially great for sleeping because you are able to fold the hammock over yourself to stay warm, dry, and away from bugs.The one downside to this hammock is that it can be more expensive than other hammocks on the market.  However, I believe that you get what you pay for.  ENO is a great and well-known brand in the camping world and they make a very high quality product.Overall I highly recommend the Eagles Nest Outfitters DoubleNest Hammock.  If you love camping and hanging out outdoors you will not regret investing in this product.  The DoubleNest Hammock can take your outdoor adventure to the next level.

title: All of my hopes and dreams of what a hammock could be have been met in the reality of ENO.
author: Scott B.
comments: This thing is super quality. I've only had one other hammock in my life, and it was way too narrow to sleep in. This thing has some generous amount of room without the added weight. It's also ridiculously strong. I'm about 6' 1", 225lbs and I don't ever get the familiar feeling that I'm going to pop a seam when I'm shifting my weight around in this thing. Fully stretching out is so comfy, it's wonderful. You can also have enough room to have 2 people in it, but I would say that 2 people sitting in it sideways is more ideal than laying in it (unless you're wanting to either get to know this person REALLY well, or perhaps start a small family). Set up is a cinch. You literally just wrap clip the carabiner into the pre-made rope loops and straps around the trees and you're good to go. I accidentally dropped it (while it was bundled) in the creek one evening and a dog almost grabbed it and ran off with it, but I was lucky enough to get it before he has had way with it. It definitely was wet, but once I opened it up ans shook it out, it dried in like a minute and a half. No big. The color is everything I wanted. It makes me think of Bob Marley, which is super cool for just chilling. I also found that there is enough material to wrap over yourself for a little added warmth and bug coverage. Of course, you'll probably want to get a bug net if you're going to pull an all nigher in it.

title: Good Quality but Very Pricey
author: j
comments: I purchased this to take with me on a trip to Hawaii. It makes sense, Hawaii and hammocks, so obviously had to get one. I purchased this because my classmates at my university had talked about this since I started attending, so figured it would be a good brand. I also follow Derek Hansen's blog and purchased his book. It contains quite a bit of information about hammocks for anyone interested. The Ultimate Hang: An Illustrated Guide To Hammock Camping. I purchased the DoubleNest because I am 6'4" and weight nearly 300 pounds, so I knew a single wouldn't work for me. I have had this nearly two years now and really haven't had any issues with it. I did replace the carabiners at the ends with more sturdy ones, so that brought some extra piece of mind. I purchased this in conjunction with Eno's Atlas straps to hang up with. Overall quality is great. The problem I have with it and the reason I deducted 1 star is price. Between this and the Atlas straps, I forked out nearly $100. I can find a hammock and strap kit for half that! I realize now that I could've gotten a much better deal, but at the time I just wanted to use the same brand my peers used. In the future though, I think I will opt for more reasonably priced options, unless this price goes down.

comments: I recently went camping with friends, and ended up sleeping in a hammock other than my ENO. I have never appreciated how much smart design and engineering went into the DoubleNest as when I was fighting to stay in my borrowed knock-off brand at three in the morning. The DoubleNest is ostensibly a simple product, with plain but durable lightweight materials and a seemingly normal attachment system. What you don't appreciate at first sight is how hard the ENO hammocks work to keep your tossing and turning self from flipping the hammock over while you sleep. The build quality in ENO gear is top of the class, and take down and set up are easy with a little practice. I will say, however, that the 'Double' in DoubleNest is very much up to interpretation. If you aren't an exceptionally cuddly person, you'll probably want your own hammock. Camping can be an exercise in enduring discomfort, but with an ENO hammock, you've got a little cradle of comfort that goes with you anywhere.

I have set up my hammock enough times to confidently say I know how to set it up properly and what angle they should be it. I still really do like my hammock and so I went out and got climbing grade carbiners, something I can really trust. I emailed ENO about this and I didn't feel like they handled it well telling me that I didn't close the carbiner or set it up properly. If they want to be a top brand for hammocks they should be using higher quality carbiners. So my trust has been lost really and I'm slowly looking to get different straps and eventually a new hammock as well.

title: YOU CANNOT BE COMFORTABLE WITH TWO PEOPLE IN THIS HAMMOCK.
author: Amazon Customer
comments: YOU CANNOT BE COMFORTABLE WITH TWO PEOPLE IN THIS HAMMOCK. My issue with eno is that the "double nest" is not remotely large enough for two normal sized human beings. When you attempt to get in w another person it's an awkward mess of butting knees and accidental copping of feels. This fact makes me question how ridiculously small a "single nest" could be. To add insult to injury, the stuff sack that attaches to the side of the hammock ripped off after a few weeks of relatively heavy use. But there are good things about eno. I love their straps, really easy to set up, conveniently long, and undoubtedly strong. The carabineers on each end seem cleverly engineered and quite strong as well. It's ironic that the only part this hammock company got wrong was the actual hammock... When you want to buy a hammock eno is the first brand you hear of. Everyone has one. I believe this is because they were the first or one of the first to manufacture parachute material hammocks. I'm no internet complainer but it makes me mad when I pay a lotta money for a mediocre product. The hype of the company doesn't live up to its standard nor justify the price point of their products. IF YOU WANT AN AWESOME DOUBLE PARACHUTE HAMMOCK GET A "GRAND TRUNK" BRAND DOUBLE. But be sure to get some eno straps cuz they're great.

title: it is important to realize that a good, lightweight tent will weigh less than a hammock ...
author: Alexi
comments: To preface this, I am a minimalist backpacker/camper. Considering this hammock is double nested, it does compact fairly small and it decently lightweight. If you're going the route of using a hammock instead of a tent, it is important to realize that a good, lightweight tent will weigh less than a hammock setup (including tarp and suspension system.) The hammock setup mostly exists to provide you the freedom of choice to sleep comfortably above the ground, and with clear skies, a lovely, unobstructed view to fall asleep to, as well as a casual way to rest and relax during the day. This hammock serves those purposes wonderfully.As far as using it for two people, prepare to be close. A double nested hammock is not meant for a couple that gets hot and stuffy and cramped in the middle of the night. If you're a couple that likes to cuddle, and are a bit on the smaller side, then I think you'll find this hammock to suit your needs both wonderfully and comfortably as my boyfriend and I did. As a single person hammock, it does provide great protection from bugs and it's extra comfy and roomy. As with all hammocks, I suggest having something underneath you on cooler nights to protect from the under draft, and it also helps with keeping away mosquitos. This material is light and breathable, so they will bite you if unexposed skin is pressed against the hammock.For what it was made for, this hammock does the job, and it remains a permanent part of my camping gear.

title: Perfect for a couple, luxurious for a single
author: Deborah C White
comments: I'm an avid camper but have never really liked the idea of sleeping exposed to elements and have always instead elected for a tent. However, as I've gotten older, my back problems (scoliosis) have increased and sleeping on the ground inside a tent has been more and more troublesome, even with an air mattress. My wife finally had enough of my groaning in the morning and decided to buy us this hammock. I was pretty skeptical but after one night of sleeping in it, I'm hooked. I'll never sleep on the ground again. Now, admittedly, I can't compare this with other hammocks as this is the only one I've owned. However, I will say that I can't imagine them being much better. She and I can both easily fit in it and cuddle together as there is more than enough fabric to contain us both. Combined, we actually exceed the 400 lb limit by a bit. I'm a bit on the heavier side. Yet it still holds up with no problem at all. I've been using it for over a year now and love it. Additionally, there's enough extra material that if I'm sleeping in it solo, I can wrap the remainder over the top of me and "cocoon" myself. This was particularly helpful on a dewy morning last weekend. I awoke to a wet hammock and a dry sleeping bag. Love it.

title: Best Piece of Outdoor Gear You Can Buy!
author: Kate
comments: I have had my ENO Double nest for SEVEN YEARS. That is seven years of packing, unpacking, toting, Stretching, scrambling in and out with cats and dogs and sharp pens/pencils from studying during college. This hammock will NOT disappoint. While it is a bit pricey, divide by at least seven and look at what you're spending for every year's worth of gorgeous days and camping, hiking, backyard relaxing or park playing.For campers: I suggest getting the double nest even if you will be the only one using it. You will be able to place something heavy in the packing pocket attached on the side, swing it over across yourself and have a good amount of "cocoon" room to keep bugs off or feel less exposed even when under netting or tarps.For hikers: LIGHTWEIGHT! Same tips apply. Just a little extra weight and you can fit two people for a break along the trail, or sleeping. Double is the way to go!For Backyard adventurers: This is a great option for "lawn furniture" when you have backyard parties and cookouts. Comfy for the Sunday nap, reading with littles and cuddling your furbaby in the shade. Get the straps specially made for hammock hanging and set up is a cinch!Park Players: My only advice is to bring it , but KNOW YOUR PARKS. Some places will not allow you to hang these up because of possible damage to trees. I have heard some will let you know if they are welcome, others won't  and some will allow you to hang them but only with some kind of cloth underneath the strap to prevent bark stripping. This only requires a phone call or asking the ranger station.Looking for a graduation gift for your future college student?Want something unique for your out-door loving Mom or Dad for mother's day and father's day?Are you and your spouse looking to spend more time together on the trail?Want to make special memories with the kids?This hammock is one of the few things you can get without any buyers remorse.*** I did not receive any benefits for writing this review, that's how much I love ENOS!!! ***

title: I love the cocoon style

comments: I love my hammock!! It arrived at my house very quickly and was packaged very nicely. When I opened it, the hammock was packed down very small and I thought wow this thing is no very big. I opened it up and set it up(with mallome straps, I highly recommend) and was amazed at the ease of use. The included carabineers are very nice and hold up to 400 lbs(181 kg). The hammock is sewed into the bag so that you never lose it and believe it or not the hammock easily packs down back into the bag. It takes a little practice to learn how to lay in it comfortably and I have laid in this hammock for 3 hours at a time so far and had no back, neck, or leg pain. I plan to camp for 5 nights with this on memorial day 2016. I find the best part of this is to store your gear in the included pouch and then lay it over the other side of the hammock creating a great cocoon effect and you stay cozy and comfortable.Pros:Rich colorhigh weight capacityquality hardware includedsewn in compression bagdouble nest is very adequate to hold 2 peoplecomfortablelight weightCons:takes a little practice to get just rightI would definitely buy another one and highly recommend

title: A great hammock, but not all that you need in one package.
author: Colt F.
comments: I recently acquired this hammock as my first, and I do have to say that it is a great hammock at a good price. I'm 5'10 and weigh 290 lbs and I can sleep in this comfortably. My only issue with these hammocks is that they don't include some kind of basic straps nor cordage for hanging. For the price if you were to walk into any retailer that had these it's a great deal and you come out ahead. However, with just five minutes of basic search on Amazons site one can find a multitude of other brands that both straps and hammock can be bought for the same price as this ENO. Is it worth the money, sure thing, it's a great value. But I'd like to see ENO step up the game, and include a basic hanging system in the same package for the same price. As an example I spent 6 bucks at my local provider of 550 paracord and made two 12ft straps in about 30 minutes. Final thought Eno's Hammocks are a buy, especially if you are a first time hammock user and want to see if you like it. Just be aware that they are not all inclusive.

It's extra comfy with a pillow. You definitely should invest in the Atlas XL straps so you can hang it almost anywhere. Get the right amount of sag and you'll never want to get out of this hammock. I look forward to some more lazy spring and summer days in it even though I've steadily used it throughout the winter for some snow hammocking near frozen lakes. One regret I have is the color, this bright green-yellow definitely attracts bugs in the warmer weather than, say, a darker color would, but I pay it no mind. title: Professional Power Lounging
author: Love muffin sugar plum
comments: Im a professional power lounger with over 40 years of experience under my belt.  This was the very first portable power lounger that I bought.  Its small and light weight and fits easily into my backpack without taking up a lot of space.SIZE:  Yes size does matter.  Im 5'10" tall and 220 lbs.  I prefer the extra space that this double size offers.  It allows for plenty of room to add a sleeping mat and sleeping bag.  I can also pull the sides over the top to have a cocoon type of effect which is nice for shading the sun.  I can also roll over and curl up my knees for side sleeping.  Sometimes I even sit up in the hammock with my feet hanging out (like sitting on a couch) and pull the back side up for neck and head support.WARMTH:  This breathes, therefore its not warm.  I add a sleeping pad and a sleeping bag.  A sleeping bag alone is not enough because the loft gets compressed causing it to lose its effectiveness.  The ultimate would be a hammock quilt attached to the outside of the hammock, but those are expensive (note to self:  add to wish list).STRENGTH:  Plenty strong enough for me at 220.  The wife and I can both fit in this, but its not as comfortable as each having our own.  Plus she snores <U+0001F634><U+0001F4A4> <U+0001F4A4>and then blames it on me<U+0001F644>.HANGING:  Hanging is super easy IF you have hammock straps, which I HIGHLY recommend.  I have three sets, one is ENO brand, but they all seem pretty similar.

title: Same Quality and Smaller then Cheaper Competitors.  Can not recommend.
author: Vexatious
comments: I bought this one and also a cheaper competitor version.  I could not honestly tell any difference in quality between then, not enough to justify any increase in price over the competitor Hammocks.  My biggest problem is it is also a lot smaller then the competitor one I bought. SO I paid more for a smaller hammock of the same quality in my opinion.  I recommend buying the cheaper competitor version that includes straps and saving yourself $30. These are also made in Vietnam, same location as the competitors so once again not sure where the price increase is derived from.  It is so much smaller in comparison that I thought maybe they had sent me the wrong one... then I saw it clearly states on the product that its the DoubleNest....The Hammock itself appears to be well made, no problems or issues, The smaller size I feel did make it less comfortable then the competitor, to the point my wife decided after trying we would never both sit in this one again and simply use the other one.  Good product but when you can buy the same quality that is larger with straps included for less there is no point in buying this.

title: Best Purchase Ever!
author: SouthernStorm
comments: This is our first ENO hammock, and all the hype I've heard about them is perfectly justified in this neat, little package. I ordered this as a Christmas gift for my 12 yr old daughter, and she LOVES IT! Even though it was only 35 degrees outside, my daughter set it up and took a warm blanket with her to enjoy trying it out. Super easy to set up, strong and durable fabric, awesome colors, and balls up in it's own built in pouch that takes up less room in an overnight bag than a hooded sweatshirt. It should be noted that these hammocks do not come with the strap system needed for hanging it, so remember to order your straps! We used the Heavy Duty Extra Long Hang Tight Hammock System straps from Nature's Hangout. They are much better than some of the Atlas straps used by ENO and have far more loops to get the perfect height. Overall I love this product and can't wait to take it beyond our backyard as we travel. Awesome product at an affordable price!

The material is very soft and feels good against your skin and it does allow wind to move through it easily making it very comfortable even during the summer. It's extremely easy to fold back up and fit into the bag or take out which makes storing the hammock a breeze! Absolutely in love with it!

title: From a First Timer's POV
author: Kristina
comments: I bought my husband this hammock along with the ENO Atlas straps everyone recommends.We went out and tested it today after a short hike, and it does in fact house two average sized people quite well. Using the straps made hooking up the hammock to trees a lot easier. Just make sure you find two trees that are sturdy and the right distance apart.Not many people review this product from a first timer's point of view, so make sure you watch a few videos on how to properly set up a hammock before use. It is very easy to use.Comfortability was so good that we both almost fell asleep. With two people in the hammock, the extra material that would normally cover one person is not there, so bring some sleeping bags or blankets. Wind does blow through it, but a sleeping bag would get rid of that issue.Overall, my husband absolutely loves his gift, and we will go back out to camp with it soon. :) Highly recommend.

title: To Females in the 5'3 120lb range: Singlenest or Doublenest (Get the Double!)
author: 1like2run
comments: I'm 5'3 120lb female and I was debating between the single or the doublenest hammock. I read through reviews and looked at videos online and most were given by males over 5'10+ in the 150-180lb range; needless to say, I was skeptical how accurate their reviews would be with respect to my size and stature.The biggest concern I had was that the singlenest would be too small and unfavorable with company, and that the doublenest would wrapped me up like a burrito.I ended up buying the doublenest and it is great!! Very roomy and comfortable. It does create a burrito effect if I were to lay straight parallel in the hammock with my arms by my side, but since that's an awkward position anyway, I didn't have to worry about getting swallowed up. I prefer lying at an angle (stretching the fabric out wider rather than having it tunnel over me) or having my arms out bracketing the side of the hammock.If you're still not convinced, just remember that the doublenest is intended for two people! So just shell out the extra $10 bucks or so (which is nothing) and get the double and you can invite your friends to hang in your hammock with you!I set up my doublenest for the first time today at a park and got complimented by three passerby and a ton of smiles from people checking out the hammock! Go buy yours now :)

title: A Great Hammock
author: Gena R.
comments: I bought this hammock earlier this year, and it has quickly become one of my favorite outdoor items (along with the ENO Atlas straps). I take it with me whenever I'm going to be outside. It is very easy to set up and take down (it takes me < 5 minutes to do both). It is extremely comfortable, and great for relaxing and sleeping. A single person using this hammock can completely close it over them from the top (as seen in the picture). I have tested the 400 lb. weight limit with two people, and the it holds up great. If using it for sleeping, I would recommend getting some sort of underquilt since a breeze makes for a cold, unpleasant night.

title: One of the best things we own
author: Baygent
comments: I'd wanted a hammock for a long time and looked at a variety of styles and models and am so glad I opted for the Eagle's Nest.  It's a breeze to set up.  We use the straps (purchased separately) to attach it to trees.  The straps don't damage the trees and when taken down, the hammock easily folds up into the attached pouch that's no bigger than a small purse.  Plus, it's very lightweight so it's easy to take on trips.  You can sit in the hammock and use it as a swing, as a regular hammock, or you can pull the flap over you and be completely enclosed like a cocoon.  My son loves playing in the hammock and he can be rough on things but it seems very sturdy.  Everyone who has tried it has enjoyed it.

title: ENO DoubleNest Hammock: Review
author: Hannah R Otis
comments: ENO DoubleNest HammockI bought my Eagles Nest Outfitters (ENO) DoubleNest Hammock in December of 2014. I am very impressed with the product, as it tailors to camping needs and leisure time. If you’re looking to camp and sleep with your hammock, or just to use it around home, this product is very practical and durable.While using this product I noticed that it was very durable. All of the seams are triple stitched, and don’t bulge or tare when you have two people in it. There are three sections of fabric that you lay on all connected by this stitching. The sectioning will allow the weight to be allocated to each set of stitches, and also let you wrap or “cocoon” yourself up for shade.ENO’s website says that you can put up to 400 pounds of pressure on the fabric. Though this is a rough estimate, I have been able to put nearly 500 pounds without any effect. The price of the product reflects the durability, as it is on the higher side. If you’re looking for something simpler, a cheaper style of these hammocks may serve you well too.One of the best things about the product is its portability. You will be able to carry around the bag anywhere in preparation of setting it up. When in the bag, the hammock is about the size of a large grapefruit, allowing you to easily place it, or clip it to a backpack.The lightweight fabric is very beneficial when you are looking to have a light load for camping. Instead of carrying and setting up a tent, popping your hammock up to sleep will serve as an easy alternative. When sleeping in the hammock it may be hard to get used to the hanging sensation, but it will take a large amount of stress off of your spine and joints. Which is great for when you don’t want to wake up sore after a night of camping.I hope you were able to find this review on the Eagles Nest Outfitters DoubleNest Hammock helpful on your search for a new product.

title: Durable & Comfortable
author: kate
comments: The ENO Double Nest Hammock is built with an active outdoor person’s needs in mind. It is ideal for anyone who is looking for an effortless, and reliable product for sleeping outside. The hammock is durable, and comfortable. It is also very quick and easy to set up, and packs away nicely into any backpack or bag.All of ENO’s products are extremely durable and long lasting. The hammock itself can hold up to 400 lbs., and the seams have been triple stitched for maximum durability. The hammock comes with climbing style aluminum wire-gate carabineers, which are connected to the hammock by nautical grade line. Overall, this hammock is as strong and reliable as it gets.Comfort is definitely something that you need to consider when purchasing a product that you are going to sleep in, and the ENO Double Nest Hammock will surely meet your needs. It is made up of a breathable, and quick drying nylon that will maintain its shape and conform to your body. If you are a side sleeper, like me, you will find that this hammock may even be more comfortable than a standard sleeping pad on the ground. If you are looking to use the hammock in cooler temperatures, the hammock is wide enough to hold a sleeping pad for more insulation.You will need to buy the suspension system in order to hang the hammock up. However, this enables you to choose the straps that best fit your needs when it comes to size. For example, if you are going to be using this hammock in an area with larger trees, such as the Redwoods, you may want to purchase the corresponding XL Straps. Whereas if you are in the Midwest where the trees are smaller, the regular straps will do the trick.If you decide to enhance your outdoor experiences by investing in the ENO Double Nest Hammock, you will surely be satisfied with the durability and comfort it will provide.

title: Great Hammock
author: Allison Myers
comments: This hammock is great no matter what you’re going to use it for-camping, reading, or traveling. I have taken it with me on a number of trips and have used it at home as well. It scrunches up to a surprisingly small size when trying to pack it into a duffel or suitcase, and the bag provided for the hammock is lightweight and thin so as not to add any extra weight or volume to your luggage. The straps also come with their own bag allowing them to be neatly packed away but separate from the hammock.The hammock is super easy to set up- I have hung it in a variety of places by myself with no issues. One issue is that the LONG STRAPS do still have their limitations. I had debated ordering with the REGULAR STRAPS OR THE LONG STRAPS, but am very glad I picked the latter. They do well with small to medium sized trees, but I wish they were a bit longer to accommodate trees with larger trunks or a slightly larger gap between two trees. The straps are also adjustable, so if the gap is smaller, there is no need to worry about a hammock that sits too low. That being said, the LONG STRAPS are definitely worth the extra money.Using the hammock has been great so far. It comes with me on most trips whether that’s camping in the Upper Peninsula (where it not only provides a place to sleep outside of the tent, but also just a nice place to relax and read) or while living in Europe for a semester. When studying abroad, I had limited space in my luggage to bring extra non-essential items, but since it packs into a really small and light bag, it took very little space in my suitcase. On many occasions, I was very happy I had it with me to escape the bustle of Rome by taking it to a park for an afternoon of relaxing.The hammock’s quality is great. I have had it a year and used it a number of times, yet it has not developed any tears or scuffs. It’s surprisingly strong for how thin it is. Not only do two people comfortably fit inside, it does not seem to strain at all. Even my 70 pound dog has enjoyed the hammock!Overall, I highly recommend the hammock. It’s light, portable, easily set up, and durable. I also highly recommend that anyone buy it with the LONG STRAPS, and my only complaint is that I wish they were even just a bit longer.

comments: I use this all the time to camp, backpack, lounge or whatever. ENO is the best, they can be expensive but you pay for what you get. This hammock has never let me down and continues to hold its quality. The fabric dries out quickly and stays soft. Machine washable. Just keep it away from fire embers they will go right through the fabric.

title: Perfect product!!
author: Reese Huddleston
comments: Best hammock brand in the world!! Quality every time. Standard replacement of my previous double hammock after it had endured 5 years of nightly use. Love the compression sack that comes with it too. Couldn't be happier.

title: My wife and I agree that the hammock would be fine, perhaps even comfortable
author: Stefan B.
comments: Two people should NEVER attempt to sleep in a DoubleNest Hammock. We took this on the Allagash River and I can say with the utmost conviction that it was the most uncomfortable week of camping ever. My wife and I agree that the hammock would be fine, perhaps even comfortable, for a single person. We are both small people and although I had heard people say it’s uncomfortable with two people I thought it would be at least manageable. I was wrong. Good thing we brought a backup tent in the canoe.

title: Durable and Colorful
author: ohmywurd
comments: Purchased this as a gift for Father's Day and the color was as pictured. The material seems sturdy and although we have yet to test two people in it, it holds perfectly with the Atlas Straps. I was amazed at how easy it was to stuff back into the small bag and how lightweight it was. It also doesn't take very long to dry. Shortly after we set it up in the back yard it rained and got pretty damp. We brought it inside and spread it out and it dried within a few hours and we were able to pack it back away. I now understand the obsession with ENO hammocks, and I believe they are well worth the price for their ease of use and durability.

The atlas straps (sold separately but are worth the $30) are an excellent addition and make the hammock setup easy to put virtually anywhere. Love this hammock! Fun colors, very durable. Excellent for backpackers and outdoor lovers :)

title: Great hammock for relaxing outdoors
author: Ben
comments: This hammock is easy to set up and take down. It rolls up to about the size of a grapefruit and stores in its own attached bag. When the hammock is set up, the bag hangs off to the side, so you can use it to hold things like your phone or a book. The parachute-like material is strong and durable, and I have had no tears or loose threads in 3+ years of use. Carabiners on the ends can attach easily to either the "slap straps" also made by ENO or a rope with well-tied knots. When two people sit in the hammock at ones, they do tend to slide toward the middle, but once you find a comfortable position, you won't want to get out. Highly recommend this hammock.

Fit easily in my backpack with very minimal weight, will defintely be using this ALL the time.  Spend the extra money for ENO products,

title: A camping must have...
author: Andrea Harrison
comments: I absolutely love my Eagle Nest Outfitters DoubleNest Hammock! The only problem is that I will need to buy another one because my family of five are all arguing about which person(s) gets to use it next. Wonderful quality and workmanship and it truly can hold and has enough room for two people to comfortably use it. A valuable addition to our camping experience!

title: Going solo in the double
author: loftapartment
comments: Wow. This makes the great outdoors downright luxurious. (1) Find a spot with a view, (2) hang the hammock, (3) bliss out. It takes all of 5 minutes to set up or pack up (make sure you get the Atlas straps). If you are new to camping hammocks, there are helpful tips and instructions on YouTube and elsewhere. The nylon is porous - on a hot day your backside stays cool and dry. On a cool night, you need some layers. So small and light, the hammock + straps fits in my biking backpack with room to spare. And olive/olive is perfect for stealth hanging in the woods. Just be warned ... hammocks are addictive. Seriously.

title: Small, compact, and comfortable hammock.
author: Elle Emme
comments: This is a GREAT hammock! I actually have this on hand most of the time. I use it when we hike to our favorite swimming holes, I use it when my husband insists on a fishing trip in the mountains, or even when we go camping.It packs up small into the attached bag on the side of the hammock, and while it doesn't have to be used speciffically with the ENO Slap Straps, that is what I was gifted with this, so it is what we use.I have used both the double and the single, and I much prefer the double for camping overnight. It doesn't feel as "tippy" for me as I roll around or switch positions, or even get into the sleeping bag or change clothes inside the hammock.We have bought a few of these, and will be looking for another hammock for our son soon.

title: This hammock is fantastic! It's great camping gear if you have kiddos ...
author: Brad
comments: This hammock is fantastic! It's great camping gear if you have kiddos who all want to crowd into it and crawl around. Being over 6 feet tall i found it to have plenty of room long long ways and crossways to be comfortable!

title: Five Stars
author: cajunmom
comments: awesome...came in handy hiking the grand canyon!!

title: Awesome lightweight hammock!
author: Stephen A. Means
comments: I've tested this sleeping outdoors here in the PacNW summer. Great hammock, ALMOST perfect.Pros:-Very lightweight, even with straps.-Packs into a stuff sack with built in strap to pack down even further.-Attached stuff sack doubles as sleep storage (for instance my glasses)-Enough material to cover yourself up pretty well at night, if you're in a low bug area you might not even need a net.Cons:-Thin parachute material means you need to be careful of what is underneath it, because a sharp branch, brambles, etc. will tear it.-It's called the DoubleNest, but two people are not realistically going to sleep in it.-Material frays a little along the seams, even brand new! Not so sure about long term durability.-Straps not included, and the ENO ones while nice aren't cheap either.If you go in knowing the cons and are ok with this for your use case I'd say this is an awesome buy, especially considering the price vs the competition.

title: Very comfortable. Now I just need an accessory to hold ...
author: Megan
comments: Had this item in my cart for a while, spotted it in a Dick's sporting goods one day and immediately purchased it. Boyfriend has a Trek light hammock and I honestly cannot tell the difference between the two doubles. I would totally suggest getting double since, more room to party! Very comfortable. Now I just need an accessory to hold my beer while I'm climbing in and out!

title: Five Stars

comments: Great hammock, but beware-- the colors are switched in the newer stock. The picture shows khaki base with emerald lining, but the hammock I received was an emerald base with khaki lining. I returned it for a different color, but other than that, it's a fantastic hammock!

author: summer
comments: I love this hammock!! Love the color. So comfortable and easy to set up. Takes no more than 5 minutes. Upon opening there seemed to be a snag or two. Almost like a run in a stocking. Also there was a slight discoloration. Made me wonder if it was a return or something. They don't seem to be getting any worse with use so decided to just keep the hammock and deal with it. Would definitely recommend this brand!

title: ABSOLUTELY AWESOME. I own this hammock
author: Zach
comments: ABSOLUTELY AWESOME. I own this hammock, along with the Atlas straps from ENO. I'm 6'4 210 pounds, so I knew I needed a doublenest. (I have fit comfortably in this when I was 290lb as well.) There is a lot of room. I can't image two people my size deciding to snuggle up in this thing, but for two smaller people I'm sure it would work. I have used mine miles back in the wilderness and had great sleep under the stars. It is super lightweight and the built-in stuff sack means that you can't lose anything. It's all right there in 1-piece. When stuffed into the stuff sack, it is very small. About the size of a softball. This is a perfect hammock for outdoor enthusiasts, backpackers, hikers, etc. I highly recommend it.

title: Strong and promising!
author: Austin Chief-Owner
comments: Strong material, worth the higher price for brand product. I like the color and I spend a lot of time reading in it as I am a student.

The biners that come with it are nice for their purpose (if you're into that). Nice unit.

The hammock does fold up into a tight ball when it is time to take it down, which makes it convenient for storing it or taking it somewhere else.  If you are looking for a lightweight, easy to assemble / disassemble hammock, I would highly recommend this one.

comments: So this is the first review I am leaving here but I am just absolutely in love with this hammock. It is super portable and durable. The double nester is really spacious and easily fits my girlfriend and I. However, I definitely suggest you get the straps for easy and safe set up without the hassle of tying knots etc. If you are looking for  hammock - seriously get this one!

And still giving you room to roll on your sides. Ill never carry a tent in The woods again if i don't have to

title: Super strong, incredibly compact.
author: Indy
comments: I love this hammock!! I've slept in it several times during the summer and can highly recommend it. It's big enough that the nieces and nephews love playing in it together (fits four little people at once though it doesn't look particularly comfortable--they liked it though). You'll definitely want a blanket underneath you though if the wind is blowing at all.

title: Why a DoubleNest?  100% Recommendation!
author: Madeline Seabaugh
comments: Comfortable, strong, and absolutely what I was looking for! I recommend these to all of my friends!  Also, I was wondering whether or not to get the DoubleNest, but I am so glad I did- it has so much more fabric in its width, and I can easily share it with my brother when we are reading out under the trees on a beautiful day.  Also, because of the extra fabric, when I am hammocking alone, I can wrap myself up in it, and it's quite cozy!  The ENO packs up into its very small package easily, and goes up easily, as well.  I purchased the Atlas Straps, and have been very pleased with them, although I use my ENO mainly for recreation, not really for camping out.  Lastly, it is so breathable, and when a breeze starts, you can feel it through the fabric, which proves nice in the humid summers.

title: Very practical and way worth the $.
author: maxwell
comments: Very comfy and can easily fit 2 people as long as you don't mind being a little cuddly with the other person. If you use it for a single person, there's enough material to pull over you like sheets on a bed. It also folds and fits very easily and nicely into the little sack it's supposed to fit in.the compression band does it's job and makes it even smaller. The sack it all folds into is an awesome pocket when the hammock is outstretched also, great to put your phone in and just lay back and relax.

title: These hammocks speak for themselves! Took this thing with ...
author: Temujin
comments: These hammocks speak for themselves!Took this thing with a pair of Atlas Straps on a week long hiking/camping trip and didn't regret a single cent spent on it.

comments: Wonderful hammock. We have ropes tied to trees in the backyard with bowline knots so we just have to clip this bad boy up and we're in business.

title: Five Stars

title: Five Stars
author: Alex Mann
comments: Love love love. Eno hammocks are the best!

title: I love it
author: Doug
comments: Used it for a 4 day music festival and loved it.  I made a frame that used my receiver hitch and could hang it in the back of my truck.  The fabric is soft and comfortable and keeps you cool.  Dries really fast if it gets wet.  I also bought a cheap rain fly to use with it which kept the dew off.  My two boys played quite rough with it for a week after I got it and I have noticed a couple small runs in the fabric but really had no impact to the structure of the hammock.  I'm glad I got the double because I can flip the excess over like a cacoon to deter bugs.  Very light and easy to pack.  May not ever need my tent again.

title: Five Stars
author: Derek B.
comments: Love this product

title: I thought it would be fine for me to take out the stains myself instead ...
author: ad1515
comments: When I received my new hammock I had multiple oil stains as if it wasn't new. After trying all night to get it out, a couple oil stains are still present. I thought it would be fine for me to take out the stains myself instead of waiting to exchange and receive my shipment which could take weeks. After all the hard work to take out the oil stains and no luck, I should have exchanged it since I paid so much money to have a new hammock.Other than that, I love the hammock. Very light weight and comfortable. Easy to put up and enough room for singles and doubles.

title: Five Stars
author: Robin Devonna Brewley
comments: Awesome, my husband loves it!

title: While i was warm and comfortable. The rest of the group in tents was ...
author: Sean C.
comments: Used it for the first time two days ago. Also bought the atlas straps. Had it set up in 2 minutes flat. Never happens with a tent. Put a thermorest pad underneath and a blanket on top. Outside temp dropped to about 45* at night. While i was warm and comfortable. The rest of the group in tents was freezing and uncomfortable. Best nights sleep Ive ever had outdoors. Also great while not sleeping for a place to lounge and relax Unfortunetly now I have to buy two more for the girlfriend and her kid

title: but it actually worked out really nicely! I could fold the sides over and cocoon ...
author: Brooke McFarlane
comments: I was a little worried that the double person hammock would be too big and/or stretchy, but it actually worked out really nicely! I could fold the sides over and cocoon myself in to keep bugs out.this hammock is also really comfortable; I nearly spent a whole day lounging about in it because I was so comfy! I've yet to have a guest sleeping in it with me, so I can't comment on how that is.

title: Heavy duty, light weight hammock.
author: Just1jess
comments: This is a well made hammock for outdoor use.  It's large enough for two.  Bought for my 12 year old daughter.  This hammock packs up really small, so it's easy to throw in a back pack for hiking and camping or even just to grandma's house.

title: I love this hammock!
author: Nate Greiwe
comments: I love this hammock! I'm 6'3", and I can lay in it comfortably for hours, and I've even slept in it overnight while camping. Excellent product and excellent quality.

title: It was a perfect gift for her
author: Linda
comments: My twelve year old granddaughter loves it!  It was a perfect gift for her.

title: Fun gift to give teens.
author: Barbara Lyle
comments: Colorful, light, and fun.

title: Having a lot of fun with this purchase
author: kyle parKer
comments: Having a lot of fun with this purchase. Comfortably fits two if you don't mind being right up next to each other. Very durable and strong!

title: Expensive but well worth it.
author: Caleb
comments: This is by far the best hammock I have ever been inside. With that said, I am extremely pleased that I bought the doublenester instead of the single. It allows for much more wiggle room, sitting sideways, and those comfortable weird positions, while also giving the option of sharing it with someone else. I'm 5'9" and 160lbs and it feels pretty big (I'm fine with this).I do, also, highly recommend the Atlas straps ($30). It does cost a whopping $100 for the hammock and the straps, but I think that it is worth every penny. It is quick and easy to set up and take down and very comfortable.Lastly, consider a pad under your sleeping bag when sleeping in it overnight because wind can cut through it a little bit. Expensive but EXCELLENT!

title: Loved!!
author: --Brown
comments: Loved!!! Packs into a small lightweight ball a few inches in diameter.  Stuffed in our backpack and took to Yosemite!  Definitely buy the atlas straps to go with it! Those two items are all you need!

title: Worth the money!
author: Giuseppe C
comments: Received this as a gift,  never had a hammock before but i absolutely love it. The side are a bit large with one person inside, but it dosent bother me at all. I use it for camping and occasionally I set it up in the back yard just to relax.

title: Bag will rip and stitches will start to fray!
author: Nsku
comments: This hammock served me great three times, however on a hot summer afternoon I opened my backpack to see that the bag containing the hammock had completely ripped!. The hammock stitches were even starting to fray! Avoid!

title: Solid Hammock
author: Spencer
comments: Bought as a gift, it functions perfectly. Great quality

title: Perfect for camping and hiking
author: keegan
comments: Great product! Perfect for camping and hiking. Very light weight and packs down to the size of a softball.

title: Great Value
author: Kevin W
comments: Coming from someone who is pretty frugal this is a product I would be happy paying more for. Bought the Atlas straps as was recommended by a friend of mine who is a much heavier user of her Eno than I am. The hammock itself is very well built and the canvas is very soft and comfortable, it surprises me how durable it is for how light and easy to pack it is. Have set it up a few times and couldn't be happier to have another great reason to enjoy a nice day! The retro tri-colored hammock is also surprisingly more tasteful in person than I was expecting it to be =]

title: Great hammock, excellent portability.
author: Birdski
comments: Comfortable, versatile, and light weight. This light weight hammock is portable, and packs itself back into its sewn on bag when your done. Easy hassle free installation. It comes with its own carabiners that support up to 400lbs. It is noted on the carabiners that they are not meant to be used for anything other than the hammock. It is also worth noting that the hammock does not come with its own tree straps. If your looking for a great hammock that will last, don't look past this one.

title: Five Stars
author: Melinda
comments: Great product.

title: Great
author: aj
comments: Bought this for my dad for Father's Day. Be loved it!

title: Simple and Effective
author: Big_Guy_with_Girls
comments: Really impressed with how easy these things are to hang and the quality of the materials.  Kids absolutely love them.  I'm probably going to get one for myself.

title: Easy to use, very comfortable and portable. Just a great buy!
author: Gear and Wear
comments: These are the best hammocks on the market. They are small and portable yet very strong, holding up to 400lbs. Also there are lots of colors to pick from giving you lots of style options. (If your interested in a more thorough review check out my outdoors gear review blog http://gearandwear.weebly.com/gear-and-wear/eno-doublenest-hammock)

title: Five Stars

I purchased one two days later and now it is a stable for our weekend activities. I love my ENO! the only thing I don't like (and maybe Im just doing it wrong) is that it keeps trying to cacoon me inside instead of spreading out like a more traditional hammock. STILL, I love my ENO.

If you're not planning on sleeping in the hammock or relaxing with two people in it then the single best will be a better option since the top of the hammock will still be open

title: Pretty amazing. I actually slept in this rather than ...
author: CollegeKid
comments: Pretty amazing. I actually slept in this rather than my bed (which I used for storage) for about two months in my dorm. Strong, spacious, compact when being carried--it's just great. The only things holding it back from five stars are two attributes of the material. It is not the most comfortable against bare skin and it makes a substantial (but not terrible) amount of noise.Those things being said, it is amazing. It hangs anywhere, is comfy, and completely cocoons you. Highly recommended.

title: LOVE IT!
author: anonomus
comments: Love it! Bought the double nest for the exra room. Works perfect for one or two people. I have used it a ton. Exactly as expected. Color is perfect.

title: The ENO DoubleNest Hammock is great, It is small enough that it can be ...
author: Hunter
comments: The ENO DoubleNest Hammock is great, It is small enough that it can be carried almost anywhere while being built very tough. The hammock is very comfortable and easy to set up even for a beginner like myself. This is the perfect way to spend a sunny day out on the lake. I will however warn you that it is not going to be easy to get completely comfortable with two people in the hammock. My girlfriend and I tried to lay in it together at the lake, while sitting in it was great, once we laid down we were constantly hurting each other trying to get into the perfect spot. There is also a lot of floppy material even when both of us were in there. This hammock would be great for a larger guy. If you get this hammock you HAVE to get the Atlas Straps, they making putting the hammock up anywhere you want a breeze. Overall very happy with the product.

title: but with some practice you learn how to make it fit one much more easily. I nest my elbows into the upper edges ...
author: Cassie Henninger
comments: A little big for one person, but with some practice you learn how to make it fit one much more easily. I nest my elbows into the upper edges of the ENO, which creates a sort of arm rest, then I don't feel swallowed up by the sides if I'm alone! Ps get the atlas straps!

title: Five Stars

title: LOVE IT
author: Anome
comments: Bought this for my husband as a gift and we both LOVE it. I found it odd that straps do not come with it. I bought the Atlas straps as advised from reviews and agree, they are worth every penny. Make set up and take down incredibly easy.Very happy with this product. Easy to set up and put away. Very easy to stuff back into the small stuff sack without struggle. Very comfortable, and both my husband and I are not the skinniest folks but we still found this to be comfortable. We haven't done so yet, but we plan on getting a second one and using these to sleep in while camping.My only complaint is that there was some fraying on the edge of the hammock that I noticed on our very first use of it, right out of the bag. It hadn't even been opened before so that was a little concerning. We will see how it holds up... But I still plan on buying a second one. At least they are fairly cheap. Seriously the perfect gift for someone who enjoys the outdoors. And don't forget to get the Atlas Straps too!

title: Great hammock!
author: joliet jake
comments: The ENO doublenest hammock is definitely built for two people, and since I'm a big guy I figured it would be just the right size for me, and I wasn't disappointed. First it's plenty big enough and strong enough to hold a guy like me and second its lightweight and packs small enough to allow more room in my backpack for more food or water. I went ahead and purchased the Guardian bugnet and I'm glad I did, my next purchase will be the tarp. This hammock has alot of extra material since it's built for two people  and I can lay inside of it and wrap the extra over me, I could have gone with the singlenest and been just fine either way the doublenest is rated up to 400 lbs. Which is more than enough for me. I especially like the idea of using it as a chair of sorts to relax in after a long hike. I'm extremely happy with my purchase of the ENO Doublenest hammock.

title: Eagles Nest Double Nest
author: Professor H
comments: The colors these come in a just great. Mine is so bright it makes me smile just looking at it.Eagles Nest Outfitters makes a cool hammock, in so many ways. It's built well and you just have to appreciate it's simplicity and attention to detail from eagles nest outfitters is wonderful. Comes in a little bag made of the same material, breathable parachute woven nylon and triple interlocking stitching that keeps the hammock storage and transport size very compact, and highly portable. Does not come with suspension ties, but some climbers webbing does the trick perfectly, while not adding much to the transport weight or bulk.Hammock has a maximum capacity rating of 400 pounds. Comes with aluminum wiregate carabiners. Double nest, made for two.

title: One person or two, it's great!
author: Jokoo
comments: Great hammock, alone or with a friend!NOTE:  In my case, I did not need straps as the carabiners latched onto the railing of my balcony, but be aware that the hammock does not come with straps.I bought this hammock for the balcony of my apartment. I wasn't sure what to expect, but I have been pleasantly surprised by the quality of the item. It is made of a very light yet strong material that makes it perfect for summer use. On cool days, you'll need a blanket or sleeping bag to insulate the bottom from wind as it can get quite chilly. When laying in the hammock alone, the excess material can be used to "cocoon" yourself in which goes a long way in blocking out direct sunlight or wind. When laying tandem, you won't be squashed against your partner as you might in other hammocks. There's plenty of room for closeness without either person being crushedI highly recommend this hammock.

comments: The Eagles Nest is our families first hammock.  It has exceeded our expectations!  We purchased the additional extensions which really help when you need an extra few feet to hang the hammock up. The double hammock is able to hold my husband, two small children and myself!  A wonderful addition to our camping trips!

comments: The ENO Double Nest is amazing. Goes from a compressed 6" tote to completely set up in under 5 minutes. If you're using this hammock for two people, you better be willing to be "very" intimate with each other because you will be in each others business all night. I got the "Double" because I'm a big dude.Get the "Atlas" straps instead of the others. Spend a couple more dollars. You will be 100% satisfied. This is my first hammock. All my friends are hammock campers, so I decided to try it out. I'm a big guy at 6'H, 280 lbs. The ENO Double Nest Hammock and Atlas Straps are rated to hold 400 lbs. They held me like I was weightless.Note 1: Watch YouTube videos to learn about Hammock Camping. Lots of tricks and ideas.Note 2: All new hammocks will stretch a little during first usage. So set up (at home or a park) and use for a few hours before camp out.

title: Can't go wrong
author: MG Wagon
comments: This is one of the most popular camping hammocks because of its quality and price.  I have always found the "double" hammock idea to be a little bit of a joke.  It is fine for lounging, but there is no way you could sleep comfortably with someone else.  The good part of double hammocks is that they offer more room for sleeping.  It is easier to fit a sleeping pad and sleeping bag in a double that a single, if that is the way you go.  Pretty much all camping hammocks pack down to the same size, and at 20 oz, it is pretty light.  Because this is parachute nylon, they are a little more susceptible to tearing than some of the other camping hammocks made of stronger ripstop material.  The material is why this hammock is less expensive than some camping hammocks out there, but this is on the expensive side of parachute hammocks.  The carabiners that are included are really good quality.So, the short version, if you want a really good quality, relatively low priced hammock, this is a great way to go.  There are better options out there, but unless you are an experiences hammock camper, and know exactly what your gear requirements are, this hammock will do you just fine.

It takes me less than 5 minutes to set it up in combination with the Atlas straps. I have seen other reviews that state how it is annoying that the flaps (sides) fall down in your face when laying down. That is correct, if you are laying in the double-nest in the traditional head-to-foot length-ways as a single (not so large) person the flaps will fall down on you. But I use this hammock to stretch all the way out. I lay in it diagonally, I can even almost completely lay out from side to side in it. If you want to just lay in your hammock in a traditional way, I recommend the single-nest instead.The only reason I have given this 4 stars is because the color in the picture does not match the color I received. The description says "emerald/khaki" but the picture looks almost greyish and turquoise. The actual color that came was a dark khaki with a emerald green trim. So pay more attention to what colors they say it is, then the color the photo shows. Either way I liked those colors just as well so I kept it. I would highly recommend this product!

title: Just buy one, can't go wrong.
author: RavenDesk
comments: Excellent product but maybe a touch overpriced. If you're looking to get into hammocking then this is great but by the time you're splicing your own whoopie slings from Amsteel then it's much cheaper to just make your own parachute. I've had an ENO DoubleNest for a few years and it's got a few stretch marks/tears but still very usable and unpatched. Saying this though it's lived in incredibly hard life: out for months at a time on a South Pacific (taken in during heavy weather), everyday use (daily pack/unpack) for over a year in rural South Sudan, over a year as an in cabin/on deck lounge hammock. Needless to say this is solid.My setup:2x 6-12ft of polyester webbing (300ft roll for like $15 on Ebay)2x Amsteel Whoopie slings ($20 around the web)2x Climbing wire gate carabiners ($3-5 per on Amazon)1x ENO DoubleNestUse sling to replace the rope on the ENO, attach carabiner to adjustable loop in sling, put a single end loop in webbing and wrap around tree, use a carabiner in a marlin spike hitch. Tighten up and it's ready. Setup time should take about 2 minutes.

title: I'm an experienced backpacker, and I love this.
author: Margaret
comments: I absolutely love this product. I've backpacked through Montana, Northern Wisconsin, and Alaska and I've seen many different types of hammocks and this brand is by far the most popular of all my friends, and the most reliable. I bought the purple/Fuchsia color, and the color I received was true to the image and exactly what I expected. If you are unfamiliar with this product I would suggest doing more research about this product because it is a pricy item, but worth every penny. I love being able to hammock with friends, and this is perfect for sleeping, hanging out, and relaxing.The fabric is sturdy, and the stitches are strong. The clip that connects the hammock to what ever your suspension system is feels a little weak, but has not caused any issues and is non the less reliable too. I would recommend buying the Eagles Nest Outfitters Atlas Straps to hang your hammock. Regular ropes work fine, but are a pain to tie and adjust, and the Atlas Straps are quick, hassle free, and sturdy.

title: I'm a huge fan of sleeping off the ground.
author: Amazon Customer
comments: We happen to have two large trees in our front yard so I set up my ENO Hammock, bug net, and ProFly between them. I am so glad I went with the DoubleNest. Roomy, comfortable, my legs can stretch out or bend at my whim and there's always a fold to hold them a nice relaxing place. The bug net cuts down on the breeze but it also eliminates bugs. When they're not active I just slide the bug net all to one end like a shower curtain and just enjoy being comfortable. It rained with sustained winds and I set the ProFly lower against the prevailing north and west side of the hammock which kept me completely dry.The whole set up is backpacker light and easy set up and take down. With the right sleeping bag and insulating mattress, I'm sure I would be very comfortable in sub-zero temps.

title: Good as a hammock, but bulky, messy, and slow, with additions.
author: J.N. Cahill and Tom Blalock
comments: The Eno DoubleNest is nothing revolutionary. There are a growing number of companies that make camping hammocks, and twice as many individuals who make their own. Hennessey Hammocks, Warbonnet, Grand Trunk, and Hammock Bliss, just to name a few. With that being said, it is a very good camping hammock.By itself, the DoubleNest is very spacious and very comfortable. I bought my fiancee and myself one when we first started camping. We chose the DoubleNest because we were both a bit heavier at the time. As a standalone hammock, the DoubleNest has everything you need. It's durable; mine are still going strong after two years. It's easy to set up, with the two "slap straps" to hug the tree's and the simple carabiner attachment to clip on to the straps. You could probably do it well in under a minute.When I first bought it, the slap straps had a great deal of sag to them, often requiring a reset after laying in the hammock for an hour. I bought some upgraded Atlas straps that fixed this problem, though.This issue with the ENO DoubleNest actually comes into play later on down the road. After you've hit a nasty rainstorm, or a swarm of mosquitos. The bugnet and rainfly go together well with the DoubleNest, but... not very quickly. Most of the rainflys are also not entirely big enough to offer true protection from the elements either. I actually upgraded to a Hennessey after a nice rainshower two nights ago kept splattering on me under the tarp. Additionally, you almost need another ridgeline for the tarp, and then another one for the bugnet, although I'd imagine you can probably clip the bugnet onto the tarp as well. The bugnet also hangs a bit loose, and can result in things like stepping out onto it and snapping one of the clips in half.All told, it's a great hammock, but as a hammock system for inclement weather, and inclement bugs, setting it up can be a real hassle. Taking it down, it goes without saying, can be one as well. I'd recommend it to anyone, it's a good system. I simply think there are probably better systems for around the same "total" money out there as well.

author: Mark
comments: Works like a charm and takes up very little space. I am 6'8" and weigh almost 300lbs and this fits me just fine. Have used it all summer in all types of settings, from our backyard to camping and kayak trips in the Sierras. The material and stitching has shown no wear at all yet and this this "breathes" really well which makes it comfortable on very hot days with a slight breeze. Love the hammock and my straps and will be getting another one as soon as my wife says she wants to join me on my trips, I'm not holding my breath on that but I do recommend this hammock.
