Two people can definitely fit, but I don't know how comfortable it would be with two people if they were trying to sleep.

title: it also provides for the most comfortable bed I've ever had
author: Bonmot
comments: I bought this to use as my bed in my small dwelling. Not only does it fit the bill for a compact sleeping solution, it also provides for the most comfortable bed I've ever had. Once installed, I can set it up at night in about 10 seconds. In the morning I unhook one end and roll it up to the other end where it stays out of the way until needed. I set it up so the "foot" is attached to a wall where I have a shelf unit so the rolled hammock, a pillow and blanket store right there on the shelf out of harms way. Hanging a hammock requires a little thought and experimentation. There's an on-line hammock calculator which is great for getting started. It's at:  <<< http://theultimatehang.com/hammock-hang-calculator.html >>>  I started with that and over a couple of nights made some minor adjustments and now life is good. NEVER buy a hammock with spreaders! They are uncomfortable and require the skills of an acrobat. A proper hammock automatically provides the exact right support for every part of your body. It nestles you in and feels snug but not restrictive. On a mattress I tend to be a side sleeper. I can sleep on my side in this hammock but it actually feels more comfortable to be on my back. And speaking of backs, I have had a long history of periodic back strain. Comes and goes but how quickly it clears up depends on the nature of the bed I'm using. I actually had a bit of a strain at the time I started using this hammock. Had been going on for about 6 weeks. The morning after my first night in this hammock and my back ache was gone and has not returned. A properly hung hammock of this design just provides the most natural sleeping platform there is. It also inhibits tossing and turning which reduces the effects of a "restless nights sleep" . It has never taken me more than 15 minutes to fall asleep once I started hammock sleeping. It is just so relaxing! I chose this model based on the weight rating of about 400 pounds. I don't weigh close to that but figured for full-time use 365 days a year I wanted that robustness due to wear and tear. The first couple of times I "mounted" the hammock, I did hear some light tearing sounds. It appears that was some sort of initial adjustment and has not recurred since.

My friend who went camping w me is buying one Friday when she gets paid.  Did a 5k warrior dash and was so comfy in it after run.  Almost didn't want to get out to go to my tent to sleep. Ended up having to buy some small chains and caribeaners due to locations of trees at campsite but that will give me life long added reach depending on tree locations.

title: My Favorite College Years Purchase
author: D37Mark
comments: I can't speak highly enough of this hammock, approaching 4 years of use and has suffered some expected wear - mainly the little pack that houses the entire hammock is no longer attached, but that hasn't caused any problems.Almost every time I use this hammock I receive compliments and questions pertaining to the acquisition of such a luxury.Was amazing for days of school when I had a little more time between classes than I preferred. Myself and a handful of friends actually started a "trend" of lounging in hammocks on campus between classes. Makes for great "hang out" sessions - pun intended. Takes 2 minutes to set up and less time to take down. I've comfortably slept in this hammock both during naps and overnight camping trips. When it gets too cold it easily fits a sleeping bag.I'm a 200lb, bearded man, and at times this champion of a hammock has easily borne the weight of myself and two 100lb females, myself and an excited 90lb boxer dog that at a full sprint leaped into the hammock while I was relaxing in it, and myself and a male of greater weight than I.Although I do not recommend the following - I have left the hammock outside during multiple thunderstorms. It has endured smoking sessions from an UN-welcomed friend of my sibling and I have never needed to clean it beyond wiping it down with a towel after my nephew had a slobber-fit in it.If you're struggling making a decision on whether or not to purchase this hammock, I would highly recommend purchasing it. Upon my first use, all of the lingering doubts of whether this was a wise purchase were slain. Wait for a great day of weather, set this hammock up, then equip yourself with a sandwich and cold cerveza and all of your doubts will, too, be slain.

comments: Absolutely in LOVE with this hammock! It's a portable bench, swing, bed, resting spot, or safe haven whenever you need it! Got this after testing out so many at Electric Forest 2013. I've taken it on so many hikes, chill in it at my house a lot, and it survived Electric Forest 2014. Such an incredibly sturdy and well built hammock.

author: Kathy
comments: My college daughter loves this for campus and camping. Great hammock.

title: I can read in it or nap for hours in complete comfort.  It is sown very well with good fabric.
author: Gomojo99
comments: Excellent hammock for recreation or camping.  I have used this two summers at my cabin and I can say it is sown very well with good fabric, shows little wear and should last a long time.  The fabric is cut so It curves just right under my back and I can read in it or nap for hours in complete comfort and I'm 55 and 6'1".  The fabric breaths great and it never feels hot or sticky.  I would not hesitate to camp with it along with tree straps, bug net and rain fly.  Stuffs easily into its sewn-in pocket and just crushes into a little ball.  Five stars for comfort, quality, value and the memory of happy summer naps.

title: A truly great purchase!
author: shayne
comments: This is a fantastic product and I would recommend it to anyone. I have taken it camping, hiking, used it at a train station (not suggested), at bbq's and anywhere there are kids. It's a great ice breaker and conversation starter. A safe study product I use every day indoors and out. Reply or message me if you have any questions

title: Totally changed my backpacking
author: Anthony Franklin
comments: I am about 6' and 225 pounds. I feel totally secure in these hammocks and love taking mine out on my backpacking trips now. I generally slept ok on the ground under a tarp but got tired of packing a dirty groundsheet, plus site selection is so important when sleeping on the ground. Staying sheltered from wind is interesting and I plan to move to a larger tarp than my 5.5'x9'. I am what I consider to be an 'ultralighter' and the weight of this is not bad. I can still squeak in at close to 10 pounds before food and water even with this bag and suspension.There are lighter hammocks like the Grand Trunk Ultralighter but I will leave that for super gram-weenies while I am comfortable in my Eno.

title: Help I can't get out of this man made Venus fly trap!!!
author: josh gibson howdeshell
comments: So I weigh about 275 ... When I lay in this thing I feel as though I've fallen into a Venus fly trap ... It feels like its gonna eat me.. Could be from my weight though... Or the fact that it needs some sort of spreader .. Oh and I have trouble getting out once I'm in... Lol

title: Couldn't be more pleased with a product

title: Great hammock for hiking and camping
author: Brock Turpin
comments: Great hammock for hiking and camping. My wife and I have spent a few nights sleeping in it together and been more comfortable than had we slept on the ground. I have slept many nights in it by myself and have woken up feeling great. Lightweight and durable, it has easily held over 300 pounds without a problem. It does let a night breeze through the bottom on the warm summer nights so you don't wake up sweating on the bottom. I also own the Singlenest hammock and it is perfect for one person, the extra material of the doublenest can flap in the breeze if the hammock is only occupied by one person.

comments: Lots of Fabric goes a long way on a 5'10'' guy. The Hammock has plenty of fabric and it allows you to get rolled up inside. A feature I rather enjoy. Though it's just as easy to keep the hammock from completely consuming you.If you plan to share this hammock with another person you better be dating them. It's a tight fit. it may be the extra room you need for kids though.The hammock packs into the attached bag very easily and requires no special packing.Carabiners come attached to the hammock but the straps are not included. I strongly recommend ENO Atlas Straps.

comments: Owed 3 years, used 6 times.  Awesome left it in the rain for about 2 weeks and then stored, totally forgot to wash it.  Washed it 6 months later, dried and perfect, no spots nothing.  Very Durable, just make sure you secure it to some tree or those ECO straps nice and you'll be good to go.  Slept on it for 2 nights during a backpack trip in the mountains, very comfy.Oh, the side pouch is very handy.

comments: I honestly adore this product. its lightweight, its compact, its easy to put up, very durable, has awesome colors, and most importantly its comfortable! i also recommend getting the Atlas straps to go with this as it DOES NOT COME WITH STRAPS.

author: Swampy

comments: No matter how I hung this thing, I just could not make it sit like I thought it should. It formed a sort of cocoon anytime we would lay in it, which would be great if it was cold and raining, but made for a hot, miserable lounging space during any other season. It would just wrap you up and completely cover you unless you stuck your arms out and held it open. We also couldn't find any way for two people to use it comfortably.

title: Eno
author: Dean
comments: I love it! It's worth every penny. I go out in the middle of the woods with a group of friends all the time and have a good time eating and relaxin in our eno. Great memories are made with these.

title: Don't know what I did before this.
author: Amazon Customer
comments: Since I got my hammock, I spend twice as much time outside. I didn't know I was missing this whole big part of my life. I camp more, I hike more, I kayak more, I party more. I'm not in my house hardly ever now. So easy to set up, super comfortable. There are never any achy camp mornings anymore. I wake up refreshed and ready to go. The double is worth the money, too, so the sun doesn't burn out your eyes or face in the morning. You can just pull the hammock around you like you're in a pea pod. The attached stuff sack is handy for your glasses, keys, meds, whatever you might need in the night. Although, If you're going to get serious, then I can't recommend the eno rain fly or bug net. Its just too expensive with too many components. They pack down small, sure, but I'd rather have the hammock bliss sky tent 2. Its a one-piece, double decker rain fly/bug net combo. Two hammocks can fit in this thing stacked, and is easy to set up with attached guy and ridge lines. It even has some guy lines that pull the bug net out away from you so its nice and roomy in there, even with two people. All you need to complete the set is some Eno twilights. Kinda pricey, I know, but well worth it, especially the ones that change color. I'll stop now, but seriously, I cannot recommend an Eno hammock enough. Just buy it.

title: Great Hammock.

comments: They love the hammock. Liked it so much we purchased another one. It was purchased to use on a mission trip. The size is perfect when you are limited on space when you travel.

comments: My girlfriend loves camping, but Her main concern was always of a snake getting into her sleeping bag. Now this concern seems to  be solved.

title: Love this hammock
author: WB
comments: I shopped around for a while before settling on this hammock.  I wanted a two person hammock to enjoy in the backyard.  Not only can it hold two, but the colors in the picture don't do the actual colors justice.  It's bright (the red) and the dark isn't really that dark.  It has been used in the sun and doesn't get warm because of the material.  Would definitely buy this again.

title: Dismount Can Be Tricky
author: TonyInAtlanta
comments: Getting out of this can be harder than getting into it.  I'm sure that I'll eventually get the "hang" of it.  =)Otherwise, quality product.  Handy little side pocket for glasses, phone or bottled beverage.  I like how it folds back up into the pocket for tidy storage.

title: Great purchase
author: Krista Wert

comments: This was purchased as a gift for my 18 year old niece who recently graduated from high school.  When she opened the box she noticed that a strap was broken.  I believe she will be returning it for another one.

title: Like this a lot but wish I'd known it needed more!
author: Susan
comments: I like it a lot but wish it had come with the special ropes. Have ordered them and am waiting for them now.

title: Buy this.
author: Eric D
comments: This was definitely a great purchase. The hammock is very well made. I have slept many nights in my Eno hammock including a few camping trips. This is a great product. It all bundles up nicely in the attached stuff sack and sets up in under five minutes. The only issue I've had with it is trying to sleep two people in it overnight. It just gets too crowded. it is great for spending an afternoon close to somone though. Highly recommended.

comments: Daughter wanted this for her bday and she loves it. Very comfy and easy to hang. Buy straps--not included with hammock.

title: not what is in picture
author: tony harding
comments: The picture show's a hammock with a cover but it's just a hammock.  When you click on the different colors some are just hammocks but this one show's it as a hammock/tent but it's crap.  yes I will be returning this over price hammock

title: Unreal comfort
author: Casetay
comments: Absolutely love my doublenest hammock. Fits myself and my wife very comfortably. I take it to work and hang it up in my camera truck and take a nap during lunch on set. Best investment in a long time.

title: Don't mess around, just get it
author: Alex Barnes
comments: Quality hammock. Ridiculously fast and easy to set up. the straps and the hammock together take up barely any space at all so it'll fit easily in your backpack while your out in the woods or whatever. Also it's very comfortable and strong. You seriously don't need to worry about it breaking or being too heavy for it. I'm a 5'11" 270 lb dude, and i've never felt nervous about it breaking/collapsing/tearing. Some guys might tell you to go with other brands or different set-ups, but honestly, if you just want a simple, reliable, easy-mode hammock, this is your best bet. The hammock and the straps together are under $100, so how can you miss?Easily one of the best purchases i've made in awhile. It's exactly what you need for a casual hiker/camper, and nothing you don't.

title: Perfect birthday present for my son!
author: lucymom1
comments: My 17 year old son enjoys his ENO! He can easily take it with him wherever he goes and always has a comfy place to "hang out". The material is good and strong and the colors are nice and not too bold for a guy who likes to get back to nature.

title: Get the Atlas hammock straps
author: Tracy C
comments: Using those straps, I put up the hammock in less than 2 minutes each time. Around trees, on a trailer, from a backyard playground etc. The hammock is so comfortable and the material is light enough to breathe and still block the sun if it is too hot. If it gets wet it dries pretty fast. The whole thing folds into a 6" ball that you can easily carry with you wherever you go in a backpack or even a purse. Super fun to use

title: ENO Double Nest - Awesome!
author: Scott <U+0001F600>
comments: Purchased two of these for my 12 and 14 year old.  Overall great quality product, seems very durable and the kids just love them!  The Double Nest is great for a 6' 3" guy like myself or two kids could fit in it as well.  The straps are the key, get the Atlas Straps,which provide staggered loops all the way down the strap giving you the ability to set the right distance when suspending between trees/posts etc. The others do not have this ability, its worth a little extra dollars!!If you found my review helpful, please feel free to indicate it below. Thanks! :)

title: This hammock rocks!
author: Jason Moffatt
comments: This hammock is incredible. I rigged it up right along the river and have had no worries about falling, which is good because if I did I'd land in the river.The hammock easily packs up into it's small pouch and is easily transported and extremely lightweight.Great deal. Highly recommended!

title: Best sleep ever
author: Michael S.
comments: Spent four weeks at the National Training Center in California.  Spent almost every night in this thing.  Most comfortable sleep I've ever gotten when sleeping outdoors.  I do recommend a sleep mat/pad on cooler nights because even the slightest breeze will end up cooling you down, even in a sleeping bag.  The plus side of this is that it's a great way to stay cool during the day when its warm out.Edit Update 9 June 16:I still have this hammock and it is still going strong.  Probably one of the best outdoor investments I've made.  It's my go-to item when sleeping outdoors.

title: Best Hammock Ever
author: Ray
comments: I had always wanted a hammock, but being a big guy, I was worried about being in a hammock that was not well built.  Not only did this one fit the bill, but it is light, small and very compact.  I cannot believe that the whole hammock fits in that very small bag.  Comes with 2 snap links to hook you hammock to tree straps or whoopie slings.  I got the khaki/olive one to be psudo-camo, and it is very subdued.  Every time I lay in it, I feel very secure.  The fabric feels thin, like parachute material, but still held me up fine.

title: Great for couples and larger men
author: Deen Kody
comments: I purchased the DoubleNest for myself after seeing a video review of a guy comparing the Double and Single for one person. The DoubleNest seemed to be more comfortable with all the extra room, however in retrospect the man reviewing was a fairly large guy. He said he was 6'3 and 220 pounds, so if you are around this same size I imagine the DoubleNest would be more of a suitable fit. However, I am 5'11 and 165 pounds and personally I found the DoubleNest a little less comfortable than a SingleNest was. If I laid in certain ways I could get comfortable, but even then it had to be perfect and plus since it's designed to fit two people when you lay vertically in it the ends of the hammock are very high up and I couldn't see over them unless they were pulled down.However, for two people it's great. It fully supports the weight of two people with no problems at all. It may be a little nerve racking at first but you can trust it. I would only see this product for either a married or dating couple, as the two people in the hammock will be VERY close together. I'd definitely recommend that just friends should get separate hammocks rather than splitting the money for a DoubleNest.

title: Nice hammock
author: Jason
comments: You know this is one of those times I would like to give something 2-3 stars because of the seller but unlike some I realize this is a product review and not a seller review. This is a great hammock and my son loves it. We own two others so we did not expect any less that 100% satisfaction from this one. The seller of this hammock on the other hand deservers 1 star, the hammock came with some kind of black grease all over the built-in case. My son inspected the rest of the hammock and it was ok. He tried to wash the grease off and did not have good results in the end he decided to keep it ... said he would have it dirtied up after a few campouts anyway. The seller should have seen this and not shipped this product it belonged in the scratch and dent area with 10% off on it.

title: perfect
author: tia kirby
comments: purchased on request from granddaughter and she's thrilled. sets up easily, is comfortable, and lightweight to transport.  works as promised.

title: Love the Eno hammock
author: jedean
comments: This is the third hammock our family has owned and we love this hammock.  It is light enough to carry in a pack but strong enough to hold one or two people.  The only problem is my kids keep stealing them when I buy them.

title: Must have!!!
author: Charles Mathes
comments: This hammock was very well made and holds up great. It fits two people very comfortably and had extra room on both sides. Very great deal for the money.

title: awesome hammock
author: bradford cole
comments: Great hammock! Put many hours in this hammock. Top quality product.  Buy one u won't be disappointed. Great price to boot!

title: Experience the outdoors differently
author: N. Wassmer
comments: You cannot possibly go wrong with ENO hammocks. They are high quality, light weight and extremely durable. For being compressed to the size of a small cantaloupe, the hammock is deceptively large when completely sprawled out (9 feet, 10inch long) leaving plenty of room for you or another. I would like the see the hammock come with hanging straps included (only comes with two plastic carabiners to hang) but they sell nice straps separately, of course. I would recommend purchasing two climbing grade metal carabiners to replace their plastic ones- just to be safe.Overall, fantastic product and I will continue buy these.

title: Love it!
author: Curtis R. Huff
comments: I do a lot of camping and go to many music festivals, and this hammock is so much better than sleeping on the ground in a sleeping bag!  It is big enough to fit both my girlfriend and myself, and is extremely comfortable.  Also great for just lounging out in the yard to enjoy a beer on a nice afternoon, and was perfect for viewing the recent meteor shower.  Best purchase I've made in quite a while!

title: Perfect for Hanging Out (Literally!)
author: Amazon Customer
comments: This hammock is lightweight, extremely easy to set up and comfortable for lounging or napping.  It is light years ahead of the rope hammock that I used to have:  it's way more comfortable, lighter and cheaper than that big rope one, so I was very please to get it as a replacement.  Plus, this hammock is very easy to pack up after each use--it takes me less than two minutes to set it up or put it away, so it stays much cleaner than my rope hammock did.Although this is a double hammock, the two people sharing would have to be either very small people or very OK with the idea of cuddling with each other because, unlike a bed, there's no way for one person to be one one side of the hammock while the second person gets the other side.  The instructions say that the hammock has a weight limit of 400 pounds, and the fabric is so lightweight that I would hesitate to get very close to that limit. I enjoy using this hammock alone and using the excess "double sized" fabric like a sheet or blanket.  I fold it over myself and get comfy, and the extra fabric keeps me cozy and also servers as a barrier against insects.  Because of this, I would recommend the double sized hammock even to singletons who don't intend to use the hammock with another person.  The only reason that I could see to get the single sized hammock would be to save size and weight if you were being really careful about what you are packing for a backpacking trip or something like that.  I use the hammock for lounging in the backyard while I nap or read, so I haven't given much consideration to its use as a piece of backpacking or camping gear.I would highly recommend this hammock.

title: Love it!
author: Holly McDaniel
comments: Color is awesome, and it is super durable. If you are thinking about purchasing one, get a double. Totally worth the extra money because you need more room. I'm taking this with me to sleep in on a week long hike through the Appalachian Trail! Fabric is very breathable, too.

title: Perfect
author: Charlotte
comments: My daughter love to "hammock" and this product has proven to be perfect for just going to the local park or taking on a camping trip.

title: Get what you pay for
author: Richard Ho
comments: quality made hammock. works as expected.I got 50 ft of paracord and tied knots in it to use as straps.

title: Fantastic hammock
author: Kyle
comments: Almost too good to be true! This hammock is pretty much indestructible against regular wear and tear. Very happy with my purchase.

title: Great deal
author: Brad T.
comments: Very sturdy and well made. The only thing I didn't like was that it seems to completely enclose around you.

title: So in love
author: Ashlyn
comments: Shipped fast. Thanks for including the straps!! I LOVE MY ENO! I take it almost everywhere with me because it is so easy to find places to hammock

title: Relax in comfort!!
author: Kathy K. Mccoy
comments: Great hammock!!!!  Just as described!!  Relaxing and very comfortable, easy to hang and use. Looks nice too, we really like it!!

title: Buy this!!!!!
author: biken
comments: It is amazing! I recommend buying it! 100% I recommend this highly I use it on my break to sleep in at work!

title: Comfortable hammocks
author: Kim D
comments: We ordered two of these for camping and for just having a relaxing day around the house.  They are very comfortable and should come with a warnring that says, "once in them --- you might fall asleep."  I can't wait to get more use out of them!!!

title: Couldn't be happier
author: Sam Slovisky
comments: Great product. It changed the way I look at trees...<U+0001F332><U+0001F332><U+0001F332> Super durable, and I was pleasantly surprised by how comfortable it was.

title: Perfect for hang time
author: Sydney
comments: Great colors! Can pack and game anywhere. Fun to hang with friends or relax and enjoy nature on your own. Definitely worth it!

title: Shipped Wrong Color Pattern
author: Christina Raj
comments: Love the ENO Hammock. I have 2 that I use for myself and wife. I ordered this one for my Brother Inlaw as a thank you for helping us move into our new place. But was disappointed to hear that he did not get the color combination that i had ordered. This is the first time that i have had this issue with Amazon but i read about it a lot via other posters comments. I would highly recommend this product, but check the color before you get rid of tags....

title: Love it!
author: kg4
comments: This is the best hammock out there in my opinion. I know people talk about them being too pricy, but coming from someone who was in a cheap hammock over concrete when it broke, my tailbone and I don't mind spending the extra money. It has been to countless festivals and camping trips and has never done me wrong. I put my sleeping bag in it and sleep in it all night and am comfortable. And, we even had 4 of us in it at one time watching a concert. Would recommend to anyone needing a hammock (and really amazon is the place to buy them.. I did a lot of research and this is the best deal).

title: Eagle nest.....the best
author: John Kohmann
comments: I have use the eagle nest at a few scouting events, love it and have received many comments about it. Wake up much more refreshed than sleeping on the ground !

title: perfect
author: fiftycats
comments: excellent hammock.  my son loves it and uses it all the time.  my other son has one too, and loves it.

title: Total Perfection
author: cathryn mitchel
comments: It the best !!!!! We bought two for our annual trip to St. John's USVI. They are the perfect size for an afternoon between two palm trees!

title: Pretty Fly for an Eno Guy
author: Matt McCutchen
comments: This is a great time for anyone who enjoys the peacefulness of the outdoors.I very much enjoy my quiet time as I don't get enough of it and the eno is a great outlet for that.My eno came well equipped, easy to set up, and I use it about once every few weeks.Highly recommend it for anyone who has money burning a hole in their pocket and want something chill to do (Especially great for dates!)

title: Highly Recommend the Double Nest
author: Guy McElwee
comments: Used my ENO double nest for the first time on a 3 day camping trip in WV the second week in April.  I may never use a tent again.  The hammock was very comfortable and with a tarp stretched over it I remained dry on the night it rained.  The hammock is a lot easier and quicker to put up and take down than a tent.  If you are considering buying a hammock spend the extra few bucks and get the double nest, you will be glad you did!

title: I'd buy another one if I didn't needto sleep in only one
author: Abie Antillon
comments: Light compact and comfy. Not to mention plenty of room for a guy who's 6'1". Caribiners are sturdy. There are no straps. But thats not a problem

title: Nice Hammock. Good Quality.
author: dcstand72
comments: Nice Hammock for lounging around. if you are planning to sleeping in it at night maybe add a ridgeline to get a nice repeatable lay. Awesome product.

title: I wish I could use this as my bed...
author: Malcolm Fisher
comments: I first decided to get one of these hammocks when I went to visit my girlfriend at her college campus in Georgia. They had these posted up in little spots in fourss on days with nice weather. This hammock is incredibly comfortable, miraculously strong, and super compact and easy to transport. This hammock holds two not so heavy people and with the Atlas strap system that I purchased with it I can put it pretty much anywhere. If there's within less than 25 feet between tow trees, my hammock is going up. It is a little expensive but it is by far worth the price. It is also going to be a part of my emergency camping bag. LOVE THIS HAMMOCK!!!

title: Sleep sound
author: Jeff Davis
comments: LOVE IT  LOVE IT LOVE IT!!! When I sleep in this Iwake up feeling good. No back pain and the swelling in my feet goes down.

title: Best hammock ever !
author: Sammy
comments: I had a general, store bought hammock before this, but ENO is a great brand and I'm so happy with my hammock. It's durable, compact, light and just great for camping or hanging out! (pun intended)

title: LOVE ENO
author: LESLIE ARCHER
comments: Phenomenal product and brand! I would suggest also purchasing the ENO Atlas Suspension System. Combined and you'll have all you need!

title: Double Size ENO Nylon Hammock For Two
author: GB
comments: ENO quality and workmanship are well known. They know how to make a quality hammock. Design and materials are first rate.This double sized hammock really does fit two adults comfortably, and you can throw a small child or dog or two in as well.It packs up and compresses into its own sewn-on attached pocket for travel.The material feels like parachute silk, strong yet soft to the touch. It feels...luxurious.These are amazingly comfortable. Easy to fall asleep in. If bugs aren't a concern you could sleep all night in this.It's also extremely durable. It's extremely resistant to mildew and it won't rot. Water and humidity have no effect on it.I've had several ENOs for years and they're still like new. Stitching, sewing, materials, all that is first rate. No complaints whatsoever. Reasonably priced, and money well spent.Note: ENO does not usually include rope, so you'll need your own. Polyester does not stretch & is a better choice than nylon rope. There's a range of good 'tree straps' that are easy, fast and good for the tree's trunk, such as the ENO Atlas Straps.I love this hammock. Search for 'hammock forums' for a website with tons of user info on hammocks and hammock camping.Hope this helps. Happy trails.

title: Great,  but doesn't come with straps
author: Christopher M Kobil
comments: Its perfect hammock but it would be nice if it came with straps. I had to use rope to tie it to a tree.

title: Three great nights sleep in the Ozarks
author: Fwayne
comments: There is a reason for so many 5-star reviews.  This hammock deserves it.  I'm 6'2" and 200# and this was more than roomy for me.  one reason to consider the DoubleNest is that for some, sleeping in a diagonal position provides a flatter laying position.  This hammock allows for a lot of wriggle room.  I had zero issues with it.  The included caribiners are more than adequate and it packs away easily.  I'm impressed.  I had a bit of wind at 32 degrees one of the nights.  The nice advantage of having extra material was that it helped block the breeze from under my tarp. I was completely comfortable with only a sleeping pad under my 40 degree rated sleeping bag.  I did not need the pad on another night that dipped to about 47 degrees.  I paired mine with ENO Atlas Straps  and I am equally impressed

title: Five Stars
author: James Paul Sain
comments: Lots of room

title: So Much Love
author: katie gallagher
comments: Hammock came; had to wait a few days for my straps to arrive, which was painstaking. Once I got it up- which was solo and in only a minute, I enjoyed hanging out in it. This hammock was probably my best purchase of 2013. Hands down- I've taken it camping, to school, anywhere. It is fantastic.

title: Great product
author: Amy Soto
comments: We have enjoyed using our Eno. It came quickly and with no issues. The double nest is the only way to go.

title: Very satisfied
author: Elaine M. Campbell
comments: My son picked out this hammock after trying a friends, he has been very happy with it.Easy use and very compact.My son is 5'8"

title: Awesome hammock
author: asolomon1300
comments: I bought it for my wife as a gift and she loves it. She likes to put it up as often as she can.

title: Forest green
author: Jen05
comments: It look purple and black in the picture which are my favorite colors but I should have read that it was forest green haven't tried this out yet sense it's still to cold but when I do I'm sure it'll meet my needs.

title: Great Product!
author: Garrett Roberts
comments: Go with the doublenest! I constantly look for new places to hang my new hammock, such a fun thing to have on an adventure!

title: I recommend this to all.
author: Edgar
comments: Perfect - Just what I ordered and it arrived as per the date noted in the order. Well constructed and looks to be very easy to pack and unpack..

title: Nice and roomy.
author: Greg Lindsey
comments: Very roomy and comfortable.  Durable as well. Took it to Mexico where it was very windy and it held up nicely.

title: LOVE IT.
author: sailorcolin
comments: IT has been amazing to take on every trip that I have been on. Use it all the time and couldn't live with out it.

title: You can never go wrong with an ENO Hammock!! So comfy!
author: Hannah Steffens
comments: This is my second hammock from ENO and they are great. Easy to travel with, put up in a tree, great for festivals.

title: Much better than single nest
author: Wilson Gaberino
comments: I haven't tried it with 2 people but its much more roomy that the single nest and has a better feel to it. Highly recommended

title: Great hammock!
author: MICHAEL ETHEREDGE
comments: Great hammock! Very comfortable and plenty of room for two. Super easy to set up using the ENO Atlas Straps.

title: Awesome!
author: Webtoole
comments: Great quality and can't wait to use it outdoors.  It is setup in my office and is so comfortable, it is hard to get work done ;-)

title: Daily Sleeper
author: Christopher
comments: High quality product.  Blows away perceptions of what a bed is.Everyone deserves a hammock in their lives.I love the parachute material.  I also never expected to fall asleep so fast (and so deep!!) on a hammock.

title: Solid Hammock
author: Solomon Parker
comments: This is my first hammock of this style.  I hung it between two trees this afternoon in my back yard and had a nice little nap.  Solidly constructed, reasonably priced.  I plan to get some use out of it this summer.  I liked the Forest/Charcoal color combo because it's not flashy like some of the other options, and may blend in a bit more out in the trees.

title: Freakin love it
author: Nano
comments: I like the whole idea of this hammock: the easy drying, the level of comfort, the portability and the piece of cake setting it up. The only con, if any, is that this hammock is so big you need quite a bit of space between the trees to hang it; this is really for 2 comfortable people. .If you go for it, the straps are sold separately, and they are a must, I went for the Eagles Nest Outfitters Atlas Hammock Strap, and they couldn't be better. Would buy it lifetime after lifetime.

title: Nicely made hammock.
author: GA Mom
comments: This product is well made, roomy and very easy to hang and then disassemble.  Bought it for my teenage daughter.  She and her friends now go "Enoing" at the park or in our yard.  She has spent more time outside this week than in a long time!  Highly recommend.

title: Great Product
author: Vicki Johnson
comments: I bought this item as a Christmas gift for my son-in-law and he loved it.  We did buy the extra straps because this item does not come with straps to hook the hammock to trees.

title: Must-Have Camping Hammock
author: Jamie Moore
comments: Packs small and lightweightSuper simple and speedy set up with Hammock Straps (sold separately)VersatileComfortable shared with 2 adultsKids love, safeCoveted by everyone at campground

title: Just as advertised
author: Martin Johnson
comments: My son has special needs and this is a great relaxation tool. Easy to set up, good design, feels sturdy and durable. I suggest getting the ENO indoor hanging kit as well, you may be able to get some of the parts at Lowes or whatever, but the special brackets appear to work better than something not designed for the hammock. Worth the piece of mind.

title: light compact awesome hammick
author: PJ SLAY
comments: I use this hammock alot during the summer alot in the yard and camping fell aslepp in it plenty of times in the yard but if you take this camping or hiking as a shelter i would recommend a bed roll or sleeping mat of some kind because iyour back will be hurting in the morning if you dont

title: Back pain.. GONE! Insomnia.. GONE!
author: KaleBokchoySpinachHerbsLettuceGreensCilantroBasilMintCeleryBroccoliGreenonions
comments: UPDATE: I have slept in the hammock every night for the past three weeks. The change in my life is nothing short of amazing. I used to dread "bedtime" but I look forward to hammocktime. I fall asleep so quickly nowadays!This review is after only 1 night of use. I may update this later.I installed my hammock in my bedroom (hammock room now) using ENO's Indoor Hanging Kit (ENO Indoor Hanging Kit).Upon lying down into the hammock to test it out, I immediately felt an immense level of comfort. I started gently swaying back and forth and ba-BAM! I was tired.I had the best sleep I ever had last night. I woke up without a dull lower back pain that had been bugging me, too.I am going to tell my family, friends, and co-workers, I am a hammock convert!

title: So comfortable!
author: Leigh Ann
comments: Ordered this for my son-in-law for Christmas. He put it up in our backyard. My husband tried it out and he loved it! So we had to order one for him too. Also ordered the ENO Atlas straps. Very easy to put up and down and really comfortable!

title: Great Product
author: Bt
comments: AAAAAA+++++++  Great product love it meets more than my expectations. The best hammock hands down . Off the scale workmanship.

title: Great!
author: Sailor
comments: Exactly what I was wanting! Great hammock, I have used it frequently since purchase and it is holding up great.

title: Large yet packs small
author: Dan
comments: I was suprised how small it packs. About the size of a softball but unfolded its huge and works great. Super simple to set up

title: Best thing I have ever purchased
author: Sami Reuter
comments: I absolutely love my ENO. Unfortunately, it's falling apart due to many years of wear and tear but I would definitely purchase another one in a heart beat.  LOVE ENO!!!

title: I love it
author: Steven Lehn
comments: I got this with the atas straps (and now just bought the bug net as well).  It's easy to set up and take down.  Getting it into the stuff sack is pretty easy, and it's small and lightweight for carrying.  I've camped in it a couple times as well, which worked quite well.  It can be a bit of a challenge to get into a sleeping bag inside the hammock, but once you do it's so comfortable.

title: I am LOVING this lightweight, compact hammock!
author: Charlotte Key
comments: I take it in its small and compact bag along with the slap straps I also got at Amazon, in the panniers on my recumbent trike, and whip it out and hang it between two trees with great ease. I also use it when going camping. I got a double because of my weight (220 lbs) as I wanted plenty of room. When it was pretty cold out, I used it this summer in the UP of Michigan on Lake Superior at a park, where the wind howls sometimes, and hung near the edge of a cliff, and pulled the sides up and enveloped myself to keep the wind off me while I relaxed a bit. I could easily sleep in it but most of the time I just rest my back which is a total mess. I have a small backpack I bought to put this ENO hammock and the slap straps in to keep them together, for other camping uses when not taking it on my trike. It works and is so nice to have for such a reasonable price.

title: Not the right color. But it's ok
author: Adam Abernathy
comments: They didn't ship the right color but the color they sent would have been my second choice so it's all good.

title: Awesome!
author: Michael Albert Ciaffone
comments: This is great and I use it all the time! I live in Florida so it gets hot. This hammock breaths so well that I sometimes even get cold at night! Would not recommend for camping up north unless you have a good sleeping bag to wrap up in.

title: ENO Time
author: Amazon Customer
comments: I have not had the hammock for very long but wanted to write my thoughts so far.1. Hammock appears to be good quality material, stitching, etc.2. Everybody and their brother has been buying these things - hard to find in local outdoor stores.3. I have used outside and inside and find both fairly easy to do.4. Inside mounting may be a issue depending on quality of construction and 2x4 locations - may need hammock stand5. I had trouble sleeping very well at first in the hammock due to subconscience fear that I was going to fall due to eyescrew failure.6. Overall I would say totally worth the money and my kids love it too - I have to fight for time.7. If you are looking at a complete system for hiking  with mosquito netting and tarp there are cheaper options than eno.

title: great gift
author: Cynthia Gray
comments: I gave this hammock to each of my two sons and one of their girlfriends this year and they all were delighted. I've seen 20-somethings hanging from trees in a park near my house and it looked like they were relaxing and having fun. Somehow these hammocks just attach easily and can be put in a backpack. Very cool gift.

title: Love this!
author: Amber Peterson
comments: I didn't know I would have to buy straps separately so that was disappointing but once I bought some I've used this everywhere. I backpack a lot and have slept in this many times. Holds myself my boyfriend and our two girls although it is a little crowded. One or two people is perfect. Holds up great and packs up so small it's super convenient. Very happy with this.

title: If you hike and camp near trees get this!
author: Nate S.
comments: I have previously owned cheaper hammocks and did not see the need to spend over 50 bucks on a hammock. That was until I tried one of these out. Very comfortable and sturdy. I own two and use as often as possible.

title: Rockstar comfort
author: Mark F. Holthaus
comments: I ride bikes to some jacked up places.  Lighter is better, so this works well for me.  I suggest to any serious outdoor person.

title: Great gift for college student
author: Kyle G.
comments: College students have taken up hammocking and it is a great way to get outdoors and study.  This was a gift but I have been told it is great for 2 people and very easy to put up with the additional hammock straps (not included).  Very roomy and sturdy.

title: Perfect replacement for a single eno
author: lisa otten
comments: This was a gift for someone (my daughter) who was lamenting the loss of her single eno. She thinks someone stole it from college....but was kinda glad now that she has this one. Much bigger and better.

title: Very comfortable.

comments: This is a comfortable hammock for two.  It doesn't come with straps so be sure to get those when you order.

title: ENO hammock big hit for everyone

comments: Ordered three of these for my grandchildren for Christmas.  They cover a multitude of ages because they were all thrilled - one in college one a junior in highschool and the third one 7 years old.

title: Wonderful
author: Tammye Patrick
comments: The hammock is easy to use.  It is really comfortable.  The colors are vibrant.  I will be purchasing another for a gift.

title: A place for a quick rest
author: Grace1964
comments: Excellent product. Easy to set up. Practical and an nice addition to any camp site or hiking expedition. Wise purchase.

title: Perfect

title: great buy fast shipping

title: Great Product
author: PatC
comments: Just got around to testing out the hammock recently. Great product, but would advise against buying the Eno pro straps, due to the polyester basing. Other than that, perfect.

title: Great find
author: M. Grant
comments: We bought one double for each of our children and they and we love them. We like to go on day hikes and build a fire and now we can hang these and have a lot of fun with them. It also directed our family towards the outdoors instead of getting computer games. These made the perfects larger gift to center the rest around.

title: Good gift
author: Brooks Grow
comments: It works great, it has a small profile, and it's ideal for hiking.  It was a good gift for my dad

title: Great product....
author: WSDM
comments: Use mine every year at thanksgiving at the In-laws... I'm 6.3 and wiegh 260... So COMFY!!!! Fits me and my giant sleeping bag.

title: ENO's Rock

comments: I bought this for a gift.  The color is beautiful.  The main color is a turquoise and is beautiful, especially for a female.

title: My Son loves it

comments: I didn't know you had to buy the straps separately.  So,  after Christmas, I had to find a store that sold them.  It would have been nice to have that Clearly indicated

title: loved!
author: Amazon Customer
comments: Bought this for my husband for Christmas he loved it so I tried it and it was surprisingly comfortable! I requested one for my birthday next month!

title: Great Hammock
author: K's Books and More
comments: I bought this for my son for Christmas.  He could not wait to try it out.  He loves it!  Now he's stocking up on the accessories for it.  Best purchase I made this year!

title: Just what I was looking for!
author: DR365
comments: The reason for my buying this hammock was mainly comfort level. I have had a single nest for years, and it has been great, but their is just not quite enough room to really spread out or sit in it like a seat and have anything to lean my head against.The double nest adds the right amount hammock to allow me to do those things and brings a new level of comfort to my hammocking experience. I would highly recommend it as an upgrade for any single nest owners reading.

title: #4 and counting
author: Amazon Customer
comments: My children all love their hammocks.  Look forward to hanging out in trees together, and all that other stuff. Amen.

title: DOES NOT COME WITH straps
author: Branch henderson
comments: BECAUSE IT DIDNT COME With straps like what's the point of buying a hammock without anything to hang it up with disappointed should have said it didn't come with straps ENO hammocks ARE SUPPOSED TO COME WITH STRAPS unhappy <U+0001F611>

title: Just what I ordered
author: Sara
comments: Quickly shipped and was exactly as described. Bought as a present b/c I have one and love the ease of being able to hang anywhere. Just remember to order the straps for it b/c they are separate .

title: Best quality hammock around!
author: Ibuyfromreviews
comments: We have three of this type of hammock! This is the kids favorite because they can wrapped themselves around in it. This is the best for a good price in my opinion. If the price is a little high Walmart sells a blue one that is cheaper and a great value. We have 2 Walmart and one of these.  If money wasn't an object I would for sure have 3 of these!! Dries extremely quick for an easy pack up too!

title: great product A
author: Adam
comments: Great product would buy 2 if we go on any trips.  Love it in my back yard. I haven't tried the straps yet just the stand.

title: great
author: Eric M. Brasher
comments: I used this camping in the fall and it worked out great. Set up a tarp over the top and I was ready to go. Much easier than setting up a tent when camping in milder weather. It was even in the 30's when we went. I placed a sleeping bag pad in the bottom of the hammock and it worked out great.

title: Perfect for relaxing
author: Parker Davis
comments: I use it when I go camping.It is functional easy to set up and super comfortable.If you have the means to purchase this, Do it.

title: Perfect
author: Don B.
comments: Perhaps this would be nice for the beach, damping or nestled up in your friendly neighborhood campground, either way it's perfect for two!

title: It doesn't get much better than Eno!
author: Biology Teacher
comments: I love my Eno hammocks. I make my own hammocks, and use Henessey Hammocks, but I still love my Eno! It is a great hammock that will last for years if you care for it. Leave it in the sun, wearing sharp objects while in the hammock, or setting it up over the fire are all quick ways to end the life of your hammock. I use whoopie slings (google it) with mine and homemade tree straps, but the Eno Atlas straps are also nice and made out of polyester instead of nylon. Nylon stretches so not great for hammock suspension. If you are getting into hammocking or just want a great hammock you can use for lounging, or backpacking, Eno will fit the bill!

title: great
author: Clint G.
comments: Great Hammock how ever if it's cold out at all put something between your sleepingbagand the hammock or you'll freeze.

title: Excellent,
author: Kitkat
comments: Bought this as a gift for Christmas. My son was elated ! The kids were all talking about how awesome these hammocks are for hunting...he can't wait to try it out.

title: Perfect
author: J. Morgan
comments: Love this! Holds two people plus a dog. Super strong! Great bargain. Used with the slap strap you can easily and quickly put this up anywhere you have trees 20' or less apart. Heck - just a good branch on a tree is enough.

title: LOVE LOVE LOVE!
author: Todd Pickering
comments: If you enjoy the outdoors at all then you need this! I love this thing. I also bought the slap straps so that I could set it up quickly wherever I go. This hammock is so comfortable and easy to use. It fits two people easily. Great for reading, napping or just enjoying the outdoors. I worried about trying to fit it back into the attached bag but it rolls right back up and tucks in nicely. You will regret not buying one sooner. My mother liked mine so much that I bought her one a week later.

title: Holding up and Fantastic!
author: Jhandro
comments: I have used the hammock on a handfull of occasions with B008OXZNDOstraps and it is a fantastic set up.I love the price for what you get...super lightweight and small for a great camping hammock and with the straps you can set it up in a variety of places. The material dries pretty quick if it does get wet.I wouldnt recommend putting more than 1 person in there at a time, even sitting. Im 5'9" 170lbs and Im golden with room to spare. Ive had friend over 6' and over 215 lbs be in there comfortably with no noticeable stress so it passes those types of tests.I reccommend!

title: Satisfied customer
author: Danielle
comments: My husband had an eno so we bought this one for camping together. The colors were true to the picture and the product arrived promptly.

title: A gift
author: RXM
comments: This item was requested by a family member for Christmas.  Vendor was best value source for procurement.  Can you tell my day job is to buy stuff for the government?

title: This thing is loved
author: Mel
comments: I love it, the kids love it, my dog would probably love it. This thing is the bee's knees. Buy the extra tree straps. Just buy it.

title: Great hammock
author: Pen Name
comments: This is a great hammock, I am especially glad that I purchased the doublenest.  There is a lot of room in it.  I just wish it came with some longer attachment straps.

title: tl.dr: Just buy the hammock already!
author: teresa
comments: I can't believe I lived this long without owning an ENO Double Nest Hammock. Or a hammock of any kind. If you are looking to lay in the shade and drink some wine and possibly down a psychedelic or two with to pass the time before String Cheese Incident takes the stage, this thing is downright amazing!!! Once those mushrooms take affect, you will feel as you are one with the hammock, and then the air, and then all of nature itself, because we are all one, and you're apart of something great. If you're the kind of person that likes to make a scene at a 4th of July picnic, than this hammock rocks for that too. I mean, nervous dads can't figure out that you can just ATTACH IT TO A TREE WITHOUT A KNOT! So they might take your expensive straps you bought separately and tie them into knots anyway. It's best just to let it go. You know, remember that mushroom trip and become one with the universe again. This hammock may not change your life, but it will be there making your life awesome as it changes.

title: Well made, light and compact
author: MICHAEL BARLET
comments: Awesome hammock...  I am a big guy at 350 lbs and it holds me with ease... also holds my two daughters very comfortably when I'm not using it.  Packs up very small and compact.  I will buy another one if this ever wears out.  Seams very durable and with good stitching; likely won't need to replace for a long time coming.

title: Great buy!
author: panda2582
comments: I love it! I use it for camping or relaxing. I love the extra fabric so I can cover my face while I am sleeping.

title: BUY this hammock!
author: MeG McG
comments: Truly the best hammock on the market. You can't go wrong with an Eagle's Nest hammock. Wonderful purchase. It's amazeballs!

title: Awesome investment.
author: Cheri
comments: This is great.  I can take it anywhere and put it on anything! It is very portable- make sure you get the slap straps.  REI has the slap straps on sale for $20 sometimes- it makes the experience so much easier.  I took mine to the top of a sand dune and chilled for an hour- true peace and no sand in my bikini.  It held me and my boyfriend (and the next time I went to the dunes with my mom, my mom liked it too).  It completes any relaxing experience.  Its an investment, but you will have it forever as it is quite the quality product!

title: Always in the Jeep
author: sheadberg
comments: Fantastic quality.  Very durable. Safely holds 2 grown adults.  Compact.  Stays in my Jeep at all times for whenever I have an opportunity to hang a hammock.

title: Best way to camp if you are near trees
author: M. Rudo
comments: Best way to camp period.As long as you're in a wooded area to be able to utilize a hammock, this is the way to go.Camped over rocky terrain that would have made regular tent/sleeping bag impossible.Being a side/stomach sleeper it took a bit to adjust but once you go diagonal it straightens out and works like a charm.As good as your queen size mattress at home?  No, but you're camping!Get a closed cell foam pad for under your sleeping bag inside the hammock and you're good to go for low temps as well.The plastic carabiners that come with it are fine, but for a few $ I replaced mine with some black diamond neutrino wire gate carabiners on super sale @ local EMS.  Feels more secure for no reason at all.

title: Great Hammock
author: Marcy
comments: Great hammock.  My son loves this for Boy Scout camping.  The material is quality stuff and should hold up to the riggers of teenage-boy activities.

title: Very handy and well made
author: Marshdale
comments: My daughter absolutely loves the hammock.  She's had it for about a year now, and used ofter when reading a book at the park.

title: Perfect
author: K
comments: I have a few hammocks this one is by far my favorite!I'm 6'2" 235/240 lbs and this fits me perfect with enough room for someone to cuddle up next to me( obviously weight is a factor in that situation)Just a random trip. When packing it up leave one of the clips out so you can clip it your bag instead of packing in your bag

title: Great camping gear
author: Tim Rundle
comments: We have been looking for a good Hammock to take camping and this is going to fill the bill great.

title: Good buy!
author: JG
comments: Upon opening the box, we were surprised at how small this hammock packs down, though it's admittedly the first hammock of this kind that we've seen. It's incredibly comfortable and made with fairly durable material. It says it's made for two and it does fit two people but hanging out for more longer than a cat nap probably wouldn't work out as it's most comfortable when you lay at a diagonal to make it more flat (that way your feet don't fall asleep).

title: Lightweight and strong
author: Kris H
comments: This thing packs down tiny. It weighs next to nothing and hods my 250lbs well. My only complaint is that you'll need to carry something to put between you and the hammock if it's even slightly windy outside. When I camped with it the first time my bottom half froze due to wind chill. I now use a cheap foam pad or an extra sleeping bag under me and it works great. Easy to set up. I like that I can use the extra fabric to cover myself and keep most of the bugs at bay.

title: Buy it, don't delay
author: Flave
comments: I already owned on prior to my purchase, these are great. My dad does upholstery, and he says this is well built. I trust his opinion most.

title: Great hammock
author: Todd and Robyn
comments: Light weight and packs easily, love it on the those long days elk hunting and being able to take a nap up off the ground.

title: Great Hammock
author: Julia Cartland
comments: Love their hammocks.  Small and light weight and great quality.  Highly recommend as a gift for your camping / backpacking fan.

title: good buy for hammock enthusiasts
author: chino
comments: This was used all summer more than once 390 pounds were on this and it help up great and well into the fall

title: Great hammock!
author: Wjohnson
comments: This a great hammock, it is durable and it is long enough to fit in it comfortably. I have had other hammocks made by other companies that were too short and the material didn't seem very strong, but this is exactly the opposite. As far a straps for it go I have just used tubular climbing webbing, about 2, 10 foot sections that I use as anchors for my slack line and they do the trick perfectly as they are adjustable to almost any length. Still have yet to use it back packing as it is big enough to fit a good sized sleeping bag and pads.

title: Tough Hammock, Gentle Relaxation
author: Jonathan Hsieh
comments: It feels really thin like it'll rip, but so far has held me up. I'm 235 pounds and I feel pretty safe in it. It's great to lie or sit in and enjoy outdoor weather. It's tough to beat swaying in a hammock outside in nice weather for relaxation.I've taken this thing out to the park to do work on my laptop when I wanted to get out of the office. It was great.

title: Great for college
author: Paula Riddle
comments: Bought the doublenest for my daughter at college.  Nice and roomy and loves it!  Very easy to set up and take down.

title: Hammocks are awesome people.
author: A. Saunders
comments: I actually use this thing as my "bed" at night. Given it's breathable material, it should be great for summers, but It is easy to get chilly in the colder months.

title: Great Purchase
author: bartolucci
comments: I love my eno! I'm bummed that it's about to start getting cold out and I wont be able to lounge around for a while. Shipping was quick and the pictures are very true to color. I got the kahki/teal and just love it. The only downside is that these do not come with straps! I ended up getting the atlas straps which I believe was a great choice because there are more options for lengths.Overall this is a great quality product and if you are questioning whether or not to purchase it, you should! You will not regret it. So incredibly easy to use and stores wonderfully into the bag they provide you with.

title: Better than my bed
author: Casey DeLorme
comments: This is the first of three hammocks I purchased and have tested for over a month.  I slept in it for a week before trying my bed again, and my bed left me with a stiff neck and poor sleep.I highly recommend a hammock as a bed replacement, even with a 2" tempurpedic style pad this thing beats it in comfort, and more importantly I wake up feeling fresh.I can say that having tried three, I do not recommend this one for people larger than 6 feet tall.  I feel like my feet will escape the edges when I sleep in it sometimes, and so a TrekLight or Paradiso Double Wide have been my newer goto hammocks.That said, this is by no means a bad hammock, just not meant for really large people.

title: Arboreal Bliss
author: Alex M Steenman
comments: I've not long been an outdoor enthusiast, but took on rock climbing, bouldering, backpacking, and camping with great enthusiasm in the last year and a half. Along the way, I've had plenty of experience with relaxing in the various brand hammocks of my compatriots along my travels, and Eagles Nest Outfitters' hammocks were always some of the best naps, and by their owners' input they were very durable items. So, too, has been my experience since mid-September after purchasing one for my own.In short: easy to set up (definitely get the Slapstrap Pro for greater variability in where to set up), easy to use, and comfortable. Worthy of your dollars, even more so when you can snag them on sale!

title: seems nice
author: Garrett Ryan
comments: I try not to write reviews before I use the item but in this case it was a gift so I can't really do that. I did pull the item out of the packaging and it seems really nice. I know my Dad was excited about using it and based on the other reviews I don't expect him to be disappointed. Prompt delivery.

title: can't go wrong with an eno
author: K.Natural
comments: this is an awesome hammock. you cannot go wrong with an eno. very roomy for one person and unless you're with someone really close enough to cuddle, then it's that kind of hammock. i love it and the material is strong and soft at the same time. makes a camping experience a whole lot better!

title: Best purchase of the summer
author: Frank O.
comments: Our old Hatteras Hammock rotted through last year, and I just replaced it with an ENO. I've already spent more time the last two months in the ENO than I did the entire life of the Hatteras. Because it's so compact and you can attach it with a couple of lengths of paracord, I've even thrown it in my weekend-trip backpack (i.e. 12-15Ls)/carry-on and set it up where ever I ended up. I'm not sure if its the paracord or the hammock, or just my fat butt, but after a few minutes it definitely sags a few more inches - but after you figure that out, it can be set up anywhere. My favorite place thus far is between the two pilings that hold the dock in place - I can't imagine a place that can beat that.

title: love this hammock
author: Ryan Kenney
comments: Probably the best camping hammock I've ever bought.  Very comfortable and very easy to set up. And with the combination of the bug net,  you can sleep completely worry free and relaxed.

title: Works great!
author: Brad
comments: Hammock camping takes some getting used to. The first night you love it for the new experience.... the 2nd or 3rd night you start to envy your tent friends. Don't give up though... My tent busted so I had to commit to this for a few more outtings, and now Its all I use. Take the time and adjust the tension for your comfort level. Practice getting in and out incase you need to use the facilitrees in the middle of the night you want to be able to get right back in.  Climbing into it while also trying to get into a sleeping bag seems impossible but it is easily mastered after a few attempts.The only criticism I have is that the doublenest hammock is very uncomfortable and awkward with 2 people. I would not recommend it. With one point of support at each end of this thing you will obviously gravitate towards the center and will be all up in eachothers business. Even alone you end up making a lot of adjustments in the middle of the night to stay comfortable, but in a double you wake your partner up every time you move.  My girlfriend would give this thing 1 star, but I know I'll use it plenty without her, so 5 stars from me!

title: always a great product
author: Dave M.
comments: This is the 3rd ENO I have bought, this one was for my son, we all love them. great products

title: Eno is perfect
author: Madison P.
comments: I think it goes without saying that this is absolutely perfect. My hammock came with the large part blue and the border brownish but that made it even better in my opinion. This is an amazing deal and it came so fast it was crazy. I knew it didn't come with straps because I already had bought some, so beware of that if you're reading the reviews and not the product information. Overall a wonderful buy.

title: Excellent Hammock, Poor Order Fulfillment
author: Heinrich
comments: ENO makes a fantastic Hammock.So much so that it is especially unfortunate that I have not had the good fortune of receiving the one I ordered.In fact, the Hammock I received is neither of the correct make nor color.

title: Very good
author: Mickey
comments: I use this hammock for camping along with the ENO underquilt and I love it.  I will never go back to ground camping.

title: awesome!
author: jordan
comments: Best hammock ever.  Easy setup and light weight  awesome for camping or daily use  fell asleep pretty quickly in it.

title: gift
author: Sandra Stutes
comments: ordered as a gift and have been told it is wonderful! Good construction. Top of line. Recipient very pleased. Recomend ut.

title: Say it with me: Ahhhhhhh!
author: J. Danforth
comments: Crawling into this hammock immediately releases 10% of stress from your body.  Napping in it is a surefire way to remove the remaining 90%.Setup is a snap and the integrated carry case in the form of the pocket is handy.I am 6 feet 2 inches tall and 275lbs.  The DoubleNest holds me just fine so if you're also a big ham fatty like me then you're covered.  The DoubleNest also has enough material to wrap around you completely.  I use this as a handy way to keep bugs off of me while I nap in the woods.You can attach the hammock to trees, poles, etc. with rope or the ENO straps.  I bought the Atlas straps and just solved the problem effortlessly.  Yeah, they're heavier than rope but whatever... they're cheap.  The Atlas straps also fit inside the DoubleNest carry pouch if you cram them in properly.  The whole thing winds up being about the size of a grapefruit.  It doesn't hurt very much when this ball of hammock hits you after someone throws it.A few potential flaws:1. You will have to discuss this product with everyone that sees it:  "Who makes that?!  How much was it?! Where do I get one?!"  Honestly... it's like these people haven't heard of the Internet.2. The fabric is very thin which is good for weight but it also brings a surprise.  The fabric is so thin and the circulation so good around your behammocked supine body that you will lose heat quickly.  That's great for the summer but bad for cooler weather including summer nights at higher elevations.  You can try to squish a sleeping pad in there with your sleeping bag but it's finicky.  What will probably happen is that the sleeping pad winds up on top of you mysteriously in the night and your butt is freezing.  If you intend to overnight in a hammock then ENO makes a different product which might work better for you called the Reactor but it's not available in as many groovy colors.3. If you're like me then you'll take it everywhere because you think "Yeah!  Relaxin' time!" but then you'll get out to the beach like a moron and realize that there's nothing to attach it to.

title: nice product
author: pghchico
comments: i've only used it once so far,  but have used a hammock for years.  this is a very nice hammock , nice and comfortable.  Do yourself a favor and buy the  double nest rather than the  single,  for the space and extra weight capacity.

title: Very good
author: Liam O'Neil
comments: We love this hammock. Fun forour 3  kids to lay in. Very supportive for us adults too. Highly recommend it.

title: Wonderful
author: Melissa M. Beal
comments: Relaxing, wonderful........and lots of fun for kids.  Our kids have pushed this hammock to the limit.  On a breezy fall day - being able to wrap yourself up and block the breeze is great.

title: Best hammock
author: Monarchos
comments: Got this a Christmas present for 2012.  We usually use it on our porch.  It's great.  The double is much nicer than the single nest.  If you want a hammock, get this one!  Comes with carabiners on either end.

title: Awesome hammock!
author: Kim Chambers
comments: After years of wanting a hammock, I finally purchased one! I chose an ENO DoubleNest and have LOVED it. It packs down into a small (grapefruit-sized) bag, which is attached to the hammock. Very lightweight - I've been carrying my hammock with me whenever I go out walking/hiking/biking just in case I find two perfect trees to set it up. After one use, my husband wanted one of his own (which we ordered that same day). The fabric is breathable, so it's nice to pull the ends over your head when sleeping. I highly recommend this hammock!

title: Great quality & size.
author: Bruce Tilley
comments: My son wanted this to hang out with his friends. Looks better than the other brands some have. He likes the extra size.

title: Perfect
author: Honest Abe
comments: This eno is just top of the notch. I have owned it for a year now and have camped in it multiple times where it has proved to be super comfortable! There are no "pressure points" on it at all. Definitely enough room for two people. I am 6'3" and have no issues with the size.

title: Solid Purchase
author: Potlatcher
comments: Incredibly happy with purchase. Hammock has been a great addition to our deck. The durability has withstood four kids in and out of the hammock all summer and the stitching is still solid.

title: Bought it for my wife
author: W. Stanford
comments: I really enjoy ENO hammocks. I have a single, and I just bought my wife a doublenest for her birthday. They're incredibly light and easy to set up. They are also really durable. Just remember to buy some straps and consider getting a warm blanket or pad  for cool nights (the loft makes the hammock considerably cooler than the ground.)

title: one for me one for my son..we both love them
author: Geoffrey Haim
comments: easy to hand easy to store. you will never go back to any other kind of hammock. If you have a choice always choose ENO

title: Hot and Bleh
author: B. Miller
comments: Looks nice. Well made. But, it seems to get too hot for some Texas weather. I'm disappointed with it and wouldn't recommend it for hot weather. I'll keep it because it would be too big of a hassle to return. Not sure I'll use it anytime soon.

title: great hammock
author: K.A.
comments: I bought the double nest because I am six eight and weight about 250lbs it is a perfict size for me and has held up well over the past 4 months of use. its not quite big enought for a second person, because i take up so much room. but it would work great for two normal size people to lay in. love the product and will purchase aging

title: Small to pack and comfortable
author: Reichgerdt
comments: Bought this after trying out a friend's on a camping trip.  The double is a tight fit for two, but nicely surrounds one if wanting to bring sides up to keep out wind or sun while napping.

title: ENOs are cool
author: Jake
comments: This hammock is great for relaxing, taking a nap, reading a book, browsing the web, sitting in thought, laying down, reclining, and eating from a branch of grapes.It is also very large, large enough for me and my girlfriend to lounge comfortably and at times romantically. Always appropriately, though. We are trying to make good choices and be respectful of each other. We have been dating for almost two years now, but we still hold firm to morals and values that are quite unpopular in today's mainstream society. She is a fun and spunky gal and I enjoy her company.this is a good hammock.

title: I love ENO
author: Chris Winkler
comments: Eagles Nest Outfitters Double Nest Hammock is exactly what everyone in America needs. Scratch that... in the whole world, no doubt.

title: Love!
author: Lacey Hannah
comments: The colors are bright...a little brighter than the picture shows.  I was looking for a Kelly Green, but the color is actually a lighter brighter green.  But no matter, my husband still really likes it and it looks good anyways!

title: Great purchase!
author: Stani Day
comments: This hammock is everything we wanted!  It's very sturdy and light-weight for our outdoor adventures.  We will definitely recommend this product.

title: Excellent hammock, exceeds expectations
author: Don Arledge
comments: Excellent hammock. I'm very pleased. Used it on a overnight sailing trip. It worked great. I would recommend a pad if its cool out as this hammock has really good airflow

title: Simply AMAZING!
author: RNPfrog
comments: LOVE LOVE LOVE LOVE LOVE this product!! You can set it up ANYWHERE! The only problem I have is SOOO minor! I just wish they had left enough space in the "bag" to put the straps in too.. That way you didn't have to carry two bags around with you.... But that's it! These are AMAZING! We now have one for each member of the family... Even the three year old loves hers! My teen has somewhere to go and hide from the world for awhile.. Even when it's in our own back yard.. We would suggest the double for teens and above. The singles still work GREAT.. But we all enjoy having that extra space (from the double)to wrap up in and get away from the sun or cold air depending on the weather!

title: ok for 2, but better alone
author: Val
comments: make sure to grab your own straps when heading out to camp or lounge or read or whatever reason you got your hammock. my boyfriend and I share it, but it is much more comfy alone. We are well under the 400 lb weight limit, but it still seems a bit cramped with both of us, unless we are ready to snuggle (which we usually are). The color is great and seems to hold up well. Of course if you catch it on something, yes it will snag, but really is a great purchase.

title: LOVE!
author: Gigi
comments: I grew up with hammocks in every room of the house and developed serious envy when I saw a friend with a similar hammock.  I'm glad I spent a few more bucks and purchased the Eagles Nest - DoubleNest.  I'm a petite female so I considered the single person version and I am glad I opted for the extra space.  I can wrap the extra material around me when there is a chill in the air.

title: Regular Sleeper
author: J-John.
comments: I made the switch to sleep in a hammock about three years ago, and after a long-long-long search for the best hammocks on the market I have settled with the ENO-Doublenest as my nightly hammock. I have found that this is the most comfortable, wide hammock to sleep on; great for if you move a lot during the night or want to "cuddle up". It also works great for "that" as well.Try it out if you haven't, and remember to sleep on the diagonal!

title: ENO
author: Lisa T. Mukon
comments: Kids use this every weekend to sleep out and hang out in it every afternoon after school.  Best investment made.

title: kickass hammock
author: Christopher Masiarczyk
comments: this hammock is awesome, plenty of space for two. Folds up nice in attached bag. Doesn't take up much space when you pack it.

title: Really nice hammock
author: James Loomis
comments: Very well made. Triple stitching on all the seams and double ply fabric. Cozy with two smaller people. I'm not sure how two larger folks would like it. I do know it holds 300+lbs. without a problem.

title: Good buy
author: Brandon
comments: Ordered this hammock for backpacking since it is lightweight and packs down very small. I slept in this 4 nights in a row and was not disappointed. It was very comfortable once you get the position right. It does not come with the tree straps but you can easily make some out of 550 cord or nylon webbing. Its worth the extra money to go for this double size, with it you can lay asymmetrically which allows you to lay almost in a flat plane. I did test it with two people, although not very comfortable because you are squished together, it did support our weight without stretching or tearing. All in all a great product

title: new favorite place to nest!
author: PurpleSquirrel
comments: Just bought this a couple of weeks ago as my annual addition to our camping gear. We enjoyed our hammock SO much! At various times it was a "hang out" for 3 teenage girls, a snuggly place for momma and her 6 yo snuggly boy, R&R for various mommas, and even a little shut-eye time for the 13 yo boy! Definitely strong and sturdy! Very impressed!Bonus~ it is super portable (Due to the small size) , and extremely easy to use with the ENO Slap Straps Pro Hammock straps that I also purchased through Amazon. We were able to set up quick at a park that was a detour on our way home~ hubby got to hang out with the boys by the bay while the girls hit the sidewalk sales~ win/win! :)Planning to keep the hammock and the straps in the car (In their convenient bags) so that we can "nest" whenever/wherever the mood strikes us!

title: I like it!
author: Jeff
comments: My hammock survived a weekend in Chatanooga, TN. So far, so good. I would recommend this product to anyone looking for a quality, lightweight hammock.

title: Best Hammock hands down
author: B. Spader
comments: This is worth every penny!I highly suggest buying to everyone I know.  It is so compact and easy to setup.All you need is 2 short ropes that I usually pack into the same softball size bag that is attached to the hammock.I used it one my 2 week long road trip with my family and set it up every day with ease.  We had my wife, my son, and me in the hammock with no problems at all!I plan to use it backpacking also!

title: Excellent Hammock
author: Kindle Customer
comments: These are excellent products and we were very happy with it.  I would recommend this product and Eagles Nest to anyone.

title: I purchased this for Fathers Day & my hubby loved it
author: Aloon222
