comments: I purchased this for Fathers Day & my hubby loved it. It's made very well. We love how portable it it. He used it at the beach, camping in the mountains & on our back porch! I highly recommend. I've even bought one for my Dad.

title: love ENO
author: Zak Czajkowski
comments: Works great. Easy to use. Lightweight and great for hiking or any outdoor activity.  Also holds more than enough weight for a few people!

title: Love It
author: Cassandra Spivey
comments: I found out about these through my cousin on Colorado after visiting her. Her daugher and friends were jumping, swinging, and playing on it for hours so I asked her about the Eagles Nest Hammock. She told me she had had hers for years so I decided to order one. I take it to rodeo hang it between trailors and nap. Its amazing and I know a lot of my rodeo family have started ordering them as well. They are made very durable and strong and they are so light and compact as well as so easy to set up... Amazing

title: One of the best investments of the year
author: ABarks
comments: For years I've been wanting to purchase one of these. Now, I want to go hiking and camping just so I can find a place to set this up. This hammock is extremely travel friendly - light, packs up nicely and is easy to stow away. Setting up takes 2 minutes, breaking down takes even less. For anyone interested in a product that encourages outdoor adventures, this is it. Give it a try! (For straps, I recommend the Atlas straps made by ENO)

title: Good hammock.
author: Tyler
comments: Nice and comfortable hammock, made for easy storage. Try to keep some pace dry, it takes a while for it to dry off after a rain.

title: Great
author: EricRaymondElmore
comments: This product is high quality. It is going to last a very long time. Folds into very small size for easy travel.

title: Great lightweight and portable hammock.
author: Rick
comments: This is exactly what I was looking for in a hammock. Lightweight, easy to hang, durable, portable (grapefruit size packed), and easy to repack. It is a bit expensive and doesn't come with the straps, which I have had problems with holding on to non-circular objects but overall it is well worth the price.

title: Gift for boyfriend
author: Taylor
comments: My boyfriend is an outdoorsy guy and I got him this hammock for backpacking. It's so lightweight, but when you set it up, it's large and fits two people SO comfortably. It does not, however, come with a set-up system, so if you're gifting it, make sure they have the other parts to set it up or you purchase it separately! ENO is a great brand!

title: Better than I expected
author: Tyrell J. Wall
comments: I was a little nervous about sleeping overnight in a hammock but I've done it 4 times in this hammock now and I've been very pleased with the results.  This is a comfortable hammock and seems to be well built.  I use the ENO Atlas straps with this and it works pretty slick.  I am a fairly big guy, 6'1" 210 lbs., and I have enough room in this to sleep at a slight angle (so the surface is more flat) without any problems.  I knew going into this that sleeping two people in this 'double' hammock wouldn't be a comfortable option but I honestly don't think it would even be a possibility in this thing.  It is spacious enough for me but based on my use I'm pretty sure I wouldn't fit comfortably in the single nest.  Glad I went with the double nest for my single use.

title: birthday gift for teen and everyone loves it
author: Kindle Customer
comments: sturdy, durable, colorful hammock that is able to be hung most any where.  Love how it folds into such a small pack.

title: Nothing to complain about :)
author: Meredith
comments: I love this product, The color and design, the functionality, and the size it's all great!!! I would defiantly recommend this to anyone! I <3 my eno!

title: :D
author: Chris
comments: I absolutely love this hammock. I originally purchased the 2012 doublenest but i returned it as soon as I saw this one. The colors are beautiful and I feel like it is more comfortable than the 2012, maybe it's just me though. I would, and already have recommended the 2013 doublenest to friends.

title: I LOVE this hammock
author: A. Butera
comments: So compact, lightweight and comfy! Set it up in 2 minutes on my last trip to Big Sur and we all enjoyed it all weekend long. Next time I may sleep in it. I didn't need the raintarp, although I purchased one. Straps are needed. Great product.

title: eno hammock
author: julius
comments: well worth it...great investment...i use it more then i thought i would....light weight and easily carried around...you can set it up almost anywhere and kick back and relax....

title: Awesome Hammock
author: Seahawk123
comments: Eno double nest hammock is very lightweight easy to clean and comfortable. I have it set up on my balcony and when I go camping or anywhere else I just i clip it and roll it up and bring it along. Great item!

title: GREAT SLEEPING QUARTERS FOR ONE PERSON
author: Steven foster
comments: The double says its for 2 people but I don't think I could be comfortable in this with my wife. But alone is the most awesome way to sleep. Use a good bag and bring a pad also and you will sleep like a baby.

title: Arguably one of the best things I've ever bought!
author: Mark
comments: Like sitting around doing nothing outdoors? Then look no further. This thing is perfect; super lightweight, small, surprisingly durable, and spacious. Both my girlfriend and I can sit in this thing for hours in pure comfort, although I would NOT recommend sleeping 2 people deep all night, it's perfect for naps. This product truly showed me how awesome hammocks are, people are always amazed at how comfortable and fun it is. Just buy it already dude!

title: amazing
author: jay
comments: great hammock love the rasta colors very bright and vibrant! I know everyone suggests the tree straps but save your money and get rachet straps gives you alot of flexibility on height.

title: great product great company
author: Jade
comments: Exactly what I wanted, needed, and expected. This company never lets you down.And it comes with a two year warrenty.

title: Awesome
author: Jay
comments: This is the perfect hammock. If you use this in conjunction with the Atlas hanging system by ENO, you will literally have the most versatile and convenient hammock setup available. The hammock has a carabiner on each end that attaches to the straps (sold seperately) for an easy setup every time, and when you're done hanging, the hammock rolls up into the bag that's actually sewn into the hammock itself. It doesn't get much quicker/easier than that. I also highly recommend the Atlas straps over the SlapStraps as they won't wear out over time and they give you way more hanging options. 2 thumbs up

title: Perfect for a big person
author: N. E. Sima
comments: I'm 6'2" and I was worried that a single nest might be a bit small for me. This doublenest is great. The only thing that even mildly upsets me is that the walls are high. This is completely not a problem when I'm just relaxing and enjoying the outdoors, but becomes a problem when the hammock person next to me wants to have a chat. Really I just dislike people conversating with me whilst I'm relaxing.throw in a pair of atlas straps (I've not tested) or Kammok Python straps (I have and use) and you're ready for a nice relaxing afternoon/weekend/week.

title: Great Hammock!!
author: Sophie Sanchez
comments: The ENO is so portable and easy to set up, it's wonderful. The DoubleNest is pretty large, so two people can fit, but not necessarily as comfortably as one since the hammock kind of "tacos" around the two of you, mushing you to the middle of the hammock rather than allowing you to use its full surface area. I'm very happy with it though. The fabric that it's made of is very durable and I sat in it wet the other day and the hammock dried pretty fast! Long story short, it's a worthwhile investment! :)

title: Fantastic product
author: Richard B
comments: Stats:Myself = 6ft 5inch and 235lbsLovely lady = 5ft 10inch and shhhh 135lbs ;) "don't tell her I told you"Total weight in hammock was 380lbs... 20 less than maximum.  After the new hammock finished creaking under load, it settled down to a very quiet sturdy resting spot. I was absolutely content to stay there all night with the nice sea breeze.Using kammock python straps (polyester and not nylon like the slap straps, I've heard the nylon stretches during long overnight hangs.Note on the color, should be labeled scarlet and gold not tomato/khaki. If you do not like flashy this one not for you. Was a bit more shiny and bright than I expected but otherwise very nice smooth comfortable fabric.We took it on our bike ride where we live in singer island Florida to the inlet and set it up in less than 2 mins the first time I ever used it.  Watched the sun go down for 1.5 hrs and enjoyed every second of it. I am only upset that I did not have this hammock 10 tears ago. I will never travel without it again, it even got my rather no outdoorsy lady considering sleeping and camping in it :D we had it set up for no more than five minutes when a lady came and asked us where she could get one....  We were very comfortable resting in it but for sleeping I think two separate hammocks would be best. At least for my size.Cheers eno you knocked it out if the park!

title: Fantastic Product
author: Alex
comments: The item is exactly what I wanted. I wanted a light, durable, portable hammock that I could hang from the rails on my balcony, and also hang from trees in the park near my apartment. This hammock fits the bill perfectly. It is easy to hang, extremely comfortable, and feels perfectly sturdy when I and my girlfriend lay in it together. Highly recommended to anyone looking for a portable hammock.

title: Great Hammock
author: kms254
comments: This is my first Hammock. I've tent camped a lot and I think I am sold on this. My one experience so far was in a very stormy night(we got about 2" of rain in one night). I set up a rain fly using a tarp and some para-cord and I was quite comfortable. I rigged it up high enough to not worry about splashing rain and I made sure my rain fly was set up correctly. I was a bit worried about lighting. If I knew it was going to rain that bad I would have probably picked some smaller trees. I would say I was a lot more comfortable than my friends who were in a tent which seemed lit it was going to float away. I can't wait to use this on a "normal" trip and see how it does.

title: Bought it for my son
author: Tania C Lewis
comments: My son loves it!  Very comfortable and easy to take any where you want.  He spent a whole day at the lake napping on it.

title: great buy
author: michael schneider
comments: i have used the hammock about ten times since i bought it and it is awesome! Easy to set up light weight and comfortable

title: love it
author: Tim O'Brien
comments: i had been wanting a durable hammock for a while and this fits all the needs that i use it for highly recommended

title: Hammock
author: jjkng
comments: I love this hammock !it is great , I camp with it All of the timeits comfortable and its sturdyI need the eno slap straps to put it upI wouldn't mind buying another one of these.

title: Priced less than the others, but still the great product
author: Stefan Walz
comments: I just really Wanted an ENO DoubleNest and i didn't care what color it came in.  This one was cheaper by $5-8 at the time i bought it in july 2013.Side note to people interested in this hammock.  You need to buy straps separately.  Also make sure that this is the one you want.  The doublenest has a lot of extra fabric on the sides  which can be kind of annoying in situations, if you really plan on using it with someone else or need the few extra inches in length, than i recommend this one.  You may want to see if the singlenest is a better choice for you.Good luck choosing.

title: YOU HAVE TO GET THIS!!!!!!!
author: Cannondale rider
comments: Without a doubt my most used outdoor purchase this season. Perfect for backpacking, day tripping whatever. I can throw this in my pack and bike 15-30 miles to the lake and set it up for the perfect nights rest. This hammock is so versatile and packs great. No bug net??? Lol no problem! The double wide is so big you can wrap yourself up like a pea in a pod! The next thing I'm getting is the rain fly, to eliminate having to take along my North Face tadpole tent on mountain bike camping trips . The double nest is worth every penny!!!!

title: Nice lite hammock
author: Paul Blas
comments: Had to wait a week for delivery but finally got the hammock. Nice, stuffs into a small sack and is lite to carry. Fabric seems strong as my 11 yr old has been spending a lot of time jumping in and out of it. I did end up purchasing the additional fastening straps which are easy to set up and use.

title: Swingin in the Breeze
author: Funkmeister
comments: This thing is awesome.  I always wanted a hammock. Built well, comfortable and Light. Get yourself some slap straps and you can throw this thing up anywhere, in no time flat.

title: Best purchase in a while.
author: A Chronicle of Martians
comments: What can I say?As a one person deployment, it feels more like a cocoon than a hammock, but that's just the way I like it.  This thing has helped me relax more than antidepressants and tahiti any day.

title: Rated for 2 people, might be tight for that - Very comfortable for one person, Light, Ultra Simple Setup, nice fabric
author: Townsaver87
comments: I finally got a chance to use this with some slaptraps.  I must say, very functional and comfortable.  I little spendy but the brand is good.  I don't think two people would be very comfortable unless they wanted to be very close, but I slept in this with a giant sleeping back and was super comfortable all night.  Easy to deploy and easy to pack up.  Fits in a sack sewn into itself, packs into the size of a large grapefruit after use.  Happy with purchase, stitching looks like it will last for years.  I am 200 lbs and had no worries.

title: so comfy
author: julb
comments: This is our second eno hammock. Loved the first one so much I didn't want to share with the family.

title: A little squishy for two
author: Ben Swivel
comments: It was a little squishy for my wife and I, but I've slept in it a few times just myself and I love it! It's big enough that if it starts raining a bit I can just pull it around me like a cocoon. LOVE it!

title: Lightweight and easy to use!
author: Amazon Customer
comments: I received this as a gift, and it is awesome! I live in a very small cabin so space is an issue. This hammock wraps up into a tiny bag making it smaller then a football. Its very easy to set-up and can comfortably fit 2 people with some space to go around. I recommend if you live in an area the is frequently inhabited by mosquitoes that you should also buy the matching bug net to go with it!

title: ENO!
author: Alexander Fortune
comments: I love this Hammock and so does everyone  else that tries it out. Lots of position possibilities, very portable. Just a really cool hammock!

title: Functional and Comfortable
author: badam24
comments: This hammock is exactly what it claims to be, a lightweight backpacking hammock that comfortable fits two. My only complain is that I wish the cords were a bit longer but that is easily fixed with the addition of some 1" webbing

title: amazing hammock that redefined camping for me
author: Louis Ricciardi
comments: I can set up my hammock just about anywhere as long as there's places to hang it from.  Now keep in mind you should buy the atlas strap that is sold separately from this hammock but together they make a awesome product.  You don't need to lug around a hefty tent anymore. You have the hammock.  You can make a shelter over the hammock with a simple tarp and rope.  the possibilities are endless.

title: Great Hammock
author: TK
comments: Great hammock.  I use this regularly for just hanging around and also for backpacking.  I bought several more for the rest of my family.

title: Love it
author: J Ross
comments: My first hammock for backpacking. Does exactly what I need it to do. Easy to set up and comfortable if you don't mind sleeping on your back.

title: Soo Comfy!
author: Hopster20
comments: My friend had bought one of these at gander mountain and brought it camping with us. It was soo comfy that I had to buy one and it was much cheaper online with a  better color selection. I love it and we bring it all over with us!

title: Great hammock
author: azdojo
comments: It took a few hours to find the right position to sleep in. Once I did I found it to be the the most comfortable camping experience I have ever had. Also, there is enough material to cocoon your body. No more tents for me!!! It rained the whole trip and I stayed nice and dry with a couple regular tarps hung over me. Also, I didn't need a sleeping pad with my warm sleeping bag in mid June. I love that it was so light weight for my backpack. Only thing, NOT good for two people to sleep in. That said I stillI love this hammock.

title: Perfect
author: Adam
comments: Great material and stretches after getting it. Ive been sleeping in it every day for the last month and it definitely meets my needs. Just a heads up it gets cold on the bottom because of how thin the matterial it is.

title: Bought it for one of my boys and he loves it!
author: Todd Patrick
comments: Seems pretty durable but easy to use. $10 more than the Chinese made version, but I think it will be worth it by wearing better.

title: New but great so far
author: L. Fox
comments: We have only used this twice but love it.  Light and compact it is perfect for what we want it for.

title: ENO Hammock
author: RT
comments: This is one of the best and most compact hammocks I have ever owned. It is very strong and works great. Also very comfortable.

title: LOVE this hammock
author: Jaimie L Miller
comments: I tried a friends hammock and knew I had to get this one for myself. It's super comfortable and easy to keep clean. Folds up into its small bag and easy to take with me whenever I travel!

title: Awesome Hammock!
author: Kelly
comments: This hammock is amazing.  It folds into itself and can fit in a purse.  I take it everywhere with me.  It is easy to set up.  I love reading in it and taking afternoon siestas in it.  I would highly recommend this hammock to anyone in the market for one.  If you are buying the hammock remember to purchase the straps as well to hang it with.  If you end up purchasing this hammock I hope you enjoy it as much as I am.

title: Not enough stars!
author: Gunnar Laxfoss
comments: Great hammock, Bought this with intentions of just using it for camping, finding myself stringing up whenever i get a free afternoon.Can't say enough good things about it. Price is good. Easy to hang, and durable.

title: Super light-weight and durable
author: L. Simmons
comments: We have used this hammock several times each summer camping.  Our three young kids play in it constantly and the hammock is still as solid as new.  We keep it away from bushes and don't allow shoes while in it.  Very comfortable, lightweight and durable.  Highly recommend.

title: Love it
author: Christan Kramer
comments: Light weight (as hammocks go), durable, versatile, and not too hot during summer days. Any breeze, even at 90+ degrees seems to cool the underside. I couldn't be happier.

title: SO GREAT
author: christy britt
comments: this is the best product ever! i use it allll the time! it is so great I love it, So lightweight so durable so perfect

title: Very comfortable
author: Skyler
comments: Warning, this nest is nap inducing! I like the two person version.  Though small, the hammock is a bit heavier than I imagined, but that is more my imaginations fault.  Overall, great.

title: Love it!
author: Christina Williams
comments: This is the most comfortable hammock I've ever been in. Super easy to put up and take down. You will need the Slap Straps, but they're only $20. Folds away into a bag the size of a grapefruit. I take it with me everywhere.

title: Great quality
author: Angie Wilson
comments: I bought this for a graduation gift and it was perfect. The colors were exact as the photo. Material was sturdy.

title: Quality Product
author: Brian Peck
comments: When they say it's made for two, they really mean two. When I'm in it by myself, it can be wrapped around like a blanket because it's so big. It also feels very durable and secure which is nice.

title: Top shelf product
author: James Schneider
comments: Did my research before buying this and it still exceeded my expectations. High quality construction, roomy and comfortable. Like sleeping in a cocoon. Oh, and spend a couple of extra bucks to get the Atlas straps and you're set. I highly recommend this product and ENO.

title: DoubleNest Hammock
author: John Sestak
comments: This hammock works very well. I ordered another one last year that was the wrong model, but this is exactly what I wanted. Easy to put up, easy to take down, and very comfortable!

title: perfect
author: akshep
comments: I got tired of using tents when i go camping so i got this hammock. With the atlas straps and the pro fly rain fly its the best money i have ever spent.

title: Useful
author: DenDen
comments: Comfortable, light, worked well in a native Amazonian village. The extra width is important since one sleeps in these hammocks crosswise.

title: Extra
author: BSMAN
comments: Great product and no issues after use. DoubleNest gives you a lot of extra material to play with if you plan on running it solo, which is nice. You can wrap yourself with the extra material to block sunlight or help as a blanket.

title: Great hammock, though comes with older carabiners
author: Wm. Enestvedt
comments: The hammock itself is top-notch for the price.It is well-constructed, it has a stuff-sack attached to the side (though there's a weird compression strap & buckle on it that I would have omitted, and which many users remove), and it's every bit as roomy as they say. I hang it up in my back yard and the kids fight over the chance to climb in and rock a while, or I can fall asleep peacefully if they don't notice me. Some day I would like to take it camping when I accompany my son's Boy Scout troop, as many hammock owners do. Regardless, hanging in this hammock makes me very happy.The hammock requires some kind of suspension lines. I initially bought a set of Slap Strap Pros, but they stretch a lot so I am replacing them with ENO's Atlas Straps.Note that I ordered this hammock in June of 2013, and it shipped with the older, solid metal carabiners that the manufacturer had already swapped out for lighter wire-gate carabiners. ENO sells replacement wire-gate 'biners on their web site, but says that these hammocks are essentially NOS and so they won't replace mine. :-( Not a huge deal, since I am not a gram-shaving backpacker, but I would have preferred not to have the sharp edges of the metal carabiners. (I may yet replace them with a pair from REI if it ever really bothers me enough.)

title: Love it
author: Dylan Wilson
comments: East to use setup take down. Slept for 8 hrs in it on the last canoe trip. Fantastic hammock. Love IT

title: easy and weighs nothing...
author: JfOwings
comments: the lightness of this hammock make it easy to carry - comfortable.  A great buy.  I would definitly recommend this to anyone.

title: Son loves it. But get the straps
author: Chaz Hall
comments: My son loves this. Just remember the straps don't come with it. High quality, easy to use. I'd buy it again.

title: Something rotten in the state of Denmark?
author: jack novak
comments: It split in half with no warning.placing me on the ground..............now have to find paperwork............so that I can return it.

title: Wouldn't max out weight
author: JenniA
comments: I love this product but I'm not convinced that it would actually hold 2 people.  I don't even meet the half way mark on weight capacity and it feels like it holds all it wants to hold.  Also, it just wouldn't be that comfortable with 2.  It's a great material though, soft and comfortable to lay in.  The bag on the side is convenient and it wraps up nice and easily!  When mine came in the strap was broken, I should have returned it but I was so eager to use the hammock that I wrote it off as bad luck.  Overall, great hammock!

title: Great Quality
author: Traci
comments: We haven't had this too long yet but so far we love it.  It seems to be very well made and comes with very sturdy carabiners which a lot of the other hammocks I looked at lacked.  We've already ordered a second so we can enjoy them for the summer! I also ordered the Kammock Python Straps to use with this as another buyer recommended and am very happy with them as well.

title: Love the hammock
author: willy w.
comments: Great product.......Well made. Hanging in lanai for now. Use it quite often after bike ride. Good price and light & portable!

title: meets every expectation
author: Kaitlyn Grapis
comments: This hammock was a great choice. But if you're looking to use it for just one person at times, it helps if you double it over or you'll be swimming in fabric, but its just as comfortable that way.

title: great!
author: Briana Morgan
comments: awesome! Good quality great color! easy to set up and take down. great for all ages. doesnt take up a lot of room in backpacks

title: I love this hammock!
author: Tamathi
comments: I have practically lived in this hammock every pretty day after work. I head straight to the park and string it up with my Eagles Nest Outfitters Atlas Hammock Straps. Takes just a few minutes and I'm cuddled up comfortably for a couple of hours. I highly recommend this hammock and suggest also buying this book The Ultimate Hang: An Illustrated Guide To Hammock Camping by Derek Hansen.Happy Hangin!

title: Good Product, Good Price
author: ndkolb
comments: I purchased this product and have used it several times in varying conditions.  I have enjoyed the use of the hammock and feel that it is made well.  It has held up in one wind/rain storm, sub-freezing temps (I did this just to test it out, wouldn't recommend though, it was VERY cold), and heat.  I have only had this hammock a few months so I can't talk to the longevity.  It is light, compact and everything is attached so there is nothing to lose.  My only complaint is that while the initial cost is not that expensive, there is a high cost for all other components.  Straps, bug net, rain cover, etc.  I have had to rig up my own setup for these just to save money. Overall I am please with my purchase and hope to use this for years to come.

title: Great product
author: Matt Stafford
comments: Make sure to get something to keep you warm underneath, my back froze the first time in 40 degree weather. Other than that great product.

title: Eno life
author: E. Sherwood
comments: This is exactly what it says it is: a hammock that you can put up pretty much anywhere. I keep mine in my car at all times in case I want to go on a spontaneous hammocking adventure... Or take a mid-day nap. It's pretty much really awesome.

title: Amazing
author: Joshua A.
comments: I've used my ENO 6 times and love it every time.Only problem I have is I'm to short, and cannot get out of the DoubleNest very easy! That's not the hammocks fault.

title: Great Hammock!
author: J & G Simons
comments: This is a deluxe hammock, we love ours, it's roomy, you can lay lengthwise or width wise.  I'm not saying that there aren't other great hammocks for sale, just saying you will like this one.  Reviews are your best friend!

title: Great Hammock
author: Carlisle Gunn
comments: It's what it says it is.Please note that it is VERY breathable. The wind cuts right through it, so perfect for summer.

title: Eagles Nest Outfitters DoubleNest Hammock (Khaki/Olive)
author: Munda9021
comments: Simply the best.I used this on a cruise balcony. Loved it. My wife really enjoyed it as well. Easily fits 2 people.Prosa. Great quality.b. Looks and feel good too.c. Easy to pack.d. Comfortable.ConsMake sure to buy the strings to attach it to the tree, wall or surface. I bought them from Dicks.

title: Great product
author: D-Dawg
comments: Very portable and user friendly hammock for camping. My daughter loves it and I am actually considering purchasing one of my own.

title: This thing rocks.
author: William I.
comments: I absolutely love this thing. I have only used it once so far but plan on using it a lot.

title: Wow!
author: Spencer Merrell
comments: The reviews were right... this is a great hammock. Super light weight, super strong, and easy to setup and take down. I keep mine in my trunk when not needed for camping along with some paracord and some and have set them up at parks / picknics and friends houses when we are grilling out doors. It's a bit pricy, but I wouldn't buy anything else.

title: great for on the go!
author: vincentm67
comments: I'm impressed with how small it balls up to! Not the best hammock I've been on, but worth the money

title: Great Hammock!
author: Branden Kern
comments: Light and easy to take around! Works well and is a great product! Makes setting up a nice little nest anywhere you go!

title: Love it!
author: JD
comments: I haven't used this camping yet, only around the house. It's easy to set-up, very compact and lightweight. I would recommend the DoubleNest to anyone.

title: love
author: Megan
comments: really love this product! perfect color and fits two! yay enos! cant wait to use it in the warm weather

title: We love our Double Nesk Hammock!
author: Ross Becker
comments: Hammock shipped to us the NEXT day, which was great, because the early spring weather was still unseasonably warm and we were able to lounge immediately!  I own a Hennesey camping hammock and as it is ideal for camping, the Double Nest is great for hanging out in the backyard and on the trail!  Easy to set up, easy to break down and pack up, just make sure you get yourself a pair of SlapStrap Pro's to make things even easier to hang the hammock and support your weight!

title: Fantastic!
author: Nikki D
comments: Love love love this colour! Couldn't find this in the store so I'm pretty happy about it! I don't quite remember if it was a cheaper price or not but I think so because tax wasn't included.

title: Best sleep!
author: Dustan Tye
comments: Always have been a tent camp and I had always heard about sleeping in a hammock and neverliked the traditional spreader bar back yard hammock and decided to give it a try.  I was veryworried about finding the right hammock because I am not a little guy ( 6'5 300+ pounds) and wasvery hesitant how such a small lightweight hammock could hold...boy was I surprised. Was one of the bestnights sleep I have had on a recent canoe trip it puts no pressure on the body so none of the usualtossing and turning and was able to sleep almost flat due to the size and being able to lay at an angle.I am very seriously considering putting hooks up where I can sleep in this at home....haha. The only downfall Icould have with this tent is there is no way I could sleep 2 people in it unless you were very small people and didn'tcare to be on top of each other and swing and move from every moment they make. Most defiantly order the straps forit, sooo much easier the adjust than trying it up with rope.  GREAT PRODUCT.

title: Everyone should get off the ground.
author: Duncan Sprague
comments: Hammock camping is the only way to go.  Assuming you are camping where there are trees.  I don’t remember what I paid for it but it is worth every penny.  Some of my friends have the more expensive hammocks but I can’t see where there is any great difference.  The ENO has good quality and is very light.  Not sure I like the attached stuff sack.

title: Light Weight, perfect fit
author: Amazon reader
comments: It was exactly what he wanted. Thank you and it works great for my backpacking trips. Loved the room for two.

title: Love the doublewide!
author: Mike
comments: I have slept in a few different hammocks before. Mostly cheapies, but I decided to make the investment and paired this up with some eno atlas straps. What a nice combination!I'm fairly light at 160 lbs. and, as you can imagine, felt very secure in this setup. I didn't wake up once through the night thinking I was falling out, which has always been a problem with the smaller hammocks.I don't have a bug net right now, but this hammock is wide enough to put some weight in the attached pouch and sling it over top of me to form a cocoon. It got a little stuffy inside, but it kept the bugs out; and I hate bugs when I'm trying to sleep...hate them.

title: Eno Double Nest
author: Ryan Hutchinson
comments: Do yourself a favor and grab one of these.  Easy to set up and break down.  Super comfy.  A nap wherever you'd like it.  You will not regret it.

title: Love this hammock
author: Amazon Customer
comments: I got this hammock with the Hammock Pawleys Island Tree Straps and they work great together.  I honestly got this hammock for just myself and couldn't see using it with another person for an extended period of time.  However, I would definitely buy this again as it's just perfect for what I wanted (day hiking/car camping, light weight, easy to setup).

title: Awesome hammock
author: Adam S.
comments: I had been eyeballing one of these for a few months and I decided to pull the trigger because I had a camping trip coming up I wanted to take it on. I slept very comfortably and had no issues with the hammock. I have the hammock and atlas straps..now to save up for a rain fly to complete a really cool summer time camping set up.

title: Best gift ever
author: L. M. Sheridan
comments: I purchased this for my son for his birthday.  The product was shipped quickly and was as exactly as the picture showed, the color was perfect.  He absolutely loved it and so did his friends.  Thanks for filling the order quickly and shipping quickly.  My son was thrilled with his present.

title: Love this hammock
author: Bob Miller
comments: I love this hammock so much I bought a second one for my daughter living in New Zealand. Easy to carry. Easy to put up.

title: Better than expected
author: Wayne Julian
comments: I used this 2 weeks ago finally so I thought I would go ahead and do this review. I have only used this 1 time but worked great. It seems like it is really well built and time will be the real test but grandkids and big kids gave it a real workout and it seems to be great

title: Love it!!!
author: Amazon Customer
comments: Got this DoubleNest Hammock for my son for his Birthday and he loves it!  He said it is the BEST gift he ever got!!!

title: I love my Hammock!
author: SydPatt
comments: I bought this to use  mainly in the backyard but it is perfect for travel too. It fits up to 400 pounds so that is great for two people. It has plenty of room, is very sturdy, and the bag is attached to the hammock so you can never lose it!

title: Perfect Hammock
author: Austin, Texas
comments: Our son came for a visit and he had this hammock in his suitcase, it rolls up into a small attached bag- which makes it easy to take anywhere.  We put it up and used it his entire visit, as soon as he left we ordered one for us.  Very easy to put up and take down too. We have had other hammocks but never one we liked as much as this one! Going to order another one. LOVE IT!

title: Love it-Be wary of color
author: SJ
comments: I have had an ENO single nest for about a year now and decided I'm large enough to justify a doublenest. It is significantly more comfortable for sitting and lounging sideways with a little slack, and on windy days can protect from wind chill a little better.One thing I didn't think about (not much of a camper, mind you) is color. I thought "hey, black, that will make it less obvious that there's some guy hanging out  not too far off the main trail." What I forgot is "oh crap, this is black and that's the sun, this is going to get hot really fast."That being said, I'm more than satisfied with the quality of the product. Leightweight grapefruit sized, easy to pack up and throw together, with rope or straps. Many satisfying hang-times will be had with this

title: Super Lightweight but "Buggy".
author: Flippin Hippie
comments: I slept in this hammock the first night I received it. Slept very well in a light sleeping bag. The mosquitoes will nail you through the fabric like it isn't even there, so pack some good bug juice! I'm 225 lbs. and had no issues sleeping in this hammock.

title: Very useful
author: Dcon
comments: Easy to set up, take down, and store. Worth the money if you have the place to hang it. Can be held up by all types of straps easily

title: Nylon hammock
author: glockgirl
comments: Purchased this item over a year ago. It was kept outside about 95% of the time. We washed a few times. We use it a few times a week, mainly my 3 yr get in and players hide-seek. So I was shocked to find it large tear about 36" a few inches down from the yellow/blue seem. I was very much hopping this hammock would last longer then 14m.  Will be looking for new hammock now, but not this brand.

title: Best purchase I've made in time!
author: Dirk Phoenix
comments: I love my hammock, I bought this as a gift, and get plenty of use out of it myself now.I had 4 nieces and nephews jumping around in it and its fine, works great for two peopleas well.. I recommend!

title: Great Colors
author: Adam W
comments: Nothing like getting all cozy while hanging suspended by two trees! This hammock is a great color combo and fits great for camping taking up very little space and weight.

title: No brainer.
author: Danny O'Connor
comments: I've had a few hammocks over the years and nothing even compares to ENO hammocks. They're so quality and yet so light. If you camp or backpack at all, do yourself a favor and get one. I consider it an essential piece of equipment at this point.

title: Great Hammock
author: Benjamin L. Sutton
comments: It is what it is and it works great. Very well made and seems built to last. Can attach it to almost anything.

title: love it
author: julie d
comments: excellent quality love my new hammock , i also ordered slap straps for it.highly recommend this product. looking forward to the summer hammock time

title: Absolutely fantastic
author: edwardss123
comments: We can't live without one of these on our camping trips now.  So much so, we ordered another one.  Really great product and very well made.  Can't go wrong with these.

title: Excelent quality
author: William K. Santiago
comments: Great Hammock very light and excellent quality.  I can be packaged in a small pack and carried around anywhere you go.

title: Good Hammock
author: The Basic Camper
comments: I did not get to sleep in it yet.  The ENO hammock is well made and supports me very well. Easy to set up and take down.I like the attached stuff sack.

title: AMAZING!
author: Informed
comments: I have been wanting one of these for ages! I got my boyfriend one for christmas and I try and use it as much as possible. I have a crappy imitation one from wal-mart; my advice, BUY THE REAL THING! It goes anywhere and everywhere! I live in a city and I use it all the time.

title: Nothing to complain about
author: Doug
comments: It's huge, lightweight, and strong as you'll ever need. The fiancee and I have taken it camping a few times, and also like to set up in the backyard to enjoy pretty afternoons. It stuffs into its own pocket for easy carrying. Not much else to say.Note: No ropes/straps provided. Buy the slap-straps to go with this and never look back.

title: untested so far
author: Mark H.
comments: I purchased this as a gift for my wife. I bought this hammock and the ENO Atlas Suspension Straps 9 ft. We will use them both this summer and review after our experience. I mentioned in my review of the straps that I will be putting this and the straps to the test as I am 6'2 300 lbs. I may have a child in their with me as well so we may be pushing the weight requirements to its limit. Lets see how it holds up.***UPDATE***Just got back from my camping trip and I was able to lounge in the hammock without any issues. I did not add any additional weight with kids. If you are a larger person I can vouch up to 300 lbs using the ENO loops sold separately that are rated for 400lbs. Bumped to 5 stars.

title: Very nice.
author: Levi W. Holden
comments: This is a comfy hammock that compares well to my Kammok Roo, although not quite as comfy as that. It is easy to set up, especially when using a set of Kammok Python Straps, of which I am buying another pair. Both models are very handy for a trip to the park on a lazy weekend afternoon, and are pretty similar in most other respects.

title: Awesome
author: C
comments: We use this all the time backpacking and camping!  Replace the included carabiners with lighter weight ones if you are taking it backpacking.

title: Great Hammock!
author: Pen Name
comments: I have slept in my doublenest both indoors and out around 10 times already.  My only complaint is that it appears a few stitchings on the pouch and hammock have come undone. They have not caused a problem yet and maybe never will.Would recommend to friends!

title: ENO Double Nest - Simply put; Relaxation
author: DG
comments: This is my third ENO to purchase.  I have one and my two college age boys have one.  It is simple to use and provides hours of relaxing opportunities whenever and wherever needed.  I have recommended the ENO to other family and friends!!!

title: Perfect.
author: Meredith
comments: I absolutely LOVE my hammock and it's nice having more room with the double nest. Wouldn't change a thing about it! Can't wait to basically live in it this summer!

title: YES.
author: kristian camero
comments: I got this for my birthday and loved it so much got one for my Fiance and brother! buy this for sure.

title: Exactly what she wanted
author: bobbieturn
comments: Bought this for my daughter to take to music festival weekends, etc.  She loves it.  Packs down very small and is very easy to set up and comfy.  You do have to order your own straps to attach to the trees, though, so be aware of that.

title: The Ultimate Hang!
author: Ultimate Hanger
comments: The eno doublemest is by fat the best and easiest hammock to set up and use. Get the atlas straps and your good to go! You'll never want to aleep in a tent again.

title: Stop reading and click "Add to Cart"
author: Elizabeth Suaso
comments: Trust me.This hammock is simply amazing. I don't know how else to describe it. The material is extremely lightweight and super comfortable. It is also very, very durable.I weigh 240lbs and feel very secure in this thing. I can "wrap" the extra fabric right around me. The doublenest is the perfect size for us big people, and even if we were to become fit, the extra room is just more comfortable. I could lay in this thing forever. It packs down in its own compression bag pretty small. "Grapefruit" size is probably wishful thinking, but it's pretty small considering what it is.

title: disappointed !
author: Jason
comments: This is a good hammock. But their is one " Major " issue. An issue that makes one realize that most companies have no integrity at all anymore. The design of the carabiners that hold this hammock in place, are designed ( it's obvious ) to " Rip " the hammock in order to ruin it within a specified time frame , so as to cause the buyer to purchase another in the future. This is a major character flaw in the company. And certainly is not a mistake, but is done intentionally. Nice hammock otherwise. But i will not buy from this company again. You need extra carabiners, and a slap strap as well. The 70.00 price tag includes none of this ! ! !  If you wish to have a functional hammock then your looking at another 30.00 on top of the seventy. Plus shipping.

title: fast shipper. good product, easy to use. nice. a good buy. fun time. will buy again, got to love it.
author: User
comments: fast shipper. good product, easy to use. nice. a good buy. fun time. will buy again, got to love it.

title: ENO-ing
author: gabriela r stephens
comments: My dad has one, my two sisters have one, my brother has one and several friends have one.  I didn't really realize how cool they were until my recent trip to Central America with my sister.  The hammock packs super small and can be hung pretty much anywhere!  It is so light and comfy and I had to get one.  I am planning a camping trip next week and a backpacking trip this summer on the Appalachian and my ENO is coming on both.

title: No Ropes
author: Penelope
comments: I like these hammocks but they did not send us the ropes that usually come with the hammock.  The ropes are needed to hang the hammock from trees.  I would love it if they would send me the ropes that are supposed to come with the hammock.  I am writing this in the review section because there was not an option to send a claim.  I hope someone gets this message to send the ropes.

title: Everything I expect from ENO
author: Amazon Customer
comments: I prefer this double nest version better than the extended one with an extra strip placed down the middle. It's comfy, strong, light, everything I expect from this brand. Plus, I love the colors, they were true to the picture.

title: Awesome
author: Dylan Foley
comments: I bought this hammock about a year and a half ago. I've used it at a local park and backpacking at 8000' plus (31 degrees). It is a great hammock. Comfortable, sturdy and light weight. The only thing to beware of is the cold. Even a slight breeze will give you a chill factor. When I backpacked with it, I would place my insulation pad in the hammock first, then my sleeping bag on top. Great for casual to serious outdoor use.

title: Nice
author: mark
comments: Awesome hammock.  You will definitely need an underquilt or sleeping pad underneath for colder weather camping.  I actually ended up getting another one as well.

title: Great value, Great hammock
author: Drake Vickers
comments: Great hammock. I'm a bigger guy and this thing is huge. I could almost wrap myself in it like a cocoon. In fact, I might just go out and do that now! Strong hammock, comes with carbiners to hang it up. Does not come with tree straps! so be prepared to get your own.

title: Comfy naps
author: BB man
comments: I love to sling this up between a few trees and go lay in it until the sun goes down.  Great for taking naps and reading as well as camping and exploring.  Good to keep in the car or with you on an adventure, when you aren't sure where you'll be spending the night

title: Much needed reprise
author: C. Lee
comments: This hammock is wonderful.  It can literally be hung anywhere.  I live in MN, so we can't do a whole lot outside right now.  Nevertheless, I have the hammock hanging from a loft in my room, and it is truly a life-saver when I just need to relax.

title: Great for two
author: Kristen L.
comments: hammocks are the #1 best thing to do on my campus. i love this quality and its great for two

title: Awesome Hammock
author: Amazon Customer
comments: I bought this for my boyfriend for his birthday. He absolutly loved it! We took it to a local river and hung it on some trees over the water. When we were done, we just packed it up and put it in my oversized purse.

title: get one
author: Ben Vogler
comments: Good service arrived when expected. Good product. Was as advertised. EVERYONE should T least one time in their life get one

title: The Hammock Faded and Frayed within 1st Month...
author: D. Saul
comments: So disappointed!I am Upset with the actual hammock. I REALLY wanted this for a long time, but it was pricy for a hammock. Finally, I bought for myself for Mother's day.I hung it out on my patio and thoroughly enjoyed it daily. At first I noticed it fraying (Material stretching, I bought a double... One average persons weight should not make the material stretch out?) It was only in a two areas and I really loved reading in it everyday so I ignored it. UNTIL...After a few weeks, I noticed the red stripe around the edge had faded... ALOT!!!! so much it made it look like an old hammock.I called the manufacture (Eagles Nest) which told me that... Indeed they do fade if left out too long. (It was not stated in the advertisements that they should not be used daily?) I would not have bought such an expensive hammock... only to fade and show so much wear after a month!?Here's the CRAZY part.... Eagles Nest told me they could not help me directly since I bought it (here) through a distributor. Here's the worst part, the SELLER did not care to help me at all. When I contacted (MooseHead) they said ...."It was two days past their 30 return policy, SORRY!"I was so mad.... Unfortunately, I was new to AMAZON and did not realize that I could have filed a claim here with them.I decided to finally write this review months later when I came across that old worn out looking hammock in my storage shed. I still love the idea of a compact hammock. It would be great for occassional camping trips. But, I really wanted a permanent hammock for daily use. It's too bad that Moosehead would not replace this item. I both emailed and called and was honestly given the run around.

title: fantastic hammock
author: Robin Leenders
comments: Fits two comfortably, its easy to setup and pack away. I would recommend getting hammock straps to go with it. I actually use ratcheting tiedown straps that work great

title: great!!
author: louie
comments: It is super light wieght easy to pack. Can fit two people or im my case at least three. It seems very dureable but only the test of time can tell that.

title: This kit is in two over seas bags
author: Carole R. Williams
comments: We purchased two of these hammocks for our son and our son in law.  One is a wild land fire fighter and the other is a Air Force JTAC. These hammocks along with a fly, a small stove and a water filter go everywhere these guys go period.DW

title: Userful
author: Alberto Vázquez
comments: This is an amazing product. Really light and supports a lot of weight. It is bigger than other hammocks out there. Definitely recommended.

title: Great Hammock
author: Edgar Lobo Avila
comments: It really works for 2 persons.I like the material and how you can pack it away.I totally recommend it.

title: ENO
author: Rachael
comments: I love my eno! I have had it for over a year now, and it's traveled all over with me. It's the bees knees

title: GREAT
author: J. Tour
comments: Great buy. It's so comfortable. It's great for holding two people comfortably. The color is great and you can wrap up inside and throw the worries of the world away. BUY IT NOW!!

title: Great hammock
author: Alex
comments: This hammock is amazing!  One thing to consider from the start is that when one slender person is laying in it the sides stick up pretty far, making it hard to see out of it.  It also doesn't "sleep" two people very well -- You are jammed in there together pretty uncomfortably, even two very small people.  It does work well as a chair with two people, though.  Overall, however, I love this hammock and love breaking it out on nice days and can't wait to take it to music festivals all summer!

title: Nicew product
author: Deborah A. Dodson
comments: My daughter loved it and has already used it, almost everyday.  She is a college student and I guess it is the new "fad".

title: Hammock perfection!
author: B. Nauman
comments: Strong light material. Packs small, but opens big.  Could not ask for anything more except some included high strength adjustable straps to hang it up.

title: its great
author: Ryan
comments: I love there hammocks i have a few of them. i just went out camping in it the other weekend and i slept great, Make sure you have something under you in the winter time cause it will get cold.

title: BEST way to sleep!
author: Ivy King
comments: I absolutely love my eno hammock!! It's super comfortable, and the double nest has plenty of space. I would actually recommend getting the double nest, even if you are smaller/shorter. I think the extra space increases the comfort level. It is very well made, and seems to be very durable. I also love that it packs up very small, and is light weight. It's much easier to camp with than a tent!

title: great for big guys
author: bellabo
comments: Im an avid backpacker , and this is the first time i ever bought a hammock, and i was a little worried considering in 6 foot 260lbs but it holds be perfectly.

title: Awesome!
author: Abhishek Nath
comments: Compact, durable and very comfy. I recommend you get the new eno slap straps to go with these. I loved it so much on my bike touring trip that I bought another!

title: Totally awesome
author: parker
comments: I have one, my brother has one, several of my friends have one, and they're all just as good as the last one.These things are a BLAST!! We climb a good 30-50ft off the ground and suspend these babys using 550 cord in the trees around my neck of the woods. Super light weight and a joy to use, easily deployable and dependable! true to the rating, you can get pretty close to 400lbs in these without fear of them breaking (I've never pushed the absolute limit for obvious reasons). I've carried my hammock through quite a bit even having it soaking wet and it still holds up like a champ. I even hang it under my bunk in my dorm room for a spot to chill. You don't know what you're missing until you get one.I'd recommend putting a layer of duct tape over the bag to protect it from the various thorns, briars, and limbs you encounter if you find yourself in the bush as often as I do.

title: Great hammock
author: TJ
comments: Great product and it got here soon after ordering. Easy to set up understand instructions too. It does require straps for hanging up (but we already knew that)

title: This was for my college student it came in frayed and looked like a second or third
author: Kevin Charles McNabb Sr
comments: this was a christmas gift for a college student who was going out the day after christmas with his climbingteam for a three day trip and the ENO we got was frayed and unfinished looked worst then a second looked like somrthing that went thou the line and got caught in the machine and was pulled thou and still sent out as 1st quality product had to rush the morning of the 26th and find one in town --not the color he wanted but had to have one for his outing  always have good results with ordering on line this time not so lucky

title: Excellent
author: Mr. DJ
comments: First understand that I am not a fan of sleeping on the ground. Second, I don't like to carry a lot when I go hiking.  So for me this was a perfect match, it is light, durable and easy to put up.

title: Love this!
author: Elizabeth Guzzetta
comments: We love this hammock.  It is a perfect hammock for the outdoors, especially on our camping trips.  Multiple people fit in it with ease.

title: Comfy Hammock for Camping
author: robo
comments: I like it, if your a bigger guy like I am 6'3 250 its not the easiest getting into the hammock with someone else. The material is really thin which worries me that being out in the woods it might snag on a branch or something. Overall not a bad thing to have when you go camping or hiking . It does fold up small and is easy to store.

title: Eno Doublenest Hammock
author: Cheri Williams
comments: Got this for my son for Christmas.  Many of his friends already had an Eno Hammock and take them on their camping trips.  He can't wait to use his!

title: Love my Eno!
author: love amazon
comments: My Eno Double Nest Hammock is amazing. Although the picture shows the body of the Eno as being Khaki and the sides being Teal, it was actually the other way around & actually what I wanted. I LOVE it!

title: Can't wait to use it!
author: Maggie Kelly
comments: I live in Michigan and have had several opportunities to bundle up and use  this hammock, but I should've made sure it came with straps. I guess it didn't really say it in the description though? Just need some straps and i'm set! The colours are beautiful and I've never had a bad thing to say about ENO hammocks.

title: Tiny hammock tolds two!!
author: MWH from NC
comments: I am amazed at this thing.  Folds up small enough to fit into my purse yet holds two people.  Really!!!  The college kids all hang out in these - you can see them hanging between trees as you drive by the campus.  What a reat idea!!

title: Great customer service!
author: Lucy Price
comments: My son got this hammock for Christmas and when he hung it up for the first time, he noticed a small imperfection in the fabric that may have resulted in a tear with more use.  We3 returned it to the vendor and they sent us another very quickly.  My son is going camping next weekend and can't wait to use it!

title: Sent to my son in Afghanistan
author: Laurie Phelan
comments: Sent to my son serving in Afghanistan who is using it to relax with his K-9 partner in his off time.

title: Great For Camping
author: Sparky
comments: My son does a lot of outback hiking in the summer throughout the hills and mountains of NC. He loves this hammock for its comfort and lightweight.

title: Awesome hammock!
author: TK
comments: Got this as a xmas gift and have it setup in my living room to enjoy as I watch TV/read.  It is an awesome product...super comfortable and packs away quite small.  Easy to take with you anywhere!

title: Great hammock.
author: Stevie R. Henrick
comments: I had a doublenest for myself, and I bought this one for my sister. They're great to camp in because they're so small and light and easy to set up. In mild weather, they're perfect by themselves. When it gets colder, I usually line mine with my yoga mat. I also got the ENO rain fly, I'm still perfecting how to hang it so it doesn't sag though. Anyway, great hammock, great brand, perfect for anyone.

title: just what we wanted
author: Dean Brinkley
comments: light weight, easy to use, very comfortable, just what we were looking for for the outdoorsman that back packs or packs light

title: Who needs a tent?
author: Benny B.
comments: Light weight, compact, and easy to set up. I love this thing and it is easy to sleep in. Quality built. So far no problems and I've used it alot!

title: No straps
author: Robert Anderson
comments: Very nice hammock, but does not come with any straps to hang it. You would think for the price of the hammock they would come with straps.

title: Niece loved it
author: alagirl
comments: My niece was so happy to get this!  She already put it up in the house and will be taking it back to college with her.  Y'all had the best color selection and at least $20 cheaper than the store we were going to buy it from.

title: Love, love, love it!
author: Marietta GA
comments: We bought this for our 13 year old son for camping, taking to the park, hanging out in the back yard... I think he will have a hard time keeping it away from my husband (me too)!  Very sturdy, yet lightweight and compact - will be great for camping/backpacking.

title: Great Value for a great product!
author: Jodi Massey
comments: We bought this as a gift and he absolutely loved it! Good quality and typically much more expensive than it was here, which makes it better yet!

title: Eno
author: Kathy
comments: Bought this for my daughter and she loved it.She is going to college this fall and it is the first thing she ask for.

title: LOVE!
author: Brittany Roxanne
comments: I bought this hammock as a sleeping solution.  I have severe scoliosis and the last mattress we bought just wasn't helping.  So instead of trying several other expensive alternatives I researched the most outrageous sleeping solutions  (hoping for some really cool space egg thing) and found out that hammocks are it!This is perfect for me.  I use it with an adjustable hammock stand and line it with a family quilt for those rare colder nights in Florida but aside from a night or two of learning the 30* trick, it's an insta-fit.  It's been two months since my last chiropractic adjustment and I sleep through the night, waking refreshed.So, whether you're planning on using this once a year, one a month or nightly - it's a fantastic hammock.

title: This hammock has been put through the ringer...and
author: Briene
comments: I love my eno! I've gone camping multiple times with it. I've had two people in it...hell I think I've had three. My whole family loves it ! I own a few hammocks and this is my favorite. When it's super hot in the summer it's nice and breezy, When it starts to get a bit chilly outside you can fit all the blankets and pillows you want . I took this hammock to many festivals! It folds into the smallest ball! I assumed I would take it out the first time...and I would never fit it back into a ball ever again lol....but I did!!!! When I'm not off camping I usually leave it up at our camp ground lot.... I am tempted to rig one up in my room.

title: LOVE
author: jpoll
comments: We have had our hammock for about 3 years and use it all the time! It is still like new. It travels very easily. We even recently brought it on a cruise and hung it from our balcony,  We have since bought several for friends as presents and they all love theirs as well. Great quality and easy to use!

title: A great hammock
author: Mickey Chandler
comments: I got this hammock to take to the second weekend of my Wood Badge training, and it was everything that I had hoped for.I did make some modifications to it. After reading the advice of the folks at Hammock Forums, I got rid of the heavy steel carabiners and the rope line that gathers the ends. I replaced them with some "whoopie slings" made out of amsteel, and got some tree straps made out of polypropylene rather than using ENO's Slap Straps which are made of nylon and have a reputation for stretching. The modifications were easy to make and with them the hammock is simplicity itself to setup and take down.So, why didn't this thing get 5 stars?  Because I felt the need to get rid of the stock suspension system and really heavy carabiner for something that is lighter weight and faster to use.  That modification did cost me about as much as the hammock did, but was well worth the money.I've now had this hammock for more than a year and a half. I've got no intention of tent camping again when I have the option of sleeping in this hammock. Since getting the hammock, I've stopped waking up with a sore neck and back and that alone makes this worth the money I've spent on it. My kids like it so much that my older son now has his own Eagles Nest Outfitters SingleNest Hammock and my younger two have homemade hammocks in colors that they picked themselves.Things to look for to get the best use from your hammock: trees that are 12 feet or so apart and trunks that have a diameter of at least 8 inches.

title: Excellent Hammock
author: Cowboy_Up
comments: Very pleased with hammock after 1 year of use. With tree straps and 2 in the hammock, it has held up perfectly.

title: as described but
author: Aaron
comments: ripped with only one person in there in less than a month... for the price i think that I would like a little better quality

title: eno hammock doublenest
author: Daniel Deal
comments: very nice hammock made well and holdes my weight good would buy this hammock again thank you eno Rob Deal

title: Near-Perfect Apocalypse Supply
author: Cuthbertson
comments: When the sky is afire, you will need this hammock. The weak will die and you — one of the pure and brave of heart — will retreat to the hills. It is there that you will need this. It is then that this will save you. The cities (aka "pits of sin") and those within them will doubtless perish, but with this lightweight, versatile, and remarkably comfortable sleeping apparatus, you will be fine. Never leave home without this.

title: Had to buy another one so my husband could stop stealing mine!
author: Beckster
comments: Just bought a second one for my husband since he always seems to steal mine.  I have had mine for a few years and it gets taken on every camping trip in the summer.  Super easy to set up with the optional slap straps.  I enjoy sitting it it sideways if I want to see what's going on around camp but usually I can't stay awake very long in it so I end up lying in it lengthwise/slightly on a diagonal.  I have slept in this on a couple weekend camping trips and it is much more comfortable than the ground, a cot, or a bunk.  I suggest a warmer sleeping bag than you would normally use for the temperature you are camping in since the air on your backside will make you cold sooner.  I only wish we had the right trees to hand it from in our backyard and I would use it every day in the summer!

title: Best Hammock Ever
author: Ryan Southern
comments: I love this hammock.  I use it all the time.  Setting the hammock up is very easy.  The hammock is also very relaxing.I would defiantly recommend this product to everyone.

title: ENOO hammock
author: Matthew
comments: i like this hammock! it is very sturdy and light packs really well for last minute weekend adventures. i havent had one before this but, a friend told me to get one of these because they were good quality and he was quite right. enjoy!

title: Lifes better in a hammock
author: Aaron Burden
comments: My tent is feeling lonely now, because i havent used it since getting this hammock.  Its so comfortable, light, strong, and easy to use!  f you're worried about the cold, just put a good mat and sleeping bag and you'll be fine

title: Love my hammock
author: Just me
comments: The double nest was definitely a good choice - not too big for just one person and it's nice to be able to sit side ways and swing. I've used this so many times, bounced around in it a lot, and it's still in great condition. Awesome bright colors, too

title: Great hammock
author: jwl
comments: I got this hammock last May and have camped in it many times. I swapped out the carabiners and stock cord after a few hangs for a more lightweight suspension, but the carabiners made the job easy for a beginner. Great hammock for camping trips or for simply hanging out in the yard.

title: Chillin'
author: Val
comments: Love this hammock.  First saw it at a festival in NC.  Checked it out on Amazon and found out it was $20 less.  Bought it immediately.  I have a hammock area on my property that I can hang 3 hammocks from and this will just add to my relaxing, chillin' spring & summer & fall days.

title: Great Hammock
author: Sharon Schoch
comments: Great hammock...well made. Grandchildren and adults will love it. Lots of fun for camping, by the lake or just hanging out in your room.

title: Love it
author: Danni
comments: Great hammock for camping or back yard use. Easy to set up, small and compact for storing. Bought the tree straps and I consider them a must. Makes attaching to trees quick and easy. Really comfortable. I did get in it with my husband and I dont think I could sleep in it with him (but we fit). More comfortable with my son ( He is 2) . I am planning on getting the bug net next.

title: The best product
author: M.Whit
comments: I found that this  product is great and that I love to go hammock camping in it for all kinds of things and day hikes.

title: This thing is more than a hammock- it's a people magnet
author: Gregory
comments: The quality is fantastic.  It is easy to stow in a backpack.  If you get this, buy the slap straps too.  I have had it about two years and it has not worn out.  When I take it camping, I have to almost fight to keep people off the thing because it magnetizes them like a tractor beam.  A couple other tips: the "double" is really a spacious single that allows you to cover yourself with material and keep bugs off.  And the orange looks great.  You will not regret this purchase.

title: Says its for two
author: Andrew Powell
comments: But I sleep alone. Its the true way of an highlander. Tomato and Khaki make it look like bloody dirt. Get this. Feels nice.

title: great hammock
author: Micah Doane
comments: I already knew about how awesome these hammocks were before i bought this one, a lot of my friends have them, and now it's awesome to have one of my own, these things rock, although if you do get one, get your own straps and learn how to tie knots cuz the slap straps and slap strap pros are expensive and don't let you hang from things that are far away from each other.

title: Love my eno
author: jairen thames
comments: Love this company and all their products. Super easy to setup and very light to carry. Go ahead and buy the double nest the extra space is worth it.

title: Very Comfortable
author: Wolfman
comments: I took this down and set it up at the beach in the wind. I am 5'11" and weigh over 250. This is a BIG hammock and plenty of hammock below my feet and above my head. Setup was easy with the supplied quick clips. It is so wide that even as broad shouldered as I am there was enough fabric on each side to meet over my head and if I'd had a hairpin could have pinned the edges together; definitely enough for a windbreak or sunshade. Extremely comfortable. I am now an ENO fan.

title: Awesome
author: Pen Name
comments: My order shipped right on time. I am very happy with the product. I've already been camping a few times in it. I'd suggest not purchasing the soap straps though. Heavy duty nylon cordage is inexpensive and if you can tie a knot, you've got a soap strap. I made mine for $10.

title: Enocentric
author: JDW323
comments: I first tried the Eno Hammocks at this years Rockygrass festival at one of there booths. I was impressed immediately and had to get one. The booth & in-store price was koine of steep for myself, a college senior. When I got home I reviewed some of the hammocks & straps & decided to get the Double nest with the Atlas Straps. I highly recommend them both for usability, and ease of use. Hope you enjoy your hammock as much as I have.

title: Forget the tent and sleeping pad.
author: Mr Tech
comments: My girlfriend bought me a ENO double nest hammock early this summer. We used it over a dozen times on backpack trips and on over night parties that we didn't plan driving home from. Greatest gift I have ever received. It is most comfortable with two people in the hammock, but that might just be because we are cuddle buddies. This really saved a ton of weight and space in my our backpacks for camping. It is easy to setup and is way more comfortable than the ground or even an air bed that leaves you on the ground by morning anyways. Only complaint that I have is that during the mosquito season I would recommend a good bug netting or bug repellent. My sleeping bag kept them off my body, but my hands would always get bit up good at night.

title: Great Hammock
author: S2
comments: All of my friends have hammocks so I figured i would get one too. This is a great one. Packs down small, light, nice and breathable. Lives up to all expectations. Leave the ground behind and take to the sky with an ENO Hammock!

title: zzzZZzzz
author: NotTheFilter
comments: I bought this after staring at the two trees in my backyard for a year, thinking a hammock would go perfect in between them. I was right, And this is the perfect hammock for it. It does stretch a bit but simple adjustments with the must have SlapStraps are an easy fix. And don't worry, you'll have no problem fitting it back in to that tiny bag that it comes in. (Which makes a perfect holder for the current book you're reading.)

title: eno
author: joejoe
comments: i was so excited and happy with my purchase that i set it up at home after the camping trip. by the way i think everyone on the camping trip bought one of these. its so much better than a tent in too mamy ways to start explaining. do yourself a favor go out and get one.

title: great hammock great sleep
author: mr. flower
comments: i really like this hammock so far i have been sleeping in it for 5 days and sleep very well. i will be getting another for the wife and a single for the kid...

title: great product.
author: christian
comments: Light weight strong and easy to set up.  So much more comfortable than my tent and sleeping pad.  I like how small the hammock packs down and set up is easy (once you get the correct straps and rope, not included).  better price than the discount sporting goods store in town has too.  great product!

title: Great Hammock!  Changed the way I camp!
author: azfatboy
comments: This hammock is so awesome.  I've used this hammock for a few trips now, and it has changed the way I look at backpacking and camping, primarily by increasing the FUN factor!  I was about to drop some serious cash on those ridiculously expensive backpacking chairs (the ones with only 2 legs that still cost $60+ each!), but with this hammock, I can sit, lay down, nap, lounge, eat, stargaze, and oh yeah... SLEEP!  I have actually been sleeping in this with my wife, and yes it takes some getting used to, but even if we were still sleeping in a tent, I would STILL bring this thing!  The material is thin but strong, and it stuffs easily into a ridiculously small bag.  I paired this with the Kammock Python Straps, and setup/teardown is a BREEZE.

title: Comfort in the extreme
author: M. Tillman
comments: This hammock is, in a word, amazing.  I am a good sized guy (6'2", 220), and it has ample room for me to relax and sway in the breeze.  Easy to set up at home or camping, and really comfortable.  I was a little concerned that I would have a hard time getting it back into the stuff sack, but that was a misguided worry.  You don't even have to try very hard, simply grab the carabiners and roll and smoosh it into the sack, then cinch it down with the included strap.  Takes up almost no room in my backpack, and well worth the space.

title: Best purchase made in some time!
author: TechnicolorTaco
comments: I've been wanting to get a hammock for quite a while now and have been putting it off for one reason or another. I finally broke down and spent some money that I probably shouldn't have spent(I'm sure you all know how that is...) on this hammock. I'm so glad that I did too! I went to the store to buy a couple of eye screws so I could hang it on my patio, and it works perfectly. The website recommends that the objects you hang the hammock from be 10 feet apart, mine are around 9.5 and it still works great, so you do have some wiggle room in there if you are not sure. I can't wait to take this thing out camping, it will be a great relaxation spot. Hope this review helps!

title: Easy. Fun. Comfortable.
author: Tyler
comments: Very light weight, packs down really well. My wife is not much of a camper and she loved it! If you have the extra money to spend, it'll be well worth your dollar. Got a few compliments from other campers as well when we had it set up. If you have kids, they'll love it too :)

title: I absolutely love this hammock
author: Ryan C. Dorn
comments: This hammock has revolutionized my backpacking experience.  Compared to a tent, its much lighter and way more comfortable.  I've only taken it on one trip so far so I can't comment on durability, but dirt and pine needles fell right off and I didn't experience any rips or tears after rolling around in it to test it out. If it does break down or wear out, I'll update this review.  I'm 6'2" 180lbs and the length is just fine.  It's plenty wide enough for two people but I wouldn't want to share it with anyone who I have any personal boundaries with.  You will end up spooning or in continuous shoulder to toe contact.  I haven't tried the single nest but I'd recommend the double nest for one person because the extra space lets you sleep on your side and/or spread out.I strongly recommend the additional accessories, atlas straps, a bug net, and the rain tarp.  A giant swarm of blood sucking mosquitoes would have had their way with my body if it weren't for that bug net...Back to the hammock itself though, the color was true to the picture.  The nylon material felt sturdy and evenly distributed my weight.  The stuff sack is pro all the way around, small, self compressing, acts as a pocket when you have the hammock set up.  The attached carabiners worked just fine too.The setup does have an impact on its comfort, I found I liked it pulled lengthwise pretty tight so I could scoot myself up into a reading position, or droop to the middle a bit to sleep.  Setup was pretty straightforward, no complaints.

title: the best!!!
author: Robert Brodbeck
comments: The longer I have this hammock, the more ways I find to get a great siesta!!  It is so versatile.  You can sit in it, lay in it, hide in it,  get some shade or feel the breeze from the lake.  It is so easy to put up and take down.  You can  take marvelous naps in it.  The double hammock was such a good choice so you can share it or wrap yourself in it or turn sideways in it.  Totally relaxing!!!

title: no zipper
author: doodler
comments: this item was well made, however when it came to closing it up there was no zipper to keep bugs out.....this seemed important as flyers and crawlers could easly get inside when the flap was pulled over.....when you pulled the flap over there was no screen to let in fresh air and since i only camp in the spring and summer it would have been stuffy enclosed in this hammock....i found one with a canvas bottom and 4 sides of misquito netting that felt more like what i was looking for.....amazon was amazing  handling the return....and i would buy from them again and again.

title: Awesome
author: TA
comments: Works great! I was a little worried about if this would really hold 2 people, but it does it easily.

title: Awesome buy!
author: Trevor S
comments: This hammock was a great deal! I use it almost every day whether in my backyard or going camping. Bugs will like you so a bug net would be a good investment but the hammock is great quality and comfort I highly recommend it.

title: A very nice bed replacement
author: Charles Wayne
comments: Let me say first that this has probably been one of the best purchases that I have made, ever. I like trying new things from time to time, so I decided I'd try sleeping on a hammock as a regular every night sleeper. It's comfy, you feel like you're floating in the air rather than being swallowed up by it. I set mine up in a bedroom along with this stand: http://www.amazon.com/gp/product/B000Y0GH5S/ref=oh_details_o03_s01_i00I almost laughed when I got the package in the mail, because the box I got was almost the same size as a small flat rate box from the USPS. I guess I never realized just how small this thing was when completely crushed into it's attached compression bag. It's easy to wash, I just throw it in a cold wash along with my blanket and pillow and it comes out nicely. I'm not so sure that it would  take nicely to the dryer though, so I let it hang to air dry.Durability wise, it's good. It's just beginning to get a little frayed along the edges, but I have been using for three months straight now so I suppose that's to be expected. If you were using it for camping once in a while I'd expect it to have a very long life.
