Though for one person I would recommend this one: http://www.amazon.com/Eagles-Nest-Outfitters-SingleNest-Hammock/dp/B001DDPG9I/ref=sr_1_1?s=sporting-goods&ie=UTF8&qid=1341634130&sr=1-1&keywords=Eagles+Nest+Outfitters There is a little bit too much extra nylon for one person when you have the double nest, but you never know when you might find a crazy hammock gal. ;)In short, it's pretty damn cool to sleep in a hammock every night. It's also loads cheaper to buy a new hammock and a stand rather than buy a used mattress and frame. You also might want to think about everything that happens on a bed before you buy used, which is one of the reasons I decided to get a hammock after sleeping on a futon for a months. Definitely worth the money!

title: Awesome hammock, better than expeted!
author: Tibby
comments: I was initially attracted to this hammock because of the great price, but after opening it up and trying it out I'm completely impressed!  The colors are great, the fabric is extremely comfortable and keeps you cool while you're lying in it, and the little attached bag makes packing it a breeze.  And it's even stronger than listed, it says 400 lb weight limit, and we tested it at almost 500 lbs and it held completely strong!  It's great to spend time in alone, and even better to use to cuddle up with someone else!  I'm completely satisified, and would definately recomend this to anyone looking for a comfortable quality hammock for a great price!

title: SO DURABLE
author: kttttmmmm
comments: ENO products are so trustworthy and are definitely worth the money. I would not spend any money on other hammocking products. You can never go wrong with ENO!

title: ENO Amazing
author: Podhola
comments: I purchased this hammock after hearing from a friend about his. I researched different companies and found this to be the one i bought. The shipping was timely and can't wait to use it camping this holiday.

title: Great Hammock, Heavy Biner
author: Peckface
comments: I ordered this hammock to complete my "one-link" system.  The hammock itself is awesome and generously large.  The built in stuff sack and compression strap make it really easy to stow.  When I first opened it I thought OMG this thing weighs a ton!!  But then I pulled it from the stuff sack and found that it was the steel biners that come with it that are so stinking heavy.  They came off immediately and I think the hammock itself weighs 1/3rd of what it did with both biners.  Buy the hammock and get some ultralight biners like the CAMP NanoWire 23's.  You'll be happy.

title: Very nice well made hammock
author: Ryan
comments: The hammock arrived in a smaller box than I imagined. I bought this at the reference of several friends for camping trips to areas to offroad out 4x4s. The hammock packs up extremely small, and easily folds up to the correct size again. The storage bag is integrated into the hammock, which is kind of cool, it allows you to store stuff in their while you sleep or lie in the hammock! The material is very soft and strong, the ends and rope are heavy duty. I can see this easily supporting the 400 lb limit. All you need is a pillow and a good blanket or sleeping pad and your set for a summers night. There are no straps or ropes for tying the ends included, I intended to make some out of paracord.

title: Love Eno!
author: Lippy
comments: These hammocks are some of the best out there. They are so comfortable and the weather durability is wonderful. They are also very easy to get into. I love Eno products.

title: very nice
author: Danny
comments: I've been looking at these for quite some time now and finally purchased one when they were marked down in price recently.  I wanted it primarily for camping purposes.  I've noticed that a lot of people use these rather than tents.  You can actually buy other devices similar to this that include a rain fly and enclose completely.  They are a bit pricey so I thought that I might grab one of these and experiment with it.  I bought a bug net from a surplus store and a camo tarp from Harbor Frieght for less than $20.  You'll need to get some hammock straps for this.  I tested it out on my back porch just using rope and that worked fine but you'll really need to get some straps for putting it between two trees.  There are a lot of options on Amazon so do a little research to find out what would work best for you.  This hammock folds nicely into a tight little bundle that will fit into the palm of your hand.  It was pretty easy to fold back up too.  If you want this for camping purpose (using this instead of a tent), then you are probably going to want to get a bug net and rain tarp.  The hammock does have a lot of extra fabric that can enclose you but does not have any velcro or snaps to keep it that way.  It falls in your face anyway so it probably isn't the best option.  This hammock is best for summer camping with a bug net.  It is pretty strong...but I have to admit that is was a little freaky getting into it the first time.  It's a great product and it is built with some strudy tough materials that I think will hold up for quite some time.

title: Eagles Nest Outfitters Hammock
author: Wilkstar Woods
comments: I love this hammock and have used it much!  Very lightweight, strong and easily packable.  I love the size of this hammock all packed up and in the backpack. I highly recommend this hammock to everyone!

title: Fan-friggin-tastic
author: Ash
comments: I bought this knowing I'd likely sleep in it more solo than with someone. It's spacey as HELL. I move around a lot and sleep in goofy ass positions, and this was extremely comfy. I'd have to really like the guy I shared it with because mega snuggling would commence; you aren't going to have your own space in this. If someone's a dominant sleeper (steals the covers, kicks, etc) you either want to find a happy place or talk to your sweetie about not being a punk in the night. All in all, best goddamn purchase ever. I've used this puppy not only in the wilderness, but in my backyard, friends backyards and various drunken activities where sleep is eventually required.Word of caution?Be aware of night-time temps and bring a pad or something if needed. I was in the mountains and froze my ass off. There's NO insulation, and your sleeping bag against the night air is just not gonna cut it if it's 40 or below.

title: In love
author: Monkeygirl
comments: This hammock is awesome...its so light and compact...great material and durable...easy to wash and def fits two people. Great for indoor or outdoor use, I have it hung up in my porch 24/7 unless im on a hike and camping then its with me..

title: We're in love...
author: Jeff D. Fennell
comments: Tried this out by myself, and it was awesome.  I was a little skeptical about using this with my girlfriend, but we gave it a shot.  Works wonderfully if we're both sitting, and if one is sitting and the other lays in it.  We both laid in it, and it worked, but if you do try to share it this way, you better be dating!

title: Plenty of space and quality
author: Jesse Vanderhoff
comments: Purchased this hammock as well as the pro straps after spending a healthy amount of time doing research to ensure I purchased the exact product I needed. This hammock has pleased me this far and I do not see if failing anytime soon. It easily compresses to a small size and expands with plenty of room for two people. I would highly recommend this product.

title: Lazy dayz
author: Kot
comments: I am just using this in my back yard but I could see how taking one hiking would be awsome. It is easy to set up, I did purchase the pro slap straps, and stows away very easily. The only thing I would warn you about is unlike a flat hammock on a stand it will wrap you up like a cacoon. All in all I am very satisfied so far.

title: So far so good
author: Kent
comments: Haven't taken it out on the trails yet, but have set up in the backyard and it's perfect.  I highly recomend the Pro Slap Straps to make it quicker and easier to set up.  Takes just a minute or two and you're ready to relax and take in the beauty around you.

title: I'm in love
author: Julie
comments: This is just wonderful. The material in this hammock is so comfortable, and laying in it is so nice. It is absolutely worth the price, and I would highly highly recommend it to anyone and everyone. There are other products out there, some cheaper, some more expensive, and hammocks have become something where you really can look through a lot of options to find what best suits you, but the ENO will not disappoint.One word of caution: This product does NOT come with straps to hang the hammock. I knew this ahead of time, so it wasn't a problem, but sometimes it is not altogether clear on that point that you do need to buy straps separately to hang up your new treasure.

title: Good but...
author: HairyRainDrop
comments: This hammock is very spacious. I am about 5'8" and this hammock encases me in a cocoon when I pull the sides over me.It is very comfortable to lay vertically or horizontally. I have tried this hammock with 2 people and it was still very comfortable.The reason it gets 4 stars is because there are many spots where the stitching is fraying already. It is triple stitched so I am not too worried about it, but there sure are a lot of loose strands.Overall, I would recommend this hammock.

title: Love love love it!
author: Caitlin
comments: This is a great hammock and it easily goes back into the pouch without hassle. It comfortably fits 2 grown adults at the same time and very comfortable for napping because it keeps you wrapped up so you wont fall out.

title: Love it!
author: Timswife
comments: I have bought 2 with the slaps traps for my kids. They are 11 and 17. They take them everywhere. They like to read or just hang out in them. Easy to use. Very comfy. Well made.

title: Not A Double
author: Kindle Customer
comments: I bought the advertised DoubleNest Hammock in Purple/Forest Green.  I received a SingleNest Hammock in a blue/green color.  I figured that the colors were not a big deal, so did not complain.  But it has only just now (past the return date) come to my attention that the hammock is NOT the size I bought and paid for.  It is definitely hard for a first-time hammock buyer to tell this, so make sure upon arrival that your hammock says on the bag-straps that it is a double (because there is a big difference, both in price and size)!

title: Two suggestions
author: Tynemann
comments: If you've never slept in a hammock while camping you're definitely missing out on the most comfortable SINGLE sleeping arrangement possible. Two suggestions: 1. Put your inflatable sleeping pad in your hammock underneath you. It will help keep you warmer. 2. Change out the carabiners ENO sends with this product. I'm not sure what it's called but the two stock carabiners, while appearing strong enough, have a really sharp and abrasive edging on them where the "mouth" or "teeth" of the carabiner closes. This has caught and frayed two of my webbing straps that I use to hang my hammock. Other than that it is a very strong, very dependable hammock. Again, I've only slept in it myself so I don't know what it would be like with two people- although I have the double.

title: This hammock is simply superb
author: wonsnot
comments: I can't find anything wrong with this hammock and I am a large person and it fits me very well.

title: great
author: M. Ervin
comments: worth every penny. great for taking naps in as well. great for presents no matter who you are buying for.

title: Sooo fun!
author: AlwaysAnAdventure
comments: I have slept out twice already since receiving my hammock and I love it! I think it was definitely a good choice to go with the Double Nest as opposed to the Single Nest. It's just a little extra room and you can actually wrap the sides right around you like a cocoon. It was pretty windy the first night we were out and my back was a bit cold, but the second night I put a quilt under me and it was actually colder out that night but I was sooo cozy I didn't want to get up in the morning!! Great investment; I plan on using it all summer. I also highly recommend getting the Slap Straps with it. It literally takes under 5 min to set up that way! I also love that it easily stuffs right back into the little bag attached to it. Often with things like that you can never get it back into the little packing that it came in but I have no problem stuffing the hammock back into its little bag. If you're in to camping it's a great investment, so tiny and light and soo much better than sleeping on the ground!

title: A++
author: Odis Harkins
comments: high quality great I Love the colors and it is the greatest to hang around in! the clips it comes with are heavy but easy to change to lighter ones for hiking!

title: Great for Tall People, worth the money
author: BraceYourself
comments: I'm 6'3", 175lbs, and this is excellent.  It is long enough that I don't have to worry about my feet/head sticking out.  I searched for hammocks a while, and I almost bought a cheap $20 hammock, but all the reviews said the cheap ones fail quickly.  I was in my local Cycle shop and asked what to do. He said "Do yourself a favor man, buy an ENO doublenest and forget about it.  Its worth the extra money you planned on spending, but you'll have it for life. I've had mine for over 7 years, and its still in great condition."  He was right.  I bought the doublenest, and it fits me well.  The extra material allows me to wrap it over me and completely cocoon myself if I want.  I can still lay in it with another person.  It packs up into the size of a softball, and weighs almost nothing.  I even keep my tension straps in the same bag the hammock comes with so I can string it up in a matter of seconds.  If you're debating on whether to get an ENO or a mexican made string hammock for half the price, save yourself the trouble and fly with Eagle Nest Outfitters.

title: 6'7 285lbs and sleep comfortably!
author: biggin5517
comments: The double nest for a guy my size was the only way to go. I have used it a 3 times and have not seen any fraying at the seems like others have said. holds my weight well and is long enough for me and a sleepin bag on a colder night.

title: Awesome!!
author: Bean
comments: This hammock is great.  Hubby bought as a gift for himself, but I want to steal it.  We have hung it up on our balcony and it is wonderful.  We both have laid in it together and with our two small children.  It is easy to get in and out of, even at seven month pregnant.

title: Dont go anywhere without this in my bag
author: mauilove
comments: This hammock is so comfortable and easy to put up. Small enough to fit in a backback or big bag. Bring it with me to the beach or just on a loungy day. Will keep you cool as the wind comes slightly through it. So glad i bought this!

title: Comfortable, durable, lightweight hammock
author: waetherman
comments: It's easy to forget the joy of being in a hammock, but the Eagle's Nest Outfitters Hammock quickly brings back that memory. This is a very compact (about the size of a large grapefruit or perhaps a small cantaloupe) hammock that expands to seat up to 2 adults up to 400lbs total. The hammock is about 8-9 feet long fully extended and it's perfect for lounging just about anywhere. The hammock comes with two carabiners at the ends to attach to whatever fixed point you may have in place, but buyers should note that it does NOT come with any straps, so you'd be smart to buy some. Sadly this raises the total cost for most users to up around $80, and unfortunately it increases the bulk of the overall package when travelling. Particularly frustrating is the fact that the sack which this hammock folds up in to (which is integrated in to the hammock itself and doubles as a handy side pocket when in use) isn't big enough to hold both hammock and straps. That said, packing both hammocks and straps is still a pretty easy affair and the combination easily earns space in my backpack, kayak or suitcase when travelling on vacation. I don't think I'll ever go anywhere without it again.

title: Eno Hammock
author: momtof3
comments: I bought the hammock for my daughter's birthday and she absolutley loves it.  I also bought the straps which make it easier and less harmful to the tree when using it.

title: awesome
author: D. Stout
comments: The product showed up on time and in great shape! I would definitely order this way again. This is a great prodcut. I have one and ordered this one for a friend.Thank you.

title: This Thing is Awesome!!!!!!
author: LaLa
comments: We love this hammock!  So comfy and fits two perfectly! Plenty of room for my 6'5" husband so its great for tall people too.Nice strong fabic and the color is really beautiful and vibrant. We got the Purple/Teal combo.  Ok I must get back to napping in our new hammock.

title: The love this thing..
author: M.Whit
comments: I love this thing cause I do alot of hammock camping and this thingis very much worth the price and its cheaper here then at ENO website. It comes in all kinds of colors and this one also has a warrenty. Your not going to find that with other companys. I love this thing I am thinking of getting another one...

title: Great Product
author: Jugs Hitting Net
comments: Love it! Got one, bought one for a brother, then another. :)Lightweight, sturdy, great for carrying around everywhere you go.Everyone should have one of their own.

title: Double hammock
author: A. Foltz
comments: I didn't buy this for myself, but as a Christmas gift for two incredibly outdoorsy people with lots of knowledge. They were very very excited and assured me this is exactly what they were looking for.

title: Great Gift
author: marye
comments: I bought this for my son for Christmas. He was so excited to take it out in the woods and loves to stay in it watching wild life. It's so easy to set up and can hold him and his sister.

title: Eno Hammock
author: Mrs. Cynthia D. Cornelius
comments: This was a Christmas present that my college daughter wanted.  Evidently this is a must have for college students, they hang out on campus with these.  However ours was missing a silver clip to hang it with.  We had to go to Home Depot and buy her one, missing parts is not what you want for a Christmas present ;( Other than that, it was just what she wanted.

title: Great product
author: sdcashopper
comments: Great buy!  not the lightest, so if you're backpacking alone, get a single, but totally worth it for two people.  No better way to relax with significant other after day of hiking.  It would be better if it came with straps to hand it.  Also, a rusty nail put a quick, one inch rip in it, but its a lightweight product, so its not supposed to be as tough as canvas.  Definitely worth the buy.

title: Liked it too much....
author: molly b may
comments: I bought this hammock as a gift for my daughter and she's now given me my very own.The ENO doublenest hammock is totally comfortable, weighs practically nothing, andeasily survived the two of us. I can hardly wait to take it backpacking.

title: Good
author: Andrew Wildman
comments: Like the hammock. Love eno and their products, have used friends' hammocks before. However, the hammock sent to me was not in the color that I ordered.

title: Way too cool!!!
author: imthebowman
comments: I usually cannot be bothered to enter these reviews but this hammock is just too awesome not to let you all know about it. I wanted to get it to use as a place to sit down/ lay down when I am backpacking. This stuffs into its own attached bag in about 20 seconds and remains rather small (large grapefruit). I have to admit though that I use it all the time even when I am at home. Once you dial in how best to hang it so it doesn't completely encapsulate you, hammock Nirvana can be reached. I am a big guy (225 lbs) and this thing is super sturdy and versatile. You can lounge lengthwise of course but also in a quasi sitting down laying down hybrid by being sideways. I like it so much I just slept in it in my backyard last week and had a completely rest filled sleep experience. I really wish I could give it more than 5-stars. Happy Hammocking!

title: Great Baseline Hammock
author: JT
comments: Dont spend 4 times as much on a hennessey or jungle hammock. The EVO double-nest is probably the most popular hammock among campers and hammock enthusiasts. If you wish to add accessories later (bug net, tarp, underquilt, ridgeline, peapod, etc.), you may do so, and it will cost less and be more customizable than buying one of the more expensive hammock systems. It is tough, light, and 50 bucks. Can't beat it.

title: Tomato/Khaki ENO Double Nest
author: Kristopher A. Mckenzie
comments: This is a great hammock, though a bit expensive for sure. It's comfortable and very wide, and the fabric is porous enough for sweating to not be a problem. I highly recommend buying the slap-straps (regular or pro) as well. They make it easy to hook up to a random two trees or a fence or such...

title: Hammock Camping is Awesome
author: Ken Wargo
comments: I've been backpacking the past 12 years with tents and various combinations of air mattresses, pads, mattresses + pads and have just never been able to get a good night's rest and would actually dread laying down at night.I'm a side sleeper and invariably would end up tossing and turning and wake up with my hips and shoulders hurting more the next morning than when I layed down.  At 50 something years old and having gotten my whole family involved with backpacking, I really needed an alternate solution as the mattress pads were getting larger/heavier and I didn't want to keep adding weight to my backpack.Then...... I discovered the hammock.  Oh..... what sweet relief this thing is.  I can lay almost flat in the hammock.  It rained for 12 hours the first trip out and I was able to lay/sleep in my hammock for those 12 hours and not wake up with those sore hips and shoulders.I am a converted tent camper and can't wait for my next trip now.Side note: The ENO Dry Fly worked ok during that 12 hour rain and did leak a little bit along the top seam.  I came home and sealed it with Seam Sealer, so can't comment on the Seam Sealer just yet.The ENO Pro Straps are conveninent to use, but since they are made of nylon, they stretch during the night and I found myself bumping the ground on the first night.  The second night, I just placed the straps higher up the tree to account for the stretch.  I have now replaced the ENO Pro Straps with polyester straps and a whoopie sling combination for less stretch and more precise "dialing" in of the hammock suspension system.  I will also be adding an adjustable ridge line to really "lock" the setup in place.  I am really looking forward to many more years of backpacking.  I cannot recommend the ENO Pro Straps for backpacking because of the stretch in the nylon.

title: Worth the Wait
author: Teensy Bird
comments: I watched the prices on this hammock for a while before actually buying it, so I could get it on sale. It was definitely worth the wait; I found it for a lot cheaper than I could have in a store and I got free shipping!In an earlier review, someone complained that the hammock they bought on sale ended up being a SingleNest, but the one I bought was definitely at DoubleNest for the sale price.These hammocks are a BIG hit on my college campus. On any nice day you will see a growing number of students napping, studying, or literally 'hanging out' in ENOs. I've seen friends hang their hammocks between columns on porches, inside gazebos, and between trees camping in the mountains.The hammock itself is durable, comfortable, and very lightweight. It comes equipped with 2 carabiners, so if you have rope or SlapStraps you can hang it up as soon as you open it! Also if you are looking at the SlapStraps, definitely spring for the Pros; they have extra length so that you have more options of places to set-up.

title: Great Hammock
author: Tyler
comments: I'm the scoutmaster for our local troop and go on campouts usually once a month.Since Dec. 2010 when I purchased this hammock, I have slept no less than 20 nights in it. It is extremely comfortable, lightweight*, and very large (Doublenest). I would love to purchase a couple more in different colors for my family. ENO makes a great hammock!I sleep exclusively in hammocks on campouts now. No more rocks in my back, no more uneven ground, etc.If you don't like feeling squished or laying like a banana, then hang it so it's got a fair curve to it and then "lay on the diagonal." With your shoulders to one side (left or right) and feet to the opposite side (right or left), you will lay flat in the hammock.* I've modified the suspension to remove the heavier rope and steel caribiners. Search for "Hammock Forums" to find out more.

title: Adds a whole new level of relaxation to your campsite!
author: Amoracat
comments: Got this hammock for a family tent-camping trip, and it was so much fun! Purchased it along with the tree straps for easy hanging.  It is comfortable, soft, and easy to pack.

title: Hammock ENO
author: Rick
comments: WOW! What a sleep experience! First night I tried bedding (pillow/blanket)- that didn't work. Next two nights were a sleeping bag.  Much better. I did not use a bug net, because it was summer. I hear the bugs are only bothersom in the spring and fall. Had a wonderful sleep the third night, cause the park noises subsided.

title: So Comfortable and So Durable!
author: M. McNamara
comments: This thing may be some of the best money I've ever spent on camping gear. I've had my hammock for two weeks and it has already gotten a ton of usage.This thing is so darn (got to keep this PG) comfortable. You can lay in it, you can sit in it, and it is perfect either way.It feels incredibly sturdy. I was a little skeptical at first about how this relatively lightweight material could hold so much weight, but I don't doubt it anymore. While the material is lightweight, the packed up ball is rather heavy. This is understandable, but if you're hiking it is something to consider. The packaged ball doesn't take up too much space.If you are hiking and you wanted to bring this as opposed to a tent, I'm sure the bug netting, rainfly, possibly gear holder would make great accessories and make this a great option for sleeping. I know I wanted to sleep in it.Three suggestions:1) Buy the Pro Straps. They give you a lot of flexibility.2) When hanging your hammock, hang it as tight as it will go. Get in. It will have stretched out a bit. Get out. Hang it on tighter notches if you please. Repeat as necessary. This wasn't as necessary the more times I've used it.3) If you're hanging it on a skinny tree, you may want to wrap the straps around more than once. I looped it around and then through another one of the holes. Not sure if the manufacturer recommends this (so differ to them), but it worked fine for me.Overall, I highly suggest this product.

title: Zzzzzzzzzzzzzzzzzzzzz
author: Charlie McKenzie
comments: What a great product! I secured the Eagles Nest Outfitters DoubleNest Hammock to a couple trees and slept all through the night. I'm a big guy (6'3" and 260 lbs) and this thing was perfect for me. Great purchase!

title: Son sleeps it in even when home...............
author: ATM
comments: Okay, I don't normally take the time to review products, but after this weekend I just had to.  I purchased this camping hammock for my son who is a counselor at a church camp for the summer.  He is in charge of the groups that go out into the 2000 acres owned by the camp instead of the ones that sleep in the cabins.  He had last week off and came home raving about this hammock.  He said it is easy to put up and the most comfortable thing in the world.  It's hard to question this since I went into his room and found that instead of sleeping in his BED while home, he had set up his hammock and was sleeping in it during his week off.  I'd say that is a ringing endorsement of this products since I just spent a lot more money of a new box spring and mattress (name brand) a couple of months ago for him.  Guess I could have saved that money!

title: I love this hammock
author: LindsayLou514
comments: I bought this beautiful hammock a 4 years ago and loved it.  I loved that when I slept in it by myself I had extra room and when my boyfriend and I slept in it together, we had a wonderful night's sleep.  That one was stolen last summer and we immediately replaced it with another one and I got him one for himself for his birthday.  I love this hammock.  The only thing I would change is that I wish it came with ropes.  Everything else is wonderful.

title: Great hammock (with separate attachment straps)
author: ryansamuel
comments: I previously owned a Byer easy traveler hammock until it was lost on my trip through Europe.  I enjoyed the ease of a hammock and thought I'd splurge on a more deluxe model.  The ENO hammock is comfortable, strong, and packaged very well in a small pouch.  The doublenest is plenty big, but still best used as a single.  It's nice to have the extra size, so it's worth the extra 10 bucks in my opinion.  The main downfall is the separate straps that you have to purchase and keep track of when out on the trail.  The easy traveler was an all in one set up, and is a great alternative for someone wanting a simple to use less expensive hammock.

title: Best Purchase!
author: JBryant
comments: This has been one of my most prized possessions! I love my DoubleNest Hammock! I have used it for over 2 years now and have had some of my most fond memories and relaxing moments in this hammock!

title: Worth the Cost...
author: J. Jason Nicholson
comments: I bought this Hammock under the advice of friends and I was very cautious of the price at first. I realize now that this product is well worth the money. I work at a Boy Scout camp for my entire summer every year so this product was the best thing for me. I highly recommend this product to anyone who enjoys the outdoors and is looking for a comfortable place to sleep outside.

title: Great buy!
author: Kayne
comments: Distributor ships these quickly, and they are well packaged. Very comfy and easy to set up and take down. Strong and durable, and they don't hold heat. I wish I had ordered an extra one!

title: ENO double nest hammock
comments: I bought the double nest hammock based on one my brother had on a camping trip. Everyone there could not get enough time in the hammock. I got my own and it is great. Very sturdy and comfortable. It has additional accessories you can purchase that I will definately getting to be able to sleep in the hammock on summer camping trips. Great buy.

title: Great Hammock
author: W. Horn
comments: This is a fantastic hammock. The material is excellent, and it feels very cool while I'm in it. I like the fringe material, which feels looser, and makes for a nice headrest when you lay across the hammock. It is plenty big, and very comfortable. The pouch in which the hammock is stored remains attached to the hammock and serves as a gear pouch when you're laying in the hammock. I used some high strength poly rope to attach it to the neighboring trees, and it works well. It also packs down easily to the size of a grapefruit. I'm very happy with this purchase, and would highly recommend this hammock to anyone looking for a lightweight, small packing, sleep solution for the outdoors.

title: For one person - comfy, for two people - snug.
author: Gabriel Grey
comments: It is billed as a Double Nest, but I couldn't see sleeping two people in this on an overnight in the woods. It's a lot of fun if you want to snuggle up real close to your beloved! You will be VERY close and intimate with them! But if you wanted to hang out in the backyard together both of you reading while you have a cup of coffee - might not work as well! It seems strong and well built, and can hold the weight of two average sized adults. It folds up into a little pouch so you can take it hiking, and weighs next to nothing. Good deal for the price, and for two people who are comfortable being pretty darn close for a couple of hours. But seems impracticle for two sleeping overnight.

title: one night
author: ParamedicTodd
comments: I've only spent one night sleeping in this, but it was awesome!!  Slept very comfortably, was able to side and back sleep, and it took only a couple of minutes to set up and take down.  I will definitely be using it again!

title: So far so good...
author: Tiffany.Minnick
comments: Took this to the park and with the straps it is really easy to set up and takes up VERY little space. Not sure how (2) people would comfortably fit into this but to each their own. I ordered the Olive/Khaki which keep in mind that the picture does not match the actual colors.Very lightweight, easy to carry and easy to set up.

title: Great hammock with the proper setup
author: Brent G.
comments: This brand of hammock is a brand that people either love or hate. I am one of the people who love this light weight hammock. This hammock is the one luxury item that I always take on my ultralight backpacking trips, but only after the proper modifications of course. First, I lost the big black buckle strap that is stitched onto the outside of the attached stuff sack. The strap barely worked if even, and removing it cut some weight. Second, I lost the biners which came with this thing. Those big, hulking, sharp, heavy, abominations were the source of ALOT of the overall weight of this product.... something to the score of over 5 oz. of weight. I always carry 2 VERY light weight climbing quality Blackdiamond Biners with me for various uses around camp, I simply use those when I want to hang my hammock.This hammock is easily modifiable to accomodate much more compact dedicated suspension methods to a high degree of success (think hennessy hammock). It is advisable that these mods may not hold up the weight of 2 people (a single athletic build person would be fine) But if you plan on lounging with your sweetheart after a long days hike, do yourself a favor and get the tree huggers... they add a tad more weight than I would care for but are a surefire way to avoid the dreaded busted coccyx.... (I learned this lesson the hard way)And to people who aren't interested in hiking, camping, backpacking, etc... but want a nice lightweight, colorful, travel hammock that you can EASILY set up almost anywhere that there are some trees, this is worth it.... especially if you get a deal like I got.. Here on amazon I got mine for 20 bucks less than I could have gotten from Backcountry.com, REI, or most any other store. I suggest shopping around!This hammock works great, modded or stock. I Highly recommend this hammock!

title: Why would anyone sleep on the ground when they could hang?
author: B. Fails
comments: Short review: buy this hammock, it is perfect.I bought the Double Nest for 2 reasons.  It was bigger and more roomy than the Single Nest and I'm not a small guy, AND it was on sale for LESS than the Single Nest when I bought it.This hammock is very light, but durable and strong.  It comes packed in its own attached bag which makes a very convenient pouch to stash stuff like your book or a bottle of water in when it's hanging.  The pouch also has a compression strap so you can cinch it down even smaller for packing.  I slept better than I ever have on a camping trip.  The S rings and suspension cords are strong enough to hold two people easily as advertised.You just can't lay in this thing and not feel a peaceful calm.  I recommend hanging near moving water, both for the view in the daytime and the soothing sounds at night.

title: Great Hammock
author: WarEagle86
comments: This is a great hammock; breathable, lightweight (without the stock rope and carabiners...more on this later), quality construction.  Great for lounging around the backyard or using it to camp in the backcountry.  If you're planning on using it around the yard or car camping, then you can easily use it as-is.  However, if you plan on using it for backpacking you might want to think about changing out the stock rope and carabiners for something lighter, such as Whoopie Slings or Cinch-buckles.  Great product either way though!

title: BEST HAMMOCK EVER
author: Patrick
comments: I was quite skeptical even after reading the reviews that this hammock was "awesome"...well i was pleasantly surprised that the ENO Double Nest hammock is all the hype and more!!!! The Double Nest is so comfortable and makes sleeping a ease. It a such a versatile product i even the hammock up in my small apartment. If their is anyone wondering if they should take the leap and buy a Eno Hammock of any kind, definitely do so!!

title: Tons of fun and very relaxing
author: John
comments: What can you say? I love this hammock and the easy portability of it. I've now used it to sleep in while camping, in my local park back home, for quick naps on bike trails, on campus at college, and really your options are only limited by your imagination. The DoubleNest is a must because it gives you extra wiggle room. Two people is definitely a push, but not impossible (you're gonna be in the person's space, so make it a girl you like and you're set!). If you were wondering, practically EVERYONE has the Orange/Grey combo. Doesn't bother me, but I thought I should put it out there.When it comes to sleeping in it while camping, I only recommend warm weather use. I used it in February when we had a warmer weekend here at App State, but the temperature dropped down into the 20s, and we were down in Linville Gorge by the river (across from Devil's Hole). The wind was terrible and came through the thin polyester, especially on the bottom side. Even in my good sleeping bag, I kept waking up because I was so cold, and my toes became numb because I had slid to the bottom of the hammock and my feet were more exposed. The DoubleNest allowed me to wrap the sides around my body like a cocoon, and it definitely saved me from freezing in the wind. ALSO, keep in mind that the polyester WILL STRETCH. This means if you hang up closer to the ground, you will probably end up touching it.All these things to consider just come with the territory, and should be nothing that prevents you from buying one. I know ENO offers a thermal quilt system for like $180 that goes around your hammock, but I'd say just stick to a tent if it's gonna be cold weather. Otherwise, relax and go hammock away. It's by far one of the best purchases I have ever made. (Buy the SlapStrap Pros so you aren't limited in where you can nest up)

title: First time hammock camping
author: Amazon Customer
comments: Had my first scout campout last weekend in my hammock. Woke up with no back pain & slept later than usual at a campout. As a 6' tall middle aged scoutmaster both are important.Tips -- was a cold night, so put an extra blanket between sleeping bag and the hammock. DEFINITELY do use a pad of some kind on colder nights. Woke up a couple times with a "cold spot" where the blanket had slipped from under a shoulder or hip. Next time will try a pad to give a bit more structure.Definitely recommend. Lightweight in the pack, easy to set up. Strung a simple tautline hitch rope over the top -- clipped water bottle and shoes to it. Hung a basic (cheap) tarp over to protect from the dew. I'll not go back to a tent and ground sleeping anytime soon!

title: Super Hammock
author: M. Ross
comments: I've really been enjoying my ENO Double Nest Hammock.  While still extremely light and packs into a very small space, it is stronger and heavier than most others available.  The small additional weight comes from the use of superior components, such as the parachute nylon material, the use of carabiners, and the marine-grade cord that binds the end, but it also gives you more:  More weight capacity, so you can hammock with a friend if you like; More durability that comes from materials that should stand up to longer use; More value that comes from a longer-lasting product that has greater flexibility. (can carry two of you rather than one)  I get more confidence from this hammock, too, as it just doesn't seem as stressed when I get in it as some others that come to mind.  The size is generous, going along with the capacity to hold two people, and there is enough fabric to wrap over one person completely if they are in there solo.  A stuff sack with compression strap comes with the hammock and remains attached to one side - a nice feature.However, it also comes with a higher price tag, and that's something to think about when considering whether the additional capacity and potential durability make it worth it to you.  Is it worth it?  Consider that this one comes with carabiners for attachment:  Do you already have some of these that you can use?  Do you really need them?  (Personally, while I like that it has them, I don't think they are necessary.  S hooks are cheaper but are also perfectly adequate for keeping you and your hammock aloft.  In other words, carabiners are nice, but you are paying for them, too...)  Also, this hammock does not come with attachment ropes.  You can get ENO Slap Straps eno SlapStrap Hammock Suspension Systems - Pro and Regular(which I have used and have also been happy with) but you pay extra for those, too.  Using your own rope or webbing, which both have many more uses than for dedicated hammock duty AND come with mammoth weight ratings, can be a less expensive proposition.  (Rigging your own attachment may confer upon you significant street cred with the survivalist crowd; urban posers like me, however, get the slap straps first and then learn to make my own rope attachments later...)Having said all that, this is a top-quality hammock, with superior components and high quality construction.  What I compare this to most often is the Grand Trunk Ultralight Hammock: Grand Trunk Ultralight Hammock Granted, it's not an apples to apples comparison here, as the Grand Trunk unit is significantly lighter and has a lower weight capacity.  But, I appreciate the huge value that the Grand Trunk hammock represents, as it is a fraction of the cost of the Double Nest AND comes with high-quality and strong (if relatively thin) attachment ropes included.  I've got both and I use both regularly, but in different circumstances.  I love them both, too, so I really couldn't say to choose one over the other - it really depends on your use patterns, frequency of use, and financial wherewithal.So, I can definitely recommend this hammock.  So why only four stars?  Because, well, at this price I think they really could have thrown in a set of ropes rather than selling them to you separately.

title: Excelent Performance
author: JCade3
comments: I bought this hammock and have had nothing but good things from it. I only use this for myself, and it's very comfortable. Single nest probably would've been uncomfortable for me. I bought my own separate ropes to tie it up, and other things among that though. I was able to find ones that were cheaper than offered by ENO and just as good. The hammock itself is excellent though.

title: Very practical
author: gdlg
comments: This hammock is very practical, very easy to hang on trees of with hooks, great for camping or just taking a nap on the balcony.

title: Great hammock
author: Greg
comments: The doublenest is light in weight, compact in size, and sturdy in constuction.  It is comfortable for sleeping on both your back and sides.  I like the ability to customize my sleep setup that eno provides.

title: Wow this Hammock Rocks!
author: Daniel B. King
comments: This hammock is the bomb, service was great and the hammock was delivered on time.A must have for anyone that even thinks about camping or backpacking.

title: Truly a Nice Compact Hammock
author: Mark Scott
comments: Currently using the hammock at work and has been working great on a variety of sets and conditions.I mainly use it for after lunch power naps. I like the double size because you can raise the sides to block out a breeze or lights.The hammock compacts up to about a 9" oblong very nicely with the added straps in it's self attached pouch. I also bought there versatile mounting straps which seem to work very well for the variety of structures I attach it to.

title: WORTH EVERY PENNY!
author: Andrew J. Riemer
comments: I've loved hammocks since I had my first $9 nylon mesh net model at Scout camp more than 20 years ago.  I didn't like getting my fingers (or things attached to my belt) stuck in the little holes, however.  Fast forward to the present day, and I'm a much bigger fellow.  I wanted to find a hammock that could handle a big man, and yet still be light enough to pack in on wilderness adventures, like trips to the Boundary Waters Canoe Area Wilderness (BWCA).That's when I found the Eagles Nest Outfitters (ENO) DoubleNest Hammock.  The DoubleNest may be intended for two with its 400-lb weight rating, but I found it ideal for this big guy--plenty of room and no worries about reaching that weight limit.It packs down quite small, and is very reasonable at less than 1.5 lbs.  Sleeping in it was like heaven!  There was enough material on the sides that I could pull it up around me if the breeze was a bit cool, and I loved how the integrated stuff sack served as a gear pocket so I could store items while at rest.The cordage on the hammock has proven to be resilient, and the carabiner clips on the ends are wonderfully sturdy.  I had no concerns about them breaking.ENO offers a lot of accessories that are compatible with this hammock, including bug netting and a rain tarp, but I've simply been enjoying it as an extra luxury in camp.  I have seen, however, many people in the BWCA set up with just their ENO hammocks as their camping rigs--talk about packing light!TIP---You'll still need straps or rope to attach the hammock lines to the tree trunks.  I took two eight-foot sections of poly cord (with the appropriate weight rating), and knotted the loose ends on each (effectively making two closed loops).  To attach the lines around the tree, I'd just reach a knotted loop around behind the trunk and then fed the looped end through the knotted end (basically, making a larks head know).  I then clipped the hammock's clip to the loop and repeated the steps on the other tree trunk.  If I needed the loop lines shorter, I could just add a knot before the loop.  If I needed more line, I could unknot the loop and just tie it alone.Those loops, however, made setup and takedown very quick, and were far less expensive than buying official hammock straps.OVERALL-------The ENO DoubleNest Hammock is absolutely wonderful.  I strongly recommend one for any of you larger campers, or for campers who are (or, like me, soon will be) light enough to share the DoubleNest with someone they love.

title: FANTASTIC!
author: K. M.
comments: This was THE best nights sleep I've ever had camping! When I went, it was quite cold so I needed my sleeping pad (and let me tell you... learning to sleep in a hammock with a pad and bag can be quite the challenge) to keep my back from freezing. While sleeping in a hammock is a bit more chilly than in a tent, you can easily shift weight and move around unlike in a tent where you move from one side to the other and your hips (or at least mine!) end up seriously painful when morning comes.The set up is super easy - get the slap straps as they are a breeze to use! - and went quite fast. Just make sure you hang it high enough that over the course of the night, your eno doesn't end up on the ground.I've never had any other camping hammock, but I have slept the night in a regular 1 person before and I find that for someone like me who likes to change positions, the 2 person is perfect. Its comfy, packs up easily and is all around amazing!

title: BEST gift for outdoorsy folk
author: WaterBug
comments: Just gave our 3rd ENO doublenest hammock as a gift...these are always a huge success, very well received and appreciated. Have never had anything but rave reviews from recipients (outdoors people, boaters) who love the portability, strength and comfort of these hammocks. They are extremely well made & built-in stuff bag is a big plus. Get the slap straps and you'll optimize location possibilities...straps are well-worth having.

title: THE best hammock!
author: Dmitri
comments: Perfect hammock for festivals and camping!!  Very light weight and easy to put back in bag.  Don't forget to buy the slap straps!

title: Fantastic Hammock!
author: cpen
comments: I bought this hammock as a gift for my brother and he absolutely loves it! He's 6'3" and 180lbs and he fits very nicely in it. It's comfortable, durable, supportive and easy to carry around. For a minimalist that doesn't want to tote around a tent/sleeping bag, this is a great choice. Just grab a pillow and blanket if necessary, and you're set!

title: Perfect for my herniated discs! lol
author: Jason B.
comments: I have two herniated discs in my back-the lowest two in my thoracic-and this product helped me to actually enjoy camping.  I am almost 30 years old and have never been camping in my adult life because of the awkward sleeping positions I have to use to get some shut-eye.Though these hammocks are exceptionally cold in the cooler climates, they are a relief in the humid West Virginia summers.  In cooler temperatures, it is possible to drape one of the space blankets on the underside of the hammock.  The space blanked reflects about 80% of the body temperature back to you so that 20 degree sleeping is actually effective.  By the way, while using this hammock on a 40 degree night in conjunction with a 20 degree bag, I nearly froze to death.I love this hammock! I own two double hammocks and a single.Using nylon straps (very taut) the double nest wraps completely around you cutting down on bug bites and wind (but on on your bottom side!).I hope this helps you guys!

title: Perfect for a family of 4!
author: cadensmommy1
comments: I purchased this hammock for fathers day for my husband. I looked at many types and decided to go with the ENO. I scored big points on this one. Im happy I didnt buy a cheaper version. The fabric is great and the bag you will never lose b/c it all folds up into itself very small and easy to find a spot to store when not in use. It easily fits my husband who is 6'3ft, son(3yrs) and myself-and growing belly!! Awesome hammock not to mention all the colors they come in!! I would definetly recommend the ENO straps to go along with this hammock. Easy as 1,2,3 and its up and time to relax.

title: Double nest
author: D. Curt
comments: I have owned both the single nest and the double nest I love both of them. Really well made and strong. I am close to 250 lbs and my Lab over a hundred and we both have been in it at once with no worry of failure. I bought the slap strap pros to go with this and they work wonderfully as well. To maintain optimum comfort try to keep the side angles close to 30 degrees each and lay slightly diagonal. I will take this hammock everywhere I go!

title: great product, looks different than in pics
author: C. Harrison
comments: I love the functionality of the hammock, but it's definitely not as pretty as in the pictures.  I'm sure that sounds stupid, but I got it for my wife, tried to pick a prettier one that didn't appear "manly", and I got a burnt rusty orange and almost gunmetal gray hammock.  Whoops.  It's much darker than the pictures, I wouldn't have picked it if I saw it in person.

title: ENO Doublenest Hammock
author: Mascovey
comments: I use this hammock on sea kayaking trips around the Western Australian coast and lakes. It packs up very small and is easy to carry. It is very quick and easy to erect and I get comfortable nights sleep. I definitely recommend this hammock.

title: Great product!
author: H. Angeles
comments: I got to try out my friend's ENO singlenest hammock before actually investing in my own.  And I say investment because these hammocks are not cheap.  If you are an amateur and infrequent hammock user there's no need to buy an ENO.  There are other brands that are just as comparable but for 1/3 the price.  However, this hammock is top of the line.  It packs down small, is very lightweight, easy to setup, and is very comfortable for two people.  My husband and I are not large people by any means (I'm 5'4 and he's 5'8") so we fit perfectly without actually smothering eachother.  If you are a single user you may feel swallowed up but the extra fabric is lightweight so I didn't have a major problem with it.  Because these hammocks do not come with straps you must purchase them separately.  I recommend the slap straps pro because of the length versatility.  My friend had the regular straps (which are also very easy to use) but for maximum compatibility with whatever the setup situation may be, I would get the slap straps pro.  There's nothing more frustrating than getting your hammock and not being able to set it up because the trees available are just not quite close enough.  So spend the extra $5-$10 and get pro straps.  I swear it will be worth it!

title: Great Purchase, awesome product
author: mallory
comments: I absolutely love my ENO Doublenest. Some of my friends have ENO hammocks and use them all the time, after testing theirs I knew this was definitely going to be my next purchase. However,I was hesitant about whether to buy a double or singlenest... I ultimately chose the doublenest. b/c I often keep my neice and nephews and I knew they would love to use it, as well as join me in it. I have to say this was the right decision. The weight for both hammocks is 400 lbs but you get a lot of extra width w/ the double. Both my niece & youngest nephew can climb in w/ me and get cozy while I read to them. I also recommend the Slap Straps Pro they really make setting up the hammock SO easy. My oldest nephew who is 10 can set the hammock up all on his own! I just discovered their website [...].

title: Excelente calidad
author: Jaime M. Mejia V
comments: la unica forma de probar su calidad es adquiriendo el producto. si caben 2 personas y si sirve.

title: ENO Doublenest Hammock
author: Texas bargain hunter
comments: I purchased this hammock for my son, who is a college student.  He loves it!  He no longer takes a tent camping, just his ENO and slap straps (I recommend the slap straps pro).  He is now looking to purchase a dry fly.  I've tried the hammock and it is comfortable, sturdy, and the double nest is large enough to wrap around you.  I'm very pleased with this purchase.

title: very good product
author: C. Booth
comments: I have used this hammock about a dozen times since I bought it and I love it.  The hammock is simple to set up and very comfortable.  So far it seems very durable. I would purchase again in a heartbeat.
